ploring how to demythologize certain configurations of imagery and meaning in Western culture that invisibly shape our daily experience of reality and underlay apparatuses of oppression and environmental destruction. As a social change strategist and storyteller he helps groups of people reject stories that present injustice as desirable, inevitable or unchangeable – and collectively creates new narratives, new mythologies that shift power and amplify social movements. He does this as <i>smart</i>Meme\'s writer/director. \r\n<br><br>\r\nJames staffs <i>smart</i>Meme’s Northwest office, providing project management, creative writing, concepting, advertising, and strategic marketing for <i>smart</i>Meme\'s clients and partners. <br /><br />He has participated in many legislative victories from working on direct action campaigns that got the US to adopt nuclear test moratorium legislation in 1992 to developing communications strategies and poltical advertising that helped Rural Vermont usher in the first biotechnology labeling law in the United States in 2004 (Farmers’ Right to Know Genetically Engineered Seed Labeling and Registration Act).\r\n<br><br>\r\nIn 1992 James grabbed his backpack and camcorder and headed to the Great Basin desert of Nevada, leaving behind a career in television news at ABC. He lived outside in the wild for years with the Earth First! movement and leaders of the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.wsdp.org/\">Western Shoshone Nation</a> resisting the U.S. federal government and multinational gold mining companies over issues of sovereignty, bringing media attention to numerous environmental and native rights struggles.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIn 1996 he founded CounterMedia in Chicago to provide alternative media coverage of the Democratic National Convention. Over a hundred volunteers harnessed emerging digital technologies to link grassroots media entities and progressive organizations from around the world, laying the foundation for the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.indymedia.org/\">Indy Media Center</a>  and today\'s global independent media movement.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFrom 2000 to 2003 as a writer/director for the non-profit public interest communications firm <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.sustainusa.org\">Sustain</a>, he managed environmental communications campaigns for clients including the Sierra Club, Rainforest Action Network, Earthjustice, Friends of the Earth, and <A HREF=\"http://www.wcstrategies.com/who.htm\">Wilhelm & Conlon Public Strategies</A> among others. His work has appeared most notably in <i>The New York Times Magazine, The Washington Post,</i> and <i>Communication Arts</i>.\r\n<br><br>\r\nHis afterword to BenBella Books edition of the environmental science fiction classic <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1932100059/lastwizards-20\">The Sheep Look Up</a> by John Brunner explores America\'s love affair with toxic chemicals and shows how science fiction can reshape our assumptions about the world. His essay in <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1932100849/lastwizards-20\">The Battle for Azeroth: Adventure, Alliance, and Addiction in the World of Warcraft</A> follows the trail of “Chinese gold farmers” to uncover a global movement of hackers laundering virtual gold for millions in cold hard cash while exploiting the sweatshop labor of over a 100,000 Chinese gamers. \r\n<br><br>\r\nJames has written extensively on the phenomena of the technological singularity. See his <i>Futurist</i> magazine cover story <A HREF=\"http://www.kurzweilai.net/meme/frame.html?main=/articles/art0584.html\">Exploring the Singularity</A> for a cautionary environmentalist perspective on technological convergence. His other writings on science fiction, mythology, occult philosophy and social change strategy can be found in the book <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/190259388X/lastwizards-20\">Pie Any Means Necessary - The Biotic Baking Brigade Cookbook</a> and <A HREF=\"http://www.lastwizards.com/\">LastWizards.com</A> his personal website. ','','2007-05-23 19:59:09',21,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,1,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','James John Bell',0,'',0,1,'','','left','James John Bell',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(32,'doyle canning','change agent','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">Doyle is a strategist, trainer, and organizer with a big imagination and a deep commitment to social change. She staffs <i>smart</i>Meme\'s East Coast headquarters in Burlington, Vermont.  Most recently, she collaborated on <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.turnyourbackonbush.org/\">Turn You Back on Bush </a> to ring in the second term of Bush rule with mass nonviolent direct action.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDoyle co-coordinates <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://smartmeme.com/article.php?list=type&type=50\"> <i>smart</i>Meme’s STORY program - Strategy, Training &amp; Organizing Resources for Youth </a>, and assists <i>smart</i>Meme clients looking for support in developing their media skills, campaigning strategies, messaging work, or organizing plans. She also gives clients and partners direct support as a facilitator, trainer, action designer, or collaborator and strategy architect.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDoyle has worked on a number of campaigns, projects, and mobilizations—from grassroots, one-on-one work for <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://ruralvermont.org/gmos.html\"> Vermont’s campaign to stop genetically engineered crops </a>, to media strategy and support for the movement against the Iraq war at the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://smartmeme.com/article.php?id=140\"> 2004 Republican National Convention in New York City </a>. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDoyle served as the organizing director at the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://social-ecology.org/\"> Institute for Social Ecology </a> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://nerage.org/\"> Biotechnology Project </a> from 2002-2004, and worked at the leadership of local and national grassroots efforts for people’s food sovereignty. Since 1999, Doyle has helped organize mass actions for global justice in the U.S., Canada and Australia, in places from Quebec City to Miami to Melbourne. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDoyle received her B.A. from Goddard College (‘02), with an emphasis on critical pedagogy and an endorsement as a secondary social studies teacher. In 2002, Doyle was a student-teacher of civics and geography for 9-12th graders in rural Vermont.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDoyle works through STORY to deliver trainings for youth activists in the signature <i>smart</i>Meme curriculum, as well as share traditional organizing and media skills. Doyle occasionally writes commentaries on ecology, vision and strategy for Znet, and has a chapter in the forthcoming book <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://lettersfromyoungactivists.org/\">  “Letters from Young Activists,” </a> (available from Nation Books Fall 2005.)\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen she is not off rabble rousing, Doyle likes to spend her time with her Jack Russell Terrier, Po’teen, walking in the rolling woodlands of New Hampshire. She also loves singing, horses, watching the clouds go by, and gardening.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',21,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(33,'j cookson','change agent','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">J lives in Chicago and staffs <i>smart</i>Meme\'s Midwest office. An award winning filmmaker, intuitive graphic designer, and occasional musician, J brings to <i>smart</i>Meme his creative and visual talents.  As <i>smart</i>Meme’s Creative Director, he is responsible for ad and collateral graphic design, video production, and concepting for creative actions and marketing stunts for <i>smart</i>Meme\'s clients and partners. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nJ is a graduate of the Rhode Island School of Design (RISD) with over 15 years of professional experience working in the visual arts. His past work has ranged from corporate efforts for the likes of Columbia Records, MTV and Nickelodeon, to independent films, interactive video games, music videos, documentaries, and arts and educational projects. J has been a guest instructor at the Art Institute of Chicago and has presented his work at media festivals around the U.S and in Europe.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSince 1999, J has used video and graphic design as tools of documentation, outreach and education to support issues and struggles related to ecological sustainability, food sovereignty, global justice, government and corporate accountability, police brutality, civil rights, housing activism, eminent domain, world peace, and deeper democracy. Incorporating his visual training and skill as a communicator of images and ideas, his current work has been largely reserved for noncommercial social change related services. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nExamples of J\'s past work have included widely seen designs such as the Cheney &quot;Got Oil?” image for the 2002 World Economic Forum, the Eco-Bloc poster design for the 2003 Miami FTAA, and the Krafted campaign\'s giant &quot;Mac &amp; Genes&quot; box. His film and video work has screened in festivals and art museums throughout the U.S. and Europe. He is a regular contributor to numerous publications dealing with current events, independent media and social change. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',21,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,3,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(34,'ilyse hogue','director of the board','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">Ilyse lives in San Francisco. She is one of the founders of <i>smart</i>Meme and assists clients and partners with strategic consulting and training, while shaping the direction of the organization and training curriculum as Chair of the Board of Directors.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIlyse currently works with the <a href=\"http://www.ran.org\"> Rainforest Action Network </a>as the Director of the Global Finance Campaign, which highlights the role of the corporate financial system within the environmental crisis. Her work recently forced Citigroup -- the world\'s largest private financial institution-- to adopt landmark environmental and human rights standards on their international project financing. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIlyse’s experience ranges from electoral campaigns, to Greenpeace USA’s ancient forest campaign, to organizing community-based groups around clean water demands and environmental racism in Austin, Texas. Ilyse has been closely involved with media and organizing around mass mobilizations including those against the WTO in Seattle, the World Bank/IMF in DC, the Democratic National Convention in LA, the UN Summit on Sustainable Development in South Africa, the FTAA meetings in Miami, and the Republican National Convention protests in New York. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nShe has extensive experience as a trainer, campaign strategist and media analyst including work within the independent media movement. Ilyse holds a Master\'s of Science in Resource Ecology Management from the University of Michigan. She has done community-based ecological work in Central America and Australia, as well as in the northern boreal forests of the US and Canada.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',21,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,4,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(35,'patrick reinsborough','change agent','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">Patrick lives in San Francisco and staffs <i>smart</i>Meme\'s west coast office. He engages in strategic consulting, messaging, group facilitation, mass mobilization organizing, media relations, and writing for <i>smart</i>Meme\'s clients and partners. He also helps coordinate <i>smart</i>Meme’s STORY (Strategy, Training &amp; Organizing Resources for Youth) training program.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPatrick is a longtime grassroots organizer, campaigner and media strategist who has worked on a wide range of issues including forest protection, nuclear power, police brutality, urban sprawl, peace in Northern Ireland, indigenous rights, and numerous local and global environmental justice struggles.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPatrick spent four years as the organizing director of the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ran.org\"> Rainforest Action Network</a> where he mobilized thousands of people to confront corporations who destroy the environment and violate human rights. His work included a successful campaign forcing Home Depot to stop buying old growth forest products, campaigns against the oil and finance industries and building an international solidarity network for Colombia’s traditional U\'wa people.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPatrick has been deeply involved in the emerging movement against corporate globalization as a mass direct action organizer, media spokesperson, trainer and educator. He has been involved in organizing numerous mass direct actions from the 1999 shutdown of the World Trade Organization in Seattle to San Francisco’s mass civil disobedience against the 2003 U.S. invasion of Iraq.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHe frequently writes and speaks about the ecology movement, global resistance to U.S. Empire Inc., indigenous rights and the theory and practice of social change.  He has been a guest lecturer at a range of universities including NYU, Stanford and the Annenburg School of Communications.  Several of his strategy essays were recently published by City Lights Press in the anthology <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.globalizeliberation.org/\">Globalize Liberation: How to Uproot the System and Build a Better World.</a>\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen Patrick’s not organizing or dreaming up new geeky revolutionary jargon he spends his time parenting, wandering urban space, learning to play go and playing music for his friends. \r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',21,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,5,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(36,'Strategy Service 1','','This is a strategy service','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',10,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'PRRNC.jpg','A press conference held by the reality check media team at the Republican National Convention, NYC 2004. smartMeme collaborated with other grassroots organizers A press conference held by the reality check media team at the Republican National Convention, NYC 2004. smartMeme collaborated with other grassroots organizers to frame the voices of activists in the streets.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(37,'Communication Service 1','','This is a communication service\r\n','','2004-06-25 19:04:23',11,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','2004-06-25 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(38,'Training 1','','','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',12,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(40,'Eggplant','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eggplant.coop\">Eggplant Active Media</a> is a worker run collective, providing new media and communication services to businesses, communities, organizations and individuals. Eggplant Active Media is dedicated to promoting an ecological and egalitarian society with political, economic, social, and civil freedoms for all people and communities. ','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',55,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'eggplanticonsm.jpg','eggplant.coop',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(41,'Radical Designs','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.radicaldesigns.org\">Radical Designs</a> is a full service web development group focused on the needs of non-profit and grass roots social change organizations. They provide strategic on-line campaign consulting, web design and web application development. Radical Designs programmed this website!','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',55,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,6,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'radicaldesigns.jpg','radicaldesigns.org',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(43,'Fund for Wild Nature','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://fundwildnature.org/\">The Fund for Wild Nature</a> provides small grants to small groups who get things done. They do not fund salaries or overhead. They fund action for wildlife, for endangered species, for rivers, for public lands, for the places and the life that we depend on. <br /><br />They provide this service for free, but they need money to give to organizations doing the hard work in the field. They promise you this: if you give to no other organization this year, your donation to The Fund for Wild Nature will yield results. (FWN gave smartMeme our first grant ever!).','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',55,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,3,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'FFWN.jpg','fundwildnature.org',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(44,'Design Action','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\">><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.designaction.org\">Design Action</a> does graphic design of all sorts. Having been birthed in a printshop, they are especially strong in design for print (posters, newsletters, brochures, booklets, you name it). But they also do banners, t-shirts, logos, and increasingly, websites and other interactive media…They specialize in working with non-profit, grassroots and activist organizations.','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',55,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'designaction.jpg','