n who want to influence debate, shape public opinion and garner positive media attention. SPIN offers public relations consulting, including comprehensive media training and intensive media strategizing and resources to community organizations across the country. We are growing the capacity of organizations to get their voices heard and do more effective media work on issues important to the future of our society. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',56,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'SPIN.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(82,'theory',NULL,'',NULL,'2006-07-19 21:23:23',28,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(83,'news',NULL,'',NULL,'2006-07-19 21:23:23',29,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(90,'mission','<i>Smart</i>Meme builds movements and amplifies the impact of grassroots organizing with new strategy and training resources, values based communication tools and meme campaigning. We communicate a holistic vision of grassroots social change that connects struggles for democracy, peace, justice and ecological sanity.','','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',31,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'smartmememissionsm2.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(93,'origins','subtitle for origins','','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',32,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content this is content','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(94,'our story','We started by daring to think big and imagining a world based on justice, ecological harmony and real democracy. Then we asked ourselves, \"How are we going to get there…?\"','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">\r\nThe <i>smart</i>Meme project grew out of the shared imagination of a grassroots organizer, an advertiser, a filmmaker, and an ecologist turned-international-finance-campaigner. We began as a training project focused on combining grassroots movement building with strategies to inject new ideas into the culture. As we’ve grown, we have supported grassroots mobilizations, provided direct support to grassroots partner organizations, and worked to build stronger movements for a hopeful future. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',33,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(95,'origins','The <i>smart</i>Meme project began in an old growth forest in Washington state as a training circle addressing strategies to build a more holistic and effective ecology movement. ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">\r\nThe <i>smart</i>Meme Strategy &amp; Training Project was founded to contribute to the urgent task of building more holistic, effective and compelling movements for fundamental social change. The project grew out of a training collective formed in July 2002 to conduct a 3 day movement building training at the National Earth First! Round River Rendezvous in the Gifford Pinchot National Forest in Washington state. The collective brought together a grassroots organizer, an advertiser, a filmmaker and an ecologist-turned-international-finance-campaigner to contribute their unique skills to a curriculum for building the “next environmental movement.” The objective of the training was to combine traditional movement building techniques with strategies for projecting new ideas into popular culture and challenging the underlying assumptions of the status quo.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\nAll four <i>smart</i>Meme project co-founders were united in our commitment to fundamental social change to re-orient popular culture around the values of democracy, justice, peace and ecological sanity. We shared a common belief, rooted in our decades of social change experience, that grassroots movements need new strategies to address the rapidly changing cultural and political context of hyper-consumerism, information saturation and corporatized mass culture. Our goal was to design new strategy tools to help social movements contest “idea space” by challenging the underlying assumptions that prevent social change stories from spreading in the dominant culture. \r\n <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',33,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,1,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(107,'menu of services','<i>Smart</i>Meme is a comprehensive source for strategic communications, facilitation, and design. <i>Smart</i>Meme provides a wide range of advocacy communications and movement support services on a fee-for-service basis.','<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><i>Smart</i>Meme is a national strategy center for holistic movement building founded in 2002. We develop and apply narrative power analysis and story-based strategies—frameworks to integrate organizing, messaging, and strategy through the power of storytelling. We bring combined decades of experience in grassroots movements, as well as training in the fields of advertising, advocacy, organizing, film & broadcast media, ecology, and education. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme serves national and grassroots organizations as a comprehensive source for movement based strategy consultation, messaging, meeting planning and facilitation, communications, and design. \r\n<br><br>\r\nOur firm grounding in grassroots social change work enables smartMeme to connect messaging, advertising and branding with a campaigns’ overall organizing strategy. We are not another PR firm – we are a strategy team that will work in collaboration with organizations who share our mission in order to change the stories that are eroding our collective future. \r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Consulting Program offers our partners the following services, all with the approach of story-based strategy:\r\n<br><br>\r\n*	Messaging\r\n<br>\r\n               Production of messaging strategy documents, talking points, branding and brand planning\r\n<br><br>\r\n*	Training\r\n<br>\r\n               Custom training in story-based strategies for client organizations\r\n<br><br>\r\n*	Strategy\r\n<br> \r\n               Opposition research, positioning, campaign strategy development and planning, long-range scenario development\r\n<br><br>\r\n*	Design\r\n<br>\r\n               Graphic design projects including mailers, stickers, logos, web graphics, etc.\r\n<br><br>\r\n*	Advertising\r\n<br>\r\n              Concepting, production, and placement of ads for print, radio, TV, web (and other creative venues!)\r\n<br><br>\r\n*	Facilitation \r\n<br>\r\n              Agenda design, meeting planning consultation, strategy session facilitation for organizations and coalitions\r\n<br /><br />\r\nTo explore hiring <i>smart</i>Meme please contact <a href=\"mailto:james@smartmeme.com\"> partners@smartmeme.com</a> or call 360-898-0041 to chat about what we could do with your organization! \r\n<br />','','2006-09-21 01:56:46',36,0,1,'menu',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'RVTScarecrow.jpg','A full page Ad developed for Rural Vermont in 2005.',0,'',0,1,'','','','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(106,'advertising','Advertising doesn’t have to be just the realm of corporations and huge non-profits.  <i>Smart</i>Meme specializes in finding creative and inexpensive ways to take advantage of this powerful advocacy tool.','\r\n<html><head></head><body><b>Print Advertisement</b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can use our extensive advertising experience to create a print ad that resonates with your target audience, whether it is a small trade publication or a national daily. <i>Smart</i>Meme will assist in the ad’s message development, copywriting, design, publication research and placement. The final ad can even be adapted for posters, flyers or other organizing tools that further leverage its punch.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Guerrilla Marketing Materials &amp; Ads</b><br />\r\n\r\n  \r\nDepending on the target audience it might be more cost effective to use alternative means of reaching your audience.  These could involve guerilla marketing techniques such as non-traditional advertising venues or “wild” options from messaged objects to more dramatic and confrontational tactics like banner drops.  <i>Smart</i>Meme is experienced in implementing guerrilla media and direct action communication strategies.  We specialize in stretching a small ad placement budget to maximum impact.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Television or Radio Ad Scripting and Production </b><br />\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can produce video, radio, film or other moving picture and sound media for commercial broadcast or other forms of distribution such as theatrical release, guerrilla projections or web cast and email applications. Anything from 30-second radio and tv spots to feature length film productions are possible.  The project cost will be largely determined by the length and complexity of the results desired. <i>Smart</i>Meme’s <a href=\"/article.php?id=33\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\">J Cookson</font></a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"> and <a href=\"/article.php?id=31\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\">James John Bell</font></a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"> bring years of professional writing, directing, producing, shooting, editing, and distribution experience to your project.  Please call us to discuss your project and request our portfolio reel.\r\n\r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',35,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(87,'Contribute','','','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',30,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'useraddarticle.php',1,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(109,'partners & portfolio','Our partners and clients range from international nonprofits to homegrown grassroots organizations, and our collaborations reflect our belief in a holistic vision of grassroots social change that links struggles for ecology, democracy and justice. ','\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/downloads/smartMemeClientListOct06.pdf\">Download</a> a list of <em>smart</em>Meme\'s clients and partners from 2004-2006. &nbsp;</font></p><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">This is a showcase of our work, our allies, our inspiration, our partners, and our clients. As a movement building strategy and training project, we strive to serve a wide range of organizations with a wide range of communications, training, and strategy services. We are always excited about the opportunity to work with new grassroots campaign partners in order to help develop and execute winning campaigns.  All of our work is done on a sliding scale and for any given project we will create an estimate, please <a title=\"contact us\" href=\"http://smartmeme.com/contactus.php\">contact us</a>.<a href=\"%uFFFD/article.php?list=type&amp;type=36%uFFFD\">&nbsp;</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><br /></font></p><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">In this section, you can explore a sampling of some of the services we can offer to your organization, coalition, campaign, or project, and browse through a gallery of our allies, coalition partners, buddies, and inspirations.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFor a full listing of our services, <a title=\"menu of services\" href=\"http://smartmeme.com/article.php?list=type&amp;type=36\">click here</a>.</font>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>','','2006-11-28 19:04:02',5,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',0,'',0,1,'','','','',0,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(105,'strategy','Strategy is the art of figuring out how to successfully meet your goals.  <i>Smart</i>Meme works to help grassroots groups design and implement effective strategies for meeting their campaign and organizational goals.','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><b>Campaign Strategy Development</b> <br />\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme works in partnership with coalitions, organizations, or campaign stakeholders to develop multi-tactic advocacy and pressure campaigns.  Utilizing some of our unique strategy tools we can help you power map an issue, identify points of intervention, mobilize a constituency and win a campaign.  Our diverse skill base and extensive campaign experience helps us integrate public education, grassroots organizing and communication components into a cohesive campaign strategy.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Event or Action Organizing</b><br />\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme staff can join you on the ground to support local organizing, help plan a major mobilization or coordinate a strategic action.  Our staff has extensive experience in a wide range of action planning and coordination ranging from small team-based actions, to local demonstrations, to major national convergences and large-scale nonviolent civil disobedience. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Facilitation &amp; Coalition Building</b><br />\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme staff has extensive experience in facilitation, building diverse coalitions and group process.  We can provide a facilitator for any length of meeting, consult on agenda design, group process or collective decision-making.  We specialize in assisting diverse coalitions address strategy, campaigning or messaging issues.  Our facilitators can adapt to whatever process your organization or coalition utilizes or help you find the decision making structure that is right for your situation.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Research, Analysis &amp; Conducting Strategic Think Tanks</b> <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme’s collective maintains an extensive library of advocacy, media, and issue reference material. As veteran researchers we can provide research and analysis support for any project you’re undertaking, from academic to action based.  <i>Smart</i>Meme can also conduct group strategic sessions (think tanks) where we facilitate a one-day or multi-day discussion on an emerging or current issue and/or campaign. These think tank sessions can be combined with one or more of our many  <a href=\"article.php?list=type&type=50\">trainings</a>, to help catalyze new approaches to  critical issues and campaign work.\r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',34,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(104,'what we do','<i>smart</i>Meme\'s mission is to build movements and amplify the impact of grassroots organizing with new strategy and training resources, values based communications, collaborations, and meme campaigning. <i>smart</i>Meme uses the power of narrative to advance a holistic vision of grassroots social change that connects struggles for democracy, peace, justice, and ecological sanity. ','\r\n<p align=\"left\">\r\nWe call what we do <strong> &quot;story based strategy&quot; .... </strong>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<em>Smart</em>Meme is about doing social change in a holistic way : shifting from issues to values, supplementing organization building with movement building, focusing on the intersections of story telling, relational organizing, communications, alliance building and creative new forms of civic engagement and action. \r\n<br /><br />\r\n<em>Smart</em>Meme amplifies the impact of local and national non-profit and grassroots organizations with capacity-building partnerships, collaborations, and new strategy tools to change the stories that shape the dominant culture. We integrate the art of framing, the science of strategy, and the approach of grassroots organizing through our framework of <em>story-based strategy</em>.<br /><br />\r\nStory-based strategy links traditional organizing and movement building work with new strategy, training, and communications methods to give social change workers the tools to hone their story, challenge prevailing cultural narratives, and ultimately win campaigns on the issues. As a movement support and training organization, smartMeme partners with social change organizations to offer strategic consultation and facilitation, messaging and branding, graphic design, advertising, and training. \r\n<br /><br />\r\n<em>Smart</em>Meme has helped win victories for the <a href=\"http://www.preventharm.org\">Environmental Health Strategy Center </a> (Chemical Policy Reform),<a href=\"http://www.ruralvermont.org\"> Rural Vermont </a> (Genetic Engineering), <a href=\"http://klamathrestoration.org/wp/bring-the-salmon-home-un-dam-the-klamath/\">the Klamath Tribes</a> (River Restoration), and <a href=\"http://www.notwithourmoney.org\">Not With Our Money! </a>(Prison Privatization). <em>Smart</em>Meme has strengthened the work of <strong>over 50 organizations across the country, and trained over 1,500 activists since 2002</strong>. \r\n<br /><br />\r\n<em>Smart</em>Meme consulting offers your organization strategy, communications and design services with a story-based approach and an eye for building movements. Contact us for more information at: <a href=\"mailto:james@smartmeme.com\">partners@smartmeme.com </a></p>','','2006-11-28 18:45:37',4,1,1,'whatwedo',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'stephengroupporch.jpg','<i>smart</i>Meme convened the 2006 STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq, a strategy session of youth and young veterans of the Iraq war.',0,'',0,1,'','','','',0,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(161,'Rural Vermont','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ruralvermont.org\">Rural Vermont</a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\"> is a statewide nonprofit farm advocacy group committed to supporting a strong rural economy that is environmentally sustainable and economically just. They work to educate, activate and mobilize our base and the wider community on key agricultural issues vital to the health of our state: genetically modified organisms (GMOs), Recombinant Bovine Growth Hormone (rBGH), large farm and medium farm policy, and the risks of corporately controlled agriculture to our environment and to family farmers. They work closely with <i>smart</i>Meme in Vermont.<br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',57,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,5,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',0,0,0,0,'RVTBanner.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme worked with Rural Vermont to drop this banner at the US-Canada border on the April 17 International Day of Farmers Struggle called by Via Campesina in 2004. ',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(112,'memelab','under construction','<P align=left>The memlab is under construction and will be launching soon, please check back!</P>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',27,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(214,'STORY : Strategy, Training & Organizing Resources 4 Youth','Strategy | Leadership | Movement Building ','\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">In 2004 <em>smart</em>Meme launched our youth training and movement-building program, STORY (Strategy Training and Organizing Resources for Youth). This innovative leadership program provides young activists with training, strategy support, and a peer network to apply story-based strategies. STORY has already trained over 1,000 activists in&nbsp; 20 states, and amplified the work of 15 different youth-based organizations through capacity-building partnerships. <br /></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">STORY activists share a commitment to social change and an awareness of the power of stories in our lives and work. We&nbsp; apply media literacy and narrative power analysis to campaigning for peace, global economic justice, and ecological sanity. We spread the tools and analysis of story-based strategy, and convene collaboratives to build movements. <br /></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Learn More!<br /><br />Download our latest letter on STORY <a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/Fall06STORYappealFINAL.pdf\">here</a><br /></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Visit the new STORY website, <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org\">changing the story dot org! </a><br /></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Contact STORY @ <a href=\"&lt;&quot;mailto:story@smartmeme.com&quot;&gt;\">story (at) smartmeme dot com</a><br /></font></p>','','2006-10-11 20:42:34',69,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'incitegroupondeck.jpg','in 2005 STORY convened the first national conference on story-based strategies, incite/insight,a youth leadership retreat. <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org\">Visit the STORY website...</a>',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','antiwar movement iraq veterans against the war IVAW youth peace',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(213,'The STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq','A youth-based strategy session convened by <i>smart</i>Meme’s STORY Program (Strategy, Training, and Organizing Resources for Youth)\r\n\r\n','<p><strong>Youth and young Iraq Vets are working together for peace in an exciting and timely alliance that needs to be strengthened and supported. To this end, smartMeme’s youth program, STORY, is convening a gathering this summer at the historic Highlander Center in New Market, Tennessee to bring young Iraq Vets and youth anti-war leaders together to strategize about ending this war. We feel this gathering is an essential next step in the process of building a strong, strategic anti-war movement.  </strong><br /></p><p> <br />\r\n\r\n<b>THE SPACE....</b><br><br>\r\nAn intimate 3-day retreat at the historic <a href=\"http://www.highlandercenter.org\">Highlander Center in Tennessee</a> focused on vision, strategy work, cross-cultural movement building and leadership development for young peace activists. The Collaborative emphasizes deepening the alliance of Iraq Veterans Against the War and youth and student peace networks, particularly those working on counter recruitment in youth of color communities. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>THE HAPPENINGS....</b><br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Relationship Building * Story-Based Strategizing * Capacity Building * Movement Building</b><br><br>\r\n\r\nAt the gathering, we will apply some of smartMeme’s story-based strategy tools, and deepen relationships amongst young people working to end the war in communities across the country. We will gather to explore strategies that can harness the historic moment and help to build the strong, grassroots peace movement led by those most directly affected.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<br /><br />In a rural retreat setting, we will take three days to explore narrative power analysis, story-based strategies, creative direct action at the point(s) of assumption, and more! <br /><br />The Collaborative will be a unique and intimate gathering of young activists (18 - 30 years old) working for an end to the war in Iraq and building the movements for justice in the US. The retreat will offer a reflective forum for deep discussions on the system(s), our strategies, movement building, and how the stories we tell can reshape our world.<br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>THE PARTICIPANTS....</b><br><br>\r\nThe gathering will bring together Iraq Veterans, Conscientious Objectors, Counter-Recruitment Activists, Youth from Military Families, Community Organizers, and Strategy People from across the U.S. that are currently doing work around the war. <br><br> \r\n\r\n For more information about STORY <a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/article.php?list=type&type=50\">click here</a><br /><br />For more information about <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">smart</span>Meme <a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/article.php?list=type&type=4\">click here</a></p>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',70,1,1,'about incite/insight',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'highlander.jpg','Highlander will be the site of the 2006 STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(96,'training','<i>Smart</i>Meme has provided our strategy tools and skills training to nearly a thousand grassroots activists in 14 different states and several native nations. ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\"><i>Smart</i>Meme\'s initial movement building training attracted so much interest that we were asked to write a series of follow up articles, which were eventually compiled as “Tools and Strategies for Building an Earth-centered Movement.”  These articles became the foundation for the <i>smart</i>Meme strategy curriculum, which was first presented as an interactive, multi-media training at the National Conference on Organized Resistance in January of 2003.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSince our founding, the <i>smart</i>Meme curriculum has touched thousands of activists and provided tools for re-thinking organizing and media strategies.   <i>Smart</i>Meme has trained nearly 1000 activists in 14 different states and several native nations through our <a href=\"article.php?list=type&type=50\">STORY (Strategy Training and Organizing Resources for Youth)</a> training program. We have written articles and essays on a number of subjects including movement building, successful advocacy communication strategies, and state-sponsored information warfare against grassroots movements.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',33,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(126,'STORY - training program','<i>Smart</i>Meme conducts interactive multi-media skills trainings, focusing on in-depth analysis of media, the power of story, and memes in the context of grassroots social change work.   Our latest initiative is the STORY (Strategy Training and Organizing Resources for Youth) program, which focuses on providing skills and building a culture of strategy among grassroots youth movements.  ','\r\n<p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\"><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<em>Smart</em>Meme conducts a wide range of skills and analysis trainings ranging for short tutorials to intensive multi-day seminars. <em>Smart</em>Meme’s STORY training program focuses on developing youth leadership by supporting emerging youth and student leaders in the peace, environmental, and global justice movements.  \r\n<br /><br />\r\nThe STORY program provides training in media strategies, campaign design, and grassroots organizing skills rooted in <em>smart</em>Meme’s unique <em>power of story</em> strategic intervention curriculum.  STORY also offers individualized consulting and coaching, technical assistance, and organizing resources for youth-led projects for an ecological and equitable future. For more info contact <em>story@smartmeme.com</em>.<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p>','','2006-10-11 20:52:40',50,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'http://www.changingthestory.org/about',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'STORYbar.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(97,'grassroots mobilization','<i>Smart</i>Meme has always prioritized supporting grassroots mobilization.  From the anti-war movement to the largest anti-biotech protest in U.S. history to actions demanding real democracy, we believe that (the right) actions speak louder than words.','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">\r\nIn addition to our training and analysis work, <i>smart</i>Meme has always worked to apply our ideas by directly supporting grassroots struggles as organizers, strategists, and communications professionals.  The <i>smart</i>Meme collective members bring nearly a combined half-century of experience in grassroots advocacy and action.  From Seattle 1999 to the 2nd Bush Inauguration, from the frontlines of wilderness defense and indigenous resistance to the headquarters of some of the world’s largest corporations, <i>smart</i>Meme collective members continue to immerse ourselves in creative action and struggles for justice. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn 2003, as <i>smart</i>Meme was getting underway, we worked to support San Francisco\'s Direct Action to Stop the War (DASW) with action design work and the implementation of an international media strategy to publicize domestic opposition to the U.S. invasion of Iraq. On March 20, 2003, DASW earned its place in history by mobilizing 20,000 people to shut-down the San Francisco financial district with mass civil disobedience to protest the illegal U.S. invasion of Iraq.  (For a <i>smart</i>Meme analysis of the action check out <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.afsc.org/pwork/0311/031118.htm\">San Francisco Self-Organizes to Implode Empire</a> and <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.alternet.org/story/15595/\">In Defense of Cacophony</a>).  Over the next six months, <i>smart</i>Meme continued to provide media support to DASW as it mobilized thousands of people to take direct action against corporate war profiteers such as Chevron-Texaco, Bechtel, Lockheed-Martin, SSA and APL and consistently attracted positive media attention to the anti-war/anti-empire movement. <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme has continued to support mass mobilization organizing with action design, strategy consulting, analysis and media support.  In June 2003 <i>Smart</i>Meme helped to organize the largest U.S. protest against genetic engineering and corporate control of food at the <a href=\"article.php?id=138\">Sacramento Agriculture Ministerial</a>.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn November 2003 several collective members went to Florida to support the StopFTAA mobilization with our communications, media strategy and video production skills. Our analysis piece on the action, <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.alternet.org/story/17293/\">Information Warfare in the Age of Empire</a>, was widely reprinted and helped to promote the idea of confronting state repression and information warfare by waging the <i>Battle of the Story.</i> \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn the summer of 2004 we partnered with the SPIN project to produce <a href=\"article.php?id=145\">Prime Time for Change</a>, an analysis of grassroots advocacy communications strategies at the DNC and RNC. In addition to this report, and numerous mobilization-based trainings in 2004, <i>smart</i>Meme was on the ground in Boston for the DNC, and worked in New York City organizing the Reality Check Media Team to support grassroots mobilization at the Republican National Convention.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',33,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,3,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(98,'partnerships','Since 2004 <i>smart</i>Meme has been applying our unique strategy tools and communication skills to directly supporting grassroots struggles on a wide range of issues.  ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">\r\nIn 2004 <i>smart</i>Meme began partnering with organizations, campaigns and clients to provide our communications and strategy tools and directly support grassroots efforts.  \r\n<br /><br />\r\nWe have been honored to work with frontline activists in numerous movements, and been inspired by the dedication and vision of the countless grassroots organizations we have encoutered in our work.  \r\n<br /><br />\r\nWe’ve helped family farmers in Vermont pass America’s first law to label genetically engineered seeds by supporting their campaign with advertising, communications strategy and on the ground media support.  We’ve used our facilitation skills to bring together a unique coalition of Native American tribes, commercial fisherman and environmentalists, and guide them through a campaign planning and messaging process around dam removal and river restoration in Northern California.  We supported a campaign to get toxic chemicals out of cosmetics with strategy, messaging and a hard-hitting USA Today ad.  We’ve worked with economic justice advocates, public health groups, peace activists, environmentalists, creative arts groups, direct actors, movement training organizations, fellow strategists and grassroots intellectuals. \r\n<br /><br />\r\nWorking with many different groups has given us a chance to explore new creative actions--from trick or treating at corporate criminal’s homes...to “selling” the World Bank on eBay. We look forward to more exciting partnerships and social change experiments soon!\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',33,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,4,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(113,'design and concepting','In our modern image saturated world, grassroots groups and campaigns need the power of graphic design and visual concepting at their disposal. <i> Smart</i>Meme will help you transform your work into powerful images and stories that give your messages the impact they need in order to be seen.  ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><b>Campaign/Organizational Logo Design</b><br />\r\n \r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can develop your organizational identity or a campaign theme into a finished logo. We can do a multi-stage creative process to produce multiple versions of a desired logo and will provide the finished product in both color and black &amp; white applications.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<b>Multimedia Presentation</b><br />\r\n\r\nThe use of power-point presentations and slide shows can often dramatically enhance the quality and reception of your issue/campaign briefing to decision makers, funders, or your constituents.  <i>Smart</i>Meme can design presentations for your organization or campaign that are high quality, effective messages and can be easily replicated through your network or coalition.  We can take the raw elements of what you are trying to communicate, and work with images, story, and sequence to create a presentation that can bring down the house.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<b>Campaign Materials (Action Kit, Posters, Stickers, etc.)</b><br />\r\n \r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can design and produce effective materials for your campaign ranging from mail pieces and fact sheets to unique collateral and high concept organizing materials.  Whether it’s a single flyer or an all-inclusive action kit we sopecialize in designiing specific audience targeted materials, which integrate into your overall campaign strategy and move your message. We can also work with your web team to integrate online components. Don\'t have a web team? We work with some of the best advocacy web designers out there, check out our <a href=\"article.php?id=41\">allies</a>.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<b>Point of Experience Display</b><br />\r\n \r\nStandard campaign information pieces need help in all kinds of environments. An effective way to reach key audiences is through the development of <i>point of experience</i> (POE) media.  POE media is non-conventional, interactive media that can occur at a strategic location or the focus of campaign activity.  POE media can take on many forms, from an innovative info kiosk to walking talking campaign characters.  Multiple POEs could be developed for groups in different areas to use for both attracting passer-by attention as well as earned media coverage. \r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',37,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(114,'communications','The right message at the right time to the right audience can make all the difference in your campaign.  <i>Smart</i>Meme will help you figure out what, how and when to get your campaign’s message out to the world.  ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><b>Comprehensive Strategic Communications Plan</b><br />  \r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme will work with you to develop your campaign’s overall strategic communications plan potentially including (1) marketing strategy (or organizational outreach/marketing strategy), (2) messaging, (3) media planning, (4) and campaign identity development (or organizational branding) plus logo design (see separate descriptions below). \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<b>Developing Marketing Strategy </b><br />\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can help you develop a marketing strategy that can achieve your organizational or campaign communication goals. Through meetings with your organization, team, or coalition, <i>smart</i>Meme will prepare a detailed strategic marketing strategy that identifies key audiences and potential avenues of approach, a list of appropriate marketing components (from guerrilla materials to TV ads) with a corresponding implementation plan tailored to your placement budget (from no budget on up), and provide a timeframe for when and how each of these marketing tools should be implemented to achieve maximum impact.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<b>Messaging</b><br />\r\n \r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can help you identify your messaging goals, and develop a comprehensive messaging document to inform ongoing media work on your campaign or mobilization. We can collect the diversity of messages from your coalition or mobilization and help you synthesize core message frames, sound bytes, and talking points. <i>Smart</i>Meme can also train your organization in the strategic use of these talking points, and can facilitate messaging training to your spokespeople to include reframing, spin, and tactical messaging. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<b>Media Planning</b><br />\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can help you identify your priority media targets for an event or campaign, and develop realistic goals and timelines for your implementation of a strategic media plan.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<b>Campaign Identity Development</b><br />\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme will work with you to create your campaign’s core stories and visual identity. We will construct an overall campaign message through the creation of powerful stories (image/tagline and slogan concepts) that work in concert to convey a consistent message. Special attention will be paid to describing the visual elements - from colors and fonts to a specific visual theme - that will reinforce the main campaign message. These messaging concepts are designed for implementation in future media/marketing components of the campaign ranging from communications materials (e.g., brochures, posters, displays), earned media (public relations campaigns), and/or paid media (advertising campaigns). Campaign logo design can be included.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<b>Organizational Branding</b><br />\r\n \r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can help your organization create a comprehensive branded identity that can communicate the full range of your work and base constituencies.  This process includes a full inventory and evaluation of your organizational image as well as holistic considerations about multiple audiences and organizational outreach goals. <i>Smart</i>Meme will help you find and choose a new name and/or develop a new logo and tagline that conveys powerful core identity narratives.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<b>Public Relations /Media Work: Coaching and Capacity Building</b><br />\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme is available for ongoing PR and communications support.  <i>Smart</i>Meme can develop press releases, pitch reporters, organize media events, draft and place Op-Eds or implement other aspects of a media strategy. <i>Smart</i>Meme can help clients respond to current events as they develop in the media and adjust the overall communications strategy as the campaign progresses.  We provide these services in the context of hands on training and capacity building for grassroots groups.   Activity can include: 	\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n• Research <br />\r\n• Developing a press kit <br />\r\n• Coordination of multiple partners involved in any release or media event<br />\r\n• Assembling target media lists<br />\r\n• Pitching stories to press and subsequent follow-up<br />\r\n• Ongoing media consultation and staff training.\r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',38,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(115,'writing, scripting, production ','<i>Smart</i>Meme’s team of communication professionals can help bring your message to life through good copy writing, scripting or producing your television or radio ad.','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><b>Copy Writing</b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme’s writers are experienced wordsmiths and published authors who can provide your brochure, website or campaign materials with that extra punch that makes them memorable and effective. <i>Smart</i>Meme’s writers will take the sentiment of what you wish to communicate and turn it into effective prose.  Some of our recent writing work includes: ad copy, brochures, direct mailers, web sites, newsletters, reports, and news articles. Please contact <i>smart</i>Meme for our writing portfolio.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Scripting Radio, Flash Animation &amp; TV Ads</b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can develop concepts for a sixty-second radio, flash animation or TV spot and write the final script. We can also work as the producer and direct the final spot. Additionally, we can provide media buying and ad placement services. Please contact us to request an estimate for your project and our tv/radio portfolio.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Video News Release (VNR)</b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can develop, script, produce and direct your Video News Release.   We’ll help you distribute your VNR at press events and/or upload it to satellite for global distribution.  We can work with you to make your VNR downloadable on a web site, and couple it with a comprehensive PR strategy.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>TV Ad, Video &amp; Film Production</b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme can produce video, film or other moving picture media for commercial broadcast or other forms of distribution such as theatrical release, guerrilla projections or web cast applications. Anything from 30-second spots to feature length film productions are possible.  The project cost will be largely determined by the length and complexity of the results desired. <i>Smart</i>Meme’s <a href=\"/article.php?id=33\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\">J Cookson</font></a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"> and <a href=\"/article.php?id=31\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\">James John Bell</font></a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\"> bring years of professional writing, directing, producing, shooting, editing, and distribution experience to your project.  Please call us to discuss your project and request our portfolio reel.\r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',39,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(116,'public lectures and motivational speaking','<i>Smart</i>Meme’s speaker’s bureau of eloquent change agents will transport you to the frontlines of the massive global movements for peace, justice and ecological sanity.  Whether your looking for a deeper analysis, inspirational stories of global resistance or just a booster shot for your own revolutionary imagination, our speakers will educate, entertain and motivate you regardless of your political background or experience level.','\r\n<html><head></head>\r\n<body><p align=\"left\"><b>Public Lectures/Motivational Speaking</b><br /><br />\r\n<b>Speaker\'s Bureau:  Popular Education and Inspirational Lectures</b><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme provides highly skilled and fiery speakers with extensive experience in grassroots social movements who can often provide a behind-the-scenes analysis of recent mass mobilizations or social change trends.  Our speakers weave accessible yet sweeping critiques of militarism and corporate control together with deeply ecological politics to provide a hopeful vision for the future. Recent lectures have included:<br /> <br />\r\no <i>War, Empire and Globalization: Uniting to Confront US Empire Inc.<br /> <br />\r\no Building the Next Environmental Movement <br /><br />\r\no Winning the Battle of the Story: Creating a Culture of Change.</i><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<b>Issue Presentations and Briefings</b><br /><br />\r\nOur speakers can also provide in-depth issue based presentations about a range of campaigns and topics including ecology, earth-centered politics, anti-war organizing, indigenous rights, fossil fuel addiction, resisting biotechnology, globalization, corporate control and the theory and practice of mass social change. We also present hard-hitting documentaries about recent actions or current issues in media theory and cultural criticism.  A complete list of trainings, videos and public lectures is available on request.<br /><br />\r\n</p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',40,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(187,'chicago - version>05','VERSION>05 Tactical Media Festival \r\nMay 1, 2005\r\n5:30 pm Zhou B. Center \r\n1029 W. 35th St. (35th/Morgan)','<P align=left><FONT size=2><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>\r\n Join Us for an Illuminating, Multi-media Discussion on Activist \r\n Strategies, Story-Telling, and Direct Action! </b><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWINNING THE BATTLE OF THE STORY: <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2>\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn order to make change, social movements must tell new stories that challenge status quo assumptions and shape new possibilities for action and transformation.  This \"Battle of the Story\" between grassroots movements and power holders connects our organizing struggles with the ethereal world of culture, media 