is to engage in <i>meme campaigning</i> – campaigns whose main goal is to contest <i>idea space</i> and change the way an issue is framed. <br /></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',45,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(122,'eco-bloc','The ECO-Bloc was a meme campaign which mobilized people to link their struggles for ecological sanity and real democracy.','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><i>Smart</i>Meme’s first experiment with meme campaigning was ECO-Bloc, a meme campaign to make the ecological aspects of the struggle for global justice more visible in the media and the anti-globalization movement. The ECO-Bloc meme was a simple call for people with earth-centered politics to all wear green and form visible ecology contingents in larger global justice events.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme was involved in creating the first ECO-Bloc in September 2002 at the World Bank protests in Washington D.C. The Bloc consisted of over 1000 people and was led by a contingent of indigenous and campesino movement representatives from the global south including Oscar Olivera from the Bolivian anti-water privatization struggle. The contingent marched carrying a banner that read “Global Ecology! Global Democracy!  NOW!” and returned a giant Trojan Horse of Global Debt to the World Bank Headquarters.  A second ECO-Bloc was formed in November 2003 at the Miami Free Trade Area of the Americas protests.  The ECO-Blocs articulated the links between land based struggles, earth-centered politics and the emerging global democracy movement. <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe ECO-Bloc meme was an effort to declare an end to the age of single-issue environmentalism and to name the system of global corporate rule as an over-arching threat to the life support systems of the planet.  Our hope was to stir up some conversation about how the traditional environmental movement could overcome some of its historic white, middle class baggage and articulate a more holistic vision of change. Part of this change was to start thinking of the struggle for global ecological sanity in a broader framework, which includes the massive global movements of land-based resistance such as campesino movements, small farmers networks and indigenous peoples.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMore and more grassroots activists are articulating the link between ecological struggles and movements challenging the undemocratic and exploitive character of the current global system. Perhaps an ECO-Bloc will be forming in your community soon...\r\n<br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',46,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'EcoBlocPoster.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(123,'beyond voting','Democracy is more than just voting: November 2nd to the Polls!  November 3rd to our Communities!','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><i>Smart</i>Meme conceived, developed and launched the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.beyondvoting.org\">Beyond Voting</a> campaign and website in early 2004 to draw attention to systemic flaws in the U.S. electoral process, and connect opposition to the war in Iraq and US Empire with efforts to build a democracy movement inside the United States.  The campaign was designed to harness the momentum of the election year while creating political space beyond the ballot box to build a stronger grassroots democracy movement.  Beyond Voting’s November 3rd national day of action was profiled in TIME magazine’s election cover story, and mobilized people in over 40 U.S. cities on the day after the election to demand real democracy and an end to the occupation of Iraq. <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',47,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'BV-Composite.jpg','1. San Francisco, CA<br> 2. Portland, OR<br> 3. Columbus, OH<br> 4. Pittsburgh, PA<BR> 5. Burlington, VT<BR> 6. Baltimore, MD<br>',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(124,'turn your back on bush','Turn Your Back on Bush was a highly successful meme campaign which challenged Bush’s legitimacy by organizing 5,000 people to turn their backs on Bush’s inaugural motorcade.','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\">In the wake of the 2004 elections <i>Smart</i>Meme worked with the organizers from Turn Your Back on Bush to support a mass <i>direct action at the point of assumption</i> at the 2005 Inauguration. <i>Smart</i>Meme worked in partnership with the core organizing team to design and implement this remarkable mass public display of opposition to the Bush administration’s policies.   Over 5,000 Americans from all walks of life, including veterans, military families, labor and faith community leaders lined the inaugural parade route and turned their backs on Bush’s motorcade.  The mobilization attracted international media attention and helped bring new energy into the U.S. anti-war movement by building a network in over 40 states.\r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',48,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(125,'people power strategy to stop the war','People Power is a simple and essential concept that reminds us that the obedience  and cooperation of the people is what allows any government to rule.  People around the world from Serbia to the Philippines have used people power strategies to overthrow dictators.  What could we do with people power in the US?','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><i>Smart</i>Meme was a founding member of the  <i>People Powered Strategy Project</i>, which has united us with Turn Your Back on Bush, Global Justice Ecology Project, and RANT. Together we drafted a copy of a People Power strategic framework and brought it to the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.unitedforpeace.org\">United for Peace and Justice</a> national assembly.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe proposal promoted the <i>people power</i> meme – the idea that we the people can organize ourselves to directly challenge the structural pillars that maintain the U.S. occupation of Iraq. This strategy is different than lobbying Congress or engaging in general public education. Rather, people power is a strategy to help the people of the United States learn what we have forgotten: the coercive power of government is fragile and when we organize to remove popular support from the pillars that hold up the system, then things can change fast.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPeople power is the strategy that has toppled dictators from Serbia to the Philippines so why not in the US?   People power strategies could not only stop the war in Iraq but also deepen our movements for change by helping us relearn to govern ourselves and be truly free.  To download the People Power Strategy document and to get involved with these growing efforts check out the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.globaljusticeecology.org/\">Global Justice Ecology Project</a> and contact <i>dsolnit@riseup.net</i> (David Solnit). \r\n <br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',49,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(99,'meme campaigns','<i>Smart</i>Meme’s work explores strategies to challenge underlying assumptions and reframe issues through meme campaigning.  ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">\r\nAt the heart of our work is the application of meme theory and Battle-of-the-Story strategies to real world, grassroots campaigns for change. <i>Smart</i>Meme’s trainings have provided activists with tools to engage in ‘meme campaigning’ – campaigns whose main goal is to contest <i>idea space</i> and change the way an issue is framed. \r\n<br /><br />\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme’s first experiment with these ideas was <a href=\"article.php?list=type&type=46\">ECO-Bloc</a>, a meme campaign to make the ecological aspects of the struggle for global justice more visible in the media. <i>Smart</i>Meme was involved in creating the first thousand person ECO-Blocs in September 2002 at the World Bank protests and a second ECO-Bloc in November 2003 at the Miami Free Trade Area of the Americas protests.  The ECO-Blocs articulated the links between land based struggles, earth-centered politics and the emerging global democracy movement. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme also conceived and launched the <a href=\"article.php?list=type&type=47\">Beyond Voting Campaign</a> in early 2004 to draw attention to systemic flaws in the U.S. electoral process, and connect opposition to the war in Iraq and US Empire with efforts to build a democracy movement inside the United States.  The campaign was designed to harness the momentum of the election year while creating political space beyond the ballot box to build a stronger grassroots democracy movement.  The Nov. 3 national day of action was profiled in TIME magazine’s Nov 1st elections cover story, and mobilized people in over 40 U.S. cities on the day after the election to demand real democracy and an end to the occupation of Iraq.   \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe have continued this work by applying some of our tools to support our first mass <i>direct action at the point of assumption</i> the <a href=\"article.php?list=type&type=48\">Turn Your Back on Bush</a> Mobilization at the 2005 Inauguration. <i>Smart</i>Meme worked in partnership with the core organizing team to design and implement this remarkable mass public display of opposition to the Bush administration’s policies.   Over 5,000 Americans from all walks of life participated in the action including veterans, military families, labor and faith community leaders lined the inaugural parade route and turned their backs on Bush’s motorcade.  The mobilization attracted international media attention and helped bring new energy into the U.S. anti-war movement by building a network in over 40 states.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',33,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,5,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(100,'building movements for a hopeful future','<i>Smart</i>Meme is founded on the premise that the best way to insure a hopeful future is for people from all walks of life to build powerful, holistic movements for power-shifting social change.   ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\"><i>Smart</i>Meme’s outreach and organizing efforts have mobilized tens of thousands of people, united diverse constituencies, and achieved international media coverage for a range of issues including: environmental protection, native land rights, economic justice, opposition to the invasion of Iraq, and the need for real democracy. Our images have helped educate and inspire thousands of activists and consumers. <i>Smart</i>Meme strategy essays have appeared in numerous progressive publications and we have produced several compilations of our analysis and writing.  <i>Smart</i>Meme trainers have been invited to speak and share our tools with grassroots groups around the country and internationally, including being invited to participate in the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.caracas2004.info/eng/global/loader.php?&cat=inicio&cont=indice.html\"> World Gathering of Intellectuals and Artists in Defense of Humanity </a> sponsored by the Venezuelan government in December 2004. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe continue our work to support grassroots struggles for democracy, justice and ecology with strategic consultation, training and communications work.  We continue to provide a wide range of trainings for social change activists as well as to design new strategy tools and training curriculums.  All of our work is part of building more holistic movements for a just, democratic, and hopeful future.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEvery day we are inspired by and indebted to our broad network of supporters, clients, comrades, allies and colleagues who tirelessly work for a better world.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIf we don’t already know you, we hope our paths cross soon—and that when they do, we can work together to change the world by changing the stories that shape our lives.  \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',33,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,6,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(101,'change agents','In all of our work, <i>smart</i>Meme collective members bring a commitment to hard work, integrity and a vision of fundamental social change.  ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\"><i>Smart</i>Meme strives to be an effective catalyst for grassroots social change.  Our collective members bring a variety of social change skills and draw from our wide range of experiences working with different movements and networks.  We are united by a common vision of re-orienting popular culture around the values of democracy, justice, peace, and ecological sanity.   \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',21,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'chngagntdropsm.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(102,'who we are','<i>Smart</i>Meme is a non-profit collective of long term organizers, strategists, trainers and communications professionals.','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\">The <i>smart</i>Meme collective is a group of skilled, creative and dedicated change agents who work to support grassroots movements with strategy and training resources, values based communications tools, and meme campaigning. We work to build a culture of strategy, vision, and change, connecting struggles for democracy, peace, justice, and ecological sanity.</p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',3,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(103,'what\'s new','The latest stories, features, announcements, news, and updates from <i>smart</i>Meme.','\r\n\r\n\r\n','','2007-02-22 18:12:54',9,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'CIW1.jpg','Join <i>smart</i>Meme for trainings and more at the first ever national <A HREF= \"http://smartmeme.radicaldesigns.org/article.php?id=197\">Student/Farmworker Alliance SUMMER ENCUENTRO</A>  in Immokalee, FL, August 1-7. Register Soon!',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(190,'trainings and speaking','','','','200