strong>Client:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.greenpeaceusa.org/\">Greenpeace</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</b> Moving Our Messages <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Produced Training Curriculum<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme designed a full campaign message-development curriculum for Greenpeace to use in their rigorous organizer training programs. The curriculum included a wide range of skills areas including messaging strategy, branding, analysis, polling research, and training campaign spokespeople. <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,3,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'Greenpeace.jpg','Another great example of Greenpeace’s media savvy, high profile action for the Earth. <i>Smart</i>Meme contributed to the Greenpeace’s 2004 organizer training curriculum. ',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(127,'Biodiversity Project',NULL,'',NULL,'2006-07-19 21:23:23',51,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(128,'Center for Health Environment & Justice',NULL,'',NULL,'2006-07-19 21:23:23',52,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(129,'links we like','','','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',53,0,0,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(133,'Center for Health Environment & Justice',NULL,'',NULL,'2006-07-19 21:23:23',54,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(134,'Center for Health Environment & Justice','\"<i>Smart</i>Meme provided an in depth analysis for BE SAFE\'s national PVC campaign which increased our media coverage and campaign publicity. Their team provided valuable ideas which improved our national report. Working in a collaborative manner, they assisted us in successfully targeting our audience with an effective message and strategy.\" \r\n--Anne Rabe, BE SAFE Network, Center for Health, Environment & Justice. ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.chej.org/\">CHEJ</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Project:</b> Bad News Comes in 3\'s <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Messaging Strategy Consultation; Message Document Development <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen the Center for Health, Environment &amp; Justice (CHEJ) was looking to launch their report on the toxic impacts of PVC, they worked with <i>smart</i>Meme strategists to develop their messaging strategy, and integrate a corporate campaigning savvy to move their work forward.','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','Bad News Comes in 3’s',NULL,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(135,'Friends of the River','“<i>Smart</i>Meme’s team facilitated our first coalition meetings and fostered trust among diverse groups while moving our agenda forward. <i>Smart</i>Meme’s understanding of cross-cultural issues enabled them to bring together our diverse group of Native American Tribes and conservation groups to build a campaign plan and get it off the ground.”\r\n--Dr. Craig Tucker, Klamath River Campaign Coordinator, Karuk Tribe','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.friendsoftheriver.org/\">Friends of the River</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</b> Bring the Salmon Home! <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Cross Cultural Facilitation, Coalition Building, Assistance Designing a Media Strategy, Campaign Strategy Consultation, Outreach Materials Concepting, Design and Production<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme provided consultation and cross cultural facilitation to help build a coalition uniting environmentalists, four tribal governments and commercial fishermen in a campaign to remove dams and protect endangered salmon species in Northern California’s Klamath basin. In July 2004 representatives of the tribes and other groups traveled to Scotland to protest Scottish Power’s annual shareholder’s meeting and attracted international media attention and public support to their cause. <i>Smart</i>Meme also designed a provocative direct-mail piece for the campaign to build local support in California and Oregon.','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,4,0,'','img',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',0,0,0,0,'FORstacked.jpg','Showing the front four of an eight panel design, this direct mail piece illustrated the cultural, ecological, and economic significance of restoring the salmon to their home in the Klamath’s upper basin. The back panels comprise a historical map of the Klamath Basin.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(136,'Genewise','Partnering with <i>smart</i>Meme is about passion for justice meeting passion for justice; it\'s about empowering each other. Their effect is like a magnifying glass that works with you to set the right fire at the right time…”.\r\n--Christie Phillips, Genewise Coordinator','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.genewise.org/\">Genewise</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</b> Mac &amp; Genes<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Action Design; Graphic Design<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme worked with Genewise to design this “Mac &amp; Genes” box—a spoof on Kraft’s flagship brand—to support the campaign targeting Kraft to remove Genetically Engineered (GE) ingredients from their products. Activists dressed in the box (and Butt Head Phillip Morris) went trick-or-treating in Kraft CEO Betsy Holden’s neighborhood to bring the campaign to the top of the corporate food chain. ','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',0,0,0,0,'Genewise.jpg','Genewise activists trick-or-treat in Kraft CEO Betsy Holden’s neighborhood.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(137,'Hawaii GEAN','“<i>Smart</i>Meme helped our grassroots group develop a media strategy for publicizing the hazards of the genetically engineered papaya. Working from our homes and farms in Hawaii with the help and support of <i>smart</i>Meme, we were able to get our story published in the New York Times, USA Today, the Miami Herald, and dozens of other major media markets across the US and abroad.”  --Noli Hoye, GMO Free Hawaii','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.higean.org/\">Hawaii Genetic Engineering Action Network</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</b> Sounding the Alarm about Genetic Contamination <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Support to Design Media Strategy, Campaign Messaging and Media Plan <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme assisted a coalition of farmers, environmentalists and concerned citizens in launching a public education campaign around genetic contamination of the papaya crop. The group used <i>smart</i>Meme’s tools to develop a comprehensive media plan and organize a media event that alerted the public to the serious dangerous of genetically engineered agriculture. ','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,3,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'HIGEAN.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme helped farmers and activists tell their story about contamination of Hawaii’s papaya.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(138,'Mobilization for Food Sovereignty','“<i>Smart</i>Meme’s work was critical to our coalition\'s success in disseminating our message of resistance and alternatives to industrialized agriculture. We were up against the propaganda machines of the USDA and some of the richest corporations in the world. The fact that people still heard our story speaks to <i>smart</i>Meme’s success in framing, messaging, and strategy  work.” --Tracy Lerman, Senior Organizer, Public Citizen ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> Mobilization for Food Sovereignty<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Project:</b> Hungry for Justice? <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Media Strategy, Messaging, Action Design and Mobilization Media Support <br />\r\n\r\