ates whose members\' face the challenge of the deepening economic recession in rural communities caused primarily by low farm prices and the increasing corporate control of agriculture. <i>Smart</i>Meme attended the 2004 summer meetings of the National Family Farm Coalition to offer strategy support and a “power of story” training for NFFC staff and membership. <br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,5,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'NFFC1.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme  provided media support for a farmer’s action at the 2003 Sacramento Agriculture Ministerial, where US farmers symbolically dumped genetically modified corn outside of then Secretary of Agriculture Anne Venemen’s gala reception. ',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(140,'Reality Check Media/Adopt-an-Activist','“<i>Smart</i>Meme had incredible experience in projecting grassroots messages into the corporate media. Adopt-an-activist partnered with <i>smart</i>Meme to support the Reality Check Media Team, to get the story straight about direct action at the RNC. It was the largest series of demonstrations outside a political convention, ever. Front page all week. The rest is history.” --Meddle Bolger, Director, Adopt-an-Activist','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Partner:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.adoptanactivist.org/\">Adopt-an-Activist</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</b> Reality Check! <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Organizing, Training, Media Support <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen the Republican Party selected New York City to hold its annual convention, New Yorkers started mobilizing immediately to protect the memory of September 11 from exploitation by the hawks in the GOP, and trumpet a resounding NO to the Bush agenda. <i>smart</i>Meme and Adopt-an-Activist partnered to bring <i>smart</i>Meme to New York for a six week project that became the “Reality Check A31 Media Team.” Reality Check trained activists, amplified voices, and made media space to tell the stories about peace, democracy, nonviolent civil disobedience at the 2004 RNC. <br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,6,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'RNCmont.jpg','From top to bottom: <BR>1.) Demonstrators in Herald Square chanting behind the live shot of “Hardball with Chris Matthews” on August 31st <BR>2.) Demonstrators “die in” at Halliburton on August 31st, 2004<BR>3.) September 1st: Reality Check-organized press conference to free the 1,000+ detainees at Pier 57.<BR>4.) Aug 29th UFPJ march live on C-SPAN',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(142,'Reclaim the Commons','\"<i>Smart</i>Meme provided invaluable creative, strategic, and practical guidance for the Reclaim the Commons media team. They skillfully combined training with direct support for the mobilization so that not only did we succeed in our media goals, but our whole media team came out of the mobilization better equipped with fundamental social change skills.” \r\n--Rebecca Tarbotton, Prog. Dir., The Int\'l Society for Ecology and Culture','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Partner:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.reclaimthecommons.net/\">Reclaim the Commons</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</b> Reclaim the Commons<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Training, Messaging, Media Strategy Support, Mobilization Media Support <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme supported a cross section of activists in building a media team at the June 2004 mobilization against Bio 2004 (the world\'s largest biotechnology and pharmaceutical conference). We provided messaging support, training in mobilization media strategy as well as on-site skills support throughout the actions.<br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,6,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'RTC1.jpg','Bay area residents announce their intention to shut down the BIO conference at a press conference at the Moscone Center. Photo- Jeff Paterson',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(143,'Rural Vermont','“In 2004, Rural Vermont took on Big Agribusiness in a classic David and Goliath struggle. <I>Smart</I>Meme was our slingshot, providing us with an integrated package of services, from action design to advertising to on-the-ground media work, they helped us hit the giant right between the eyes. Reporters are still talking about our great campaign. <I>Smart</I>Meme Rocks!” --Amy Shollenberger, Policy Director, Rural Vermont','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ruralvermont.org/\">Rural Vermont</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Project:</b> One Contaminated Farm is One too Many!<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Message Development, Campaign Strategy Consulting, Action Design, Facilitation, Strategic Planning Consultation, Media Work, Print Advertisements<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme provided strategic consulting, direct media support, and designed two full page ads for Rural Vermont, a statewide farmer advocacy group working for a “Time Out” on Genetically Modified Organisms (GMOs). <i>Smart</i>Meme also provided facilitation and strategic planning support to help Rural Vermont grow its campaigning capacity. The state of Vermont is the first in the nation to pass a labeling law on GMOs.<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,6,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'RVTstacked.jpg','1.) This full page ad ran in the capitol city news paper as farmers and supporters geared up to march on the statehouse. 2.) The march, led by farmers, flooded the hearing where Monsanto lobbyists were testifying to VT lawmakers—resulting in historic news coverage. <BR> 3.) This ad, run later in the ’04 session, brought together the host of issues facing VT’s family farmers in the frame of “corporate control.”',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(144,'Safe Cosmetics Coalition','“<i>Smart</i>Meme is just that: smart, savvy and visionary.  Their expert facilitation brought a new level of synergy and cohesiveness to our campaign planning meeting. Their brilliant ad design conveyed our message perfectly--with results that far exceeded our expectations.\" --Lisa Archer, Friends of the Earth - U.S.','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org/\">Safe Cosmetics Coalition</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</b> The Campaign for Safe Cosmetics<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Campaign Strategy Consultation, Coalition Facilitation, Ad Concepting, Design and Placement<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme designed a full-page advertisement for the Safe Cosmetics Coalition that ran in USA Today, and helped persuade three target companies to commit to removing hazardous chemicals from their line of products. <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSmart</i>Meme facilitated a coalition strategy session and designed a comprehensive communications plan for this impressive coalition of women’s, healthcare, and environmental justice organizations. <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n“<i>Smart</i>Meme has excellent facilitators, experienced campaigners and talented designers -- a great package. <i>Smart</i>Meme designed a powerful ad campaign for us that was a perfect hit and resulted in three top cosmetics companies taking toxic phthalates out of their products. “ -- Stacy Malkan, Campaign for Safe Cosmetics <br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,7,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'SafeCosm.jpg','This full-page ad ran in USA Today during a key corporate cosmetics gathering in New York, resulting in the right kind of buzz to ensure swift action by the targets (L’Oreal, Revlon and Unilever) to negotiate with the campaigners. The result was an immediate victory for women\'s health.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(145,'The SPIN Project','\"<i>Smart</i>Meme connected with activists and advocates from around the country to research their on-the-ground needs, and then created a useful, practical tool to help support the grassroots, real time work. <i>Smart</i>Meme\'s knowledge of both strategic communications and organizing makes them a unique and useful resource.\" --Holly Minch, Executive Director, the SPIN Project','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Partner:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.spinproject.org/\">The SPIN Project</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</b> Prime Time for Change: Grassroots Communications Strategies at DNC/RNC 2004<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Project Design, Research, Outreach, Quantitative and Qualitative Analysis, Writing and Editing, Layout and Design <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme partnered with the SPIN project to create a 26 page report that surveyed organizations planning media events at the Democratic and Republican National Conventions and offered analysis and strategic recommendations. <i>Smart</i>Meme trainers have also worked at the SPIN academy, offering support and skills training for interfacing with the media. <br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,7,0,'PRIMETIME4CHANGE!.pdf','pdf',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'PRIMETIME4.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme conducted a survey of organizations mobilizing for the 2004 DNC and RNC and collected nearly 100 responses. The results are explored and analysed in this 26- page report that was published online in July 2004.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(146,'Turn Your Back on Bush',' “Bringing vision, experience, savvy and passion to the work, <I>smart</i>Meme knows how to integrate mass action planning scenarios, media strategy, messaging, and grassroots organizing; they are architects who developed a blue print together with us to design the action from inside out--and provided hands-on support to build it, giving 110% on through the day of action.\" --Jet Heiko, co-founder and Org. Dir., Turn Your Back on Bush','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.turnyourbackonbush.org\">Turn Your Back on Bush</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Project:</strong> On January 20th, You-Turn for Change <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Strategic Consultation, Facilitation, Action Design, Messaging, Organizing<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTurn Your Back on Bush brought together people from all walks of life from over 40 states for a dramatic public demonstration of dissent at the January 2005 inauguration. TYBOB brought <i>Smart</i>Meme on board to facilitate a strategy sessions, hammer out action design and logistics, and assist with messaging strategy and on the ground coordination and support. Over 5,000 people, from Military Families to students to Iraq Vets Against the War, engaged in direct nonviolent action to kick off four more years of resistance to the Bush agenda. <br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,7,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'TYBOB.jpg','Top photo: <i>Smart</i>Meme worked on the ground to design the action, integrating strategy, messaging, and organizing work. <br><br>Bottom photo: 5,000 people, including these Iraq Vets Against the War, participated in the action on January 20th 2005.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(147,'United for Peace & Justice','“Working with <i>smart</i>Meme was an enormous help in our mobilization against the G8 Summit in Brunswick, GA.  Not only did they help us frame our message and provide us some great talking points, but their media support work throughout was invaluable!”--Lisa Fithian, Root Activist Network of Trainers; National Co-chair, UFPJ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.unitedforpeace.org/\">United for Peace &amp; Justice</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Project:</strong> State of Emergency: End the War on Iraq! <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Facilitation, Messaging Document Development, Media Plan Consultation, Remote Media Work<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDuring the 2004 Sea Island G8 Summit, Georgia’s Governor declared a “state of emergency,” seriously infringing on free speech activities. The G8 Justice Media Team worked to defend civil liberties with an offense in the media, and used the media’s lens spread the word about the demonstrations, which called for an end to the Iraq war and unjust economic globalization. United for Peace &amp; Justice worked to assemble the G8 Justice Media team to amplify the voices for change at the G8 Summit; <i>smart</i>Meme assisted with team conference call facilitation; the development of a messaging document; and remote support.<br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,8,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'UFPJ1.jpg','A press conference held by activists protesting the G8 in Savannah.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(148,'Center for Economic Justice','\"As a campaigner at the World Bank Bonds Boycott in 2004, I worked with <i>smart</i>Meme to raise the profile of the struggle for global justice with creative communications strategies. We sold the World Bank on eBay during the Fall meetings, which ruffled a few feathers at the Bank and resulted in international news coverage for our campaign!\" --Basav Sen, former World Bank Bonds Boycott campaigner','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><strong>Client:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://econjustice.net/wbbb/\">Center for Economic Justice</a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</b> Challenging Global Apartheid<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Services Provided:</b> Media Plan Development, Messaging Consultation, Media List Building, Media Work, Action Design <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme provided media support and strategy consultation to economic justice advocates from the World Bank Bonds Boycott. <i>Smart</i>Meme attracted national attention to the global campaign by orchestrating a widely reported media stunt in which the World Bank was “sold” on eBay.<br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',15,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,1,0,'','img',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'World-Bank-eBay.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme designed this action to raise the profile of the World Bank Bonds Boycott at the 2004 Fall Meetings of the IMF & World Bank, and earned media coverage in The Financial Times, CNNmoney, Reuters, and the Times Of India.',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(150,'training & strategy colleagues','Here are links to some of our esteemed colleagues who deliver social-change training and strategy consultation to grassroots struggles for justice.','','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',56,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(149,'movement support organizations','These are some of the movement support service providers that we work with to serve the needs of allied campaigns and organizations. ','','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',55,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(153,'Scout Seven Online Strategies\r\n','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.scoutseven.org\">ScoutSeven</a> harnesses the convergence of online technology, grassroots organizing, media advocacy and social justice.','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',55,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,7,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(154,'The Ruckus Society','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ruckus.org/\">The Ruckus Society</a> provides environmental, human rights, and social justice organizers with the tools, training, and support needed to achieve their goals. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWorking with a broad range of communities, organizations, and movements - from high school students to professional organizations - Ruckus facilitates the sharing of information and expertise that strengthens the capacity to change our relationship with the environment and each other. (Ruckus has helped <i>smart</i>Meme grow in countless ways!) <br />\r\n<br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',56,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,1,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'Ruckus.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(155,'Training for Change','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.trainingforchange.org/\">Training for Change</a> was founded on Martin Luther King\'s birthday in 1992, a carefully chosen birthday for a group that spreads the skills of democratic, nonviolent social change. <br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\nSince then they\'ve led hundreds of workshops for nonviolent activists around the world with their unique direct education approach.<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\nThey\'ve included crowd control workshops for Mohawks, strategic planning retreats for Greenpeace, civil disobedience workshops for nursing-home workers, strike trainings for steelworkers and civil disobedience classes for ACT-UP.<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',56,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,4,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'TFC.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(156,'The Truth Force Training Center  ','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.truthforcenyc.org\">Truth Force</a> offers training in the philosophy and methods of nonviolent action, or &quot;truth force&quot;. They are creating a space to share skills and strategies for visionary resistance. Through their work, they seek to contribute to the power of racial, economic, and social justice movements. Their approach celebrates the human spirit in struggle, and they ground their trainings in the traditions of community organizing and popular education.<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',56,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,5,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'TruthForce.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(157,'Globalize Liberation!','','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\nThis book was designed as a tool kit for creative resistance. Chapters focus on what the problems are, and how to change things. Companion trainings and study guides are available on the website.<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\nwww.globalizeliberation.org <BR>\r\n\r\n</p>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',18,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(159,'The League of Pissed Off Voters','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\">\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.indyvoter.org\">The League of Pissed Off Voters</a> is doing national voter-organizing out of New York City. Our mission is to engage pissed off 17-35 year olds in the democratic process to build a progressive governing majority in our lifetime.<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n <br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',57,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,4,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'LeagueLogo.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(160,'Direct Action to Stop the War','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.actagainstwar.org\">Direct Action to Stop the War</a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\"> (DASW) has an explict goal to “end the war for empire and uproot the system behind it.” <i>Smart</i>Meme worked at the core of DASW’s massive nonviolent direct action at the start of the ‘03 US invasion of Iraq, and still works with grassroots, direct action, anti war affinity groups and folks in the Bay Area to end empire. <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',57,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,1,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'DASW.jpg','Direct Action can stop war! DASW marching to the Oakland Docks.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(162,'United For Peace and Justice','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.unitedforpeace.org\">United for Peace and Justice</a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">\r\n is a coalition of more than 800 local and national groups throughout the United States who have joined together to oppose our government\'s policy of permanent warfare and empire-building. \r\n\r\nSince their founding in October 2002, UFPJ has spurred hundreds of protests and rallies around the country, and organized the two of the largest demonstrations against the Iraq war. \r\n(<i>smart</i>Meme became a member of UFPJ in January 2005.) <br />\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',57,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,6,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'RNC4.jpg','The massive march to say “NO to the Bush Agenda” at the Republican National Convention, August 29th 2004.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(163,'Global Justice Ecology Project','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\">\r\nEconomic globalization, war, environmental devastation and human rights abuses are inextricably linked. Social movements can magnify their effectiveness by linking together to create a powerful movement for change that addresses the common economic, social and political roots of our issues. <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.globaljusticeecology.org\">Global Justice Ecology Project</a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\"> was founded to advance these alliances. <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[<i>smart</i>Meme encourages you to check out the GJEP photo gallery!]\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',57,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,3,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'GJEP.jpg','Part of the indigenous contingent on the September 10, 2003 march toward the WTO Convention Center in Cancún, Mexico. In a communiqué to the WTO protesters, Zapatista Subcomandante Marcos wrote, “The globalization of those who are above us is nothing more than a global machine that feeds on blood and defecates in dollars.” photo: Orin Langelle',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(164,'CODE PINK: Women For Peace ','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://codepinkalert.org\">CODE PINK</a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\"> is a women initiated grassroots peace and social justice movement that seeks positive social change through proactive, creative protest and non-violent direct action. \r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n“We call on women around the world to rise up and oppose the war in Iraq. We call on mothers, grandmothers, sisters and daughters, on workers, students, teachers, healers, artists, writers, singers, poets, and every ordinary outraged woman willing to be outrageous for peace.  Women have been the guardians of life-not because we are better or purer or more innately nurturing than men, but because the men have busied themselves making war. Because of our responsibility to the next generation, because of our own love for our families and communities and this country that we are a part of, we understand the love of a mother in Iraq for her children, and the driving desire of that child for life.”\r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',57,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'CodePink.jpg','Code Pink takes Manhattan.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(165,'Western Shonone Defense Project','','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2>\r\nMission: To affirm Newe (Western Shoshone) jurisdiction over Newe Sogobia  (Western Shoshone homelands) by protecting, preserving, and restoring Newe rights and lands for present and future generations based on cultural and spiritual traditions.\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\nhttp://www.wsdp.org/\r\n<BR>\r\n</p>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',53,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(166,'Earth First!','','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2>\r\nTo begin with, we do not believe that it is enough to preserve some of our remaining wilderness. We need to preserve it all…<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\nhttp://earthfirstjournal.org/efj/index.html\r\n<BR>\r\n</p>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',53,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(167,'Military Families Speak Out!','','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2>\r\nMilitary Families Speak Out (MFSO) is an organization of people who are opposed to war in Iraq and who have relatives or loved ones in the military. They were formed in November of 2002 and have contacts with military families throughout the United States, and in other countries around the world. Thei