ot; Under certain circumstances, opting out may prevent your participation in activities for which personal information is needed, such as the participation in the memelab or subscription to <i>smart</i>Meme\'s strategy/culture email newsletter.</i><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Does smartMeme.com rent, sell or trade my information?</b><br />\r\n<i>We never give out the names, e-mail addresses, postal addresses or telephone numbers of site users.</i><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>What do I do if I have questions that aren\'t answered here?</b><br />\r\n<i>If you have any questions about this privacy statement, the practices of this site or your dealings with this website, please contact us.</i><br />\r\n</body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',62,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(178,'updates','Wonder what <i>smart</i>Meme\'s been up too? The latest stories we\'ve changed, and who we\'ve changed them with? Check out the newest memes from <i>smart</i>Meme!','If you would like to stay in the loop about what we\'re up too, catch up on the latest communications trends and theory, and don\'t mind one extra email a month, then join <i>smart</i>Meme\'s <A HREF=\"/email3.php\">strategy / culture list</A>.  ','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',26,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(188,'trainings','<i>Smart</i>Meme conducts interactive multi-media skills trainings, focusing on in-depth analysis of media, the power of story, and memes in the context of grassroots social change work. In this section you will find announcements for our upcoming trainings.','<i>Smart</i>Meme’s unique training curriculum combines traditional movement building skills with new strategies for re-framing issues, challenging assumptions, and infusing new ideas into popular culture.\r\n\r\nAll of <i>smart</i>Meme’s workshops and trainings can be tailored to your group or campaign and offered in the form of intensive, individualized coaching and consulting. <i>Smart</i>Meme can come to your campus or community and offer a package of workshops, lectures, trainings, and issue briefings, customized to meet your local needs. In addition to our <i>smart</i>Meme designed curriculum we provide a wide range of social change oriented skills trainings including grassroots organizing, media and PR skills, strategic campaigning, non-violent direct action, facilitation and group decision making. \r\n\r\nFor more information visit the <A HREF=\"article.php?list=type&type=50\">training</A> section of <A HREF=\"article.php?list=type&type=4\">what we do</A>.','','2006-09-20 19:54:35',63,0,0,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(189,'speaking presentations',NULL,'',NULL,'2006-07-19 21:23:23',64,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(192,'Internships Available for 2006!','The <i>smart</i>Meme Strategy & Training Project, a national organization dedicated to radical, grassroots social change work, is looking for interns....like you! We are accepting applications for Spring, Summer and Fall of 2006. Deadlines are March 1, May 1, and September 1.','<i>Smart</i>Meme is a collective founded in 2002 dedicated to amplifying the voices of peace, justice, democracy, and ecological sanity. <i>Smart</i>Meme supports movements with strategic social change communications, working with grassroots groups and campaigning organizations from coast to coast.\r\n\r\nInternships are now available to enable activists to plug into <i>smart</i>Meme\'s new youth-focused training initiative: <A HREF=\"article.php?list=type&type=50\">STORY (Strategy, Training, and Organizing Resources for Youth)</A>.\r\n\r\nThis internship is a unique opportunity that is designed to help develop the skills of participants as grassroots organizers, trainers, communicators, and effective change agents.\r\n\r\n<b>You are a great candidate if you:</b>\r\n\r\n--Have a passion for social change work\r\n--Hold a strong commitment to strategic anti-war, social justice, and ecological activism\r\n--Have some experience working with a youth/student activist organization\r\n--Are looking to build your skills, networks, and experiences as a social change practitioner...\r\n\r\n<b>Responsibilities of interns may include:</b>\r\n\r\n--Research (opposition research, media climate assessment, etc)\r\n--Media Work (media list building, collaboration on media releases and statements)\r\n--Outreach & Promotion (tabling, mailings, etc)\r\n--Organizing and Logistics (for smartMeme trainings and other STORY events)\r\n--Development Work (the hands on work of building this exciting new organization!)\r\n\r\nAll Spring internships require working at <i>smart</i>Meme\'s office in beautiful BURLINGTON, VERMONT for a minimum of 14 hours per week for a period of three months. <br><br>\r\n\r\nSummer internships are in the works for  SAN FRANCISCO, CA and SKOKOMISH NATION, WA. <br>\r\n\r\nInterns work with an experienced staff member who designs and oversees the completion of a special project. Interns participate in the day-to-day operations of the STORY program as well. Some travel may be required to STORY related trainings and events.\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme  will cover commuting and travel expenses into the field required by the position (interns may travel to trainings and events throughout the summer). \r\n\r\nA small housing stipend is available to the right candidate who can put in 20+ hours/week. \r\n\r\nAt the completion of the internship, each intern is given a chance to evaluate their internship, a letter of reference, and the waiver of fees to <i>smart</i>Meme\'s autumn STORY gathering...and some cool <i>smart</i>Meme gear!\r\n\r\n<b>IF YOU ARE INTERESTED, PLEASE SEND A RESUME AND COVER LETTER OF INTEREST (YOUR STORY!) TO:</b>\r\n\r\n<b><i>STORY@SMARTMEME.COM</i></b>\r\n\r\nOR\r\n\r\n<b><i>smart</i>Meme\r\n19 Church St, Suite 10\r\nBurlington, Vermont 05401</b>\r\n\r\nNo Phone Calls Please.\r\n\r\nThe <i>smart</i>Meme collective is committed to challenging historic patterns of oppression and political marginalization.  Young activists from working class backgrounds, LBGTQ people, womyn, and youth of color are particularly encouraged to apply. \r\n\r\n<i>** A housing stipend is available to the right candidate who can put in 20+ hours/week. Please tell us in your cover letter how much money per month you would require as a stipend in order to do this internship. **</i>','','2006-09-20 19:57:37',65,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-04-05',1,0,0,0,'','',0,'',0,1,'','','','',0,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(194,'scarecrows vs. monsanto','<i>Smart</i>Meme collaborated with Rural Vermont last week on an ad telling Vermont lawmakers to protect family farmers from predatory lawsuits by big biotech corporations. ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\"><strong>Scarecrows vs. Monsanto<br /></strong><br /><i>Smart</i>Meme collaborated with Rural Vermont last week on an ad telling Vermont lawmakers to protect family farmers from predatory lawsuits by big biotech corporations. <br /><br />Check it out at <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ruralvermont.org/archives/001126.html\">Rural Vermont</a>. <br /><br />This image came to life as family farm activists put scarecrows on the roadsides and on the lawn of the Vermont Statehouse to greet lawmakers on their way to work. As Monsanto lobbyists descended on the statehouse, scarecrows peered in the windows, producing chuckles and support from the committee rooms inside. <br /><br />The most prominent scarecrow &quot;Elmer&quot;, who is featured in the ad, also made an appearance in the newspapers last week, as the centerpiece of a march on the statehouse organized by Rural Vermont.<br /><br /><i>Smart</i>Meme continues to be inspired by working with our friends at Rural Vermont to defend family farmers. We were honored to attend the April 17th International Day of Farmer\'s Struggle and celebrate Rural Vermont\'s 20th anniversary. Congratulations to Rural Vermont! </font></p></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',26,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'RVTScarecrow.jpg','The full page ad as it appeared in the Vermont Paper, Times Argus. SmartMeme\'s past work with Rural Vermont can be found in the <A HREF=\"article.php?id=143\">Partners/Clients</A> section of our site.',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(195,'bellingham, WA - bellingham grassroots & independent media conference','Bellingham Grassroots & Independent Media Conference<BR>May 21, 2005<BR>Garden St. Family Center<BR> 1231 N. Garden St.<BR>Bellingham, WA','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><BR><i>Smart</i>Meme will be giving a STORY workshop on \"Winning the Battle of the Story\". \r\n\r\nBellingham Grassroots & Independent Media Conference\r\nGarden St. Family Center \r\n1231 N. Garden St.\r\nBellingham, WA\r\nMay 21, 2005\r\n\r\nFor more details visit: http://www.whatcompjc.org/mediaconf/index.html','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',63,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,1,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'BellinghamGIMC.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(196,'STORY - Spring 2005','<i>Smart</i>Meme\'s STORY program is building  collaborative partnerships with some amazing youth-led organizations.','Check out some of the youth led organizations that <i>smart</i>Meme\'s STORY program has been working with this spring:\r\n\r\nStudent Farmworker Alliance http://www.sfalliance.org in Immokalee Florida.\r\nSTORY is assisting the SFA in their efforts to make fast food fair food.\r\n\r\nDemocracy Unlimited of Humboldt County http://www.duhc.org \r\nSTORY is working to support their grassroots education efforts to amplify awareness of the need to reassert local democracy over corporate power in Northern California.  \r\n\r\nHouston Global Awareness http://www.houstonglobalawareness.org\r\nSTORY is supporting their campaign against the shameless war profiteers at Halliburton, and their nonviolent direct action at the May 18th Halliburton shareholders meeting.\r\n\r\nNational Youth and Student Peace Coalition http://www.nyspc.net\r\nSTORY is collaborating to develop their strategy session to build the youth anti-war movement.\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme will also be giving STORY workshops about \"Winning the Battle of the Story\" at the Bellingham Grassroots & Independent Media Conference, and giving a \"Power of Story\" workshop on May Day in Chicago','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',26,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,3,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'STORYbar.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(197,'AUG. 1-7: Immokalee, FL - Student/Farmworker Alliance: Summer Encuentro 2005','<i>Smart</i>Meme invites you to join us and students and youth\r\nfrom around the country for a week of skill shares, reflection,\r\ncommunity-building, trainings, and a two-day national strategy session\r\nto plan for the next phase of youth activism after the historic and\r\nprecedent-setting victory of the Taco Bell boycott!','\r\n<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Times New Roman\" color=\"#000000\">The Encuentro will take place in Immokalee, FL, from August 1-7.\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme has partnered with the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sfalliance.org\">Student/Farmworker Alliance</a> (SFA) as\r\npart of our <a href=\"http://smartmeme.radicaldesigns.org/article.php?list=type&type=50\">STORY</a> program (Strategy, Training and Organizing Resources\r\nfor Youth) to help out with this awesome event.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\nTrainers include: the Beehive Collective, the Ruckus Society, Art and\r\nRevolution, the Coalition of Immokalee Workers, the Root Cause\r\nCoalition (Miami Workers Center, LIFFT, and Power U), <i>smart</i>Meme\r\nStrategy and Training Project, United Students Against Sweatshops,\r\nStudent-Labor Action Project, Young Workers United, School of the\r\nAmericas Watch, National Youth and Student Peace Coalition, and more.\r\n<br />\r\n<br /><i>Smart</i>Meme will be offering our \'Battle of the Story\' and other strategy\r\nworkshops to help the SFA network campaign to transform the fast\r\nfood industry and further the struggle for global justice.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n**** Extremely Important***** <br />\r\nEveryone (even trainers and folks very close to the SFA or <i>smart</i>Meme) who is considering heading down for the Encuentro, needs to register ASAP. It will help to make housing, food and scholarships available to those who need it.\r\n<br />\r\n \r\n<br />For those who would like to help or support the Student/Farmworker Alliance but cannot attend the Encuentro, there are other ways assist. Funds for housing, transportation, and food as well as for travel and registration scholarships are needed. The Encuentro website <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sfalliance.org/encuentro\"> http://sfalliance.org/encuentro</a> now\r\nfeatures a PayPal button where you can make a secure and quick donation\r\nto the SFA.  All donations to the SFA are tax-deductible.\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou can also send checks or money orders made out to:\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\nStudent/Farmworker Alliance<br />\r\nPO Box 603 <br />Immokalee, FL 34143\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />Whether or not you are personally able to donate, there are still other\r\nways to help:<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\nYou can email and spread this message far and wide;  We have also made a\r\nfundraising letter available that you can download <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sfalliance.org/resources/fundletterhead.doc\"> (http://sfalliance.org/resources/fundletterhead.doc)</a> and use to\r\napproach local professors, organizations, and others for donations.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<br />\r\nDonating to the SFA at this time will help not only to make the\r\nEncuentro an amazing, unforgettable and worthwhile experience, but will\r\nalso help SFA continue to be one of the most vibrant, strategic, and effective organizations around that keeps on campaigning for years to come!\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n</font></p>\r\n</body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',63,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'CIW1.jpg','',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(198,'announcements',NULL,'',NULL,'2006-07-19 21:23:23',66,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(199,'INCITE/INSIGHT:\r\nStory Telling, Movement Building, and Creating a Culture of Strategy...\r\n','September 29-October 3,  2005\r\nAndover, New Hampshire','\r\n<html><head></head><body>The first gathering convened by smartMeme\'s new STORY program  (Strategy, Training, and Organizing Resources for Youth) focused on power analysis, story telling and movement building.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn a rural retreat setting, we will take 3 1/2 days to explore narrative power analysis, story-based strategies, creative direct action at the point(s) of assumption and more!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIncite/Insight will be a unique and intimate gathering of young activists (18 - 30 years old) working for systemic social change.  The conference will offer a reflective forum for deep discussions on the system, our strategies, movement building, and how the stories we tell can reshape our world.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSessions will focus on the power of story, the landscape of media, leadership and organization, and points of intervention to change the story for a more hopeful future.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMORE INFORMATION COMING SOON at www.smartMeme.com<br />\r\n<br />\r\n** SAVE THE DATE ** SAVE THE DATE**<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSeptember 29-October 3,  2005<br />\r\n</body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',63,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'The first gathering convened by smartMeme\'s new STORY program  (Strategy,\r\nTraining, and Organizing Resources for Youth) focused on power analysis,\r\nstory telling and movement building.\r\n','2005-07-15',1,0,0,0,'retreatlake.jpg','The STORY Retreat, Incite/Insight, will take place at the Owl\'s Nest Lodge in Andover, New Hampshire September 29-Oct 3 2005',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(200,'United Students Against Sweatshops!','August 12-15, Chicago\r\nIncludes STORY Training on Message and Media...','Build your skills around organizing, fundraising, direct action and more.\r\n\r\nStrategize about victories in the coming year for creating SweatFree campuses, holding Coke accountable for their violation of human rights, and standing in solidarity with campus workers through living wage and support for worker organizing.\r\n\r\nHear USAS 2005 International Interns report on working conditions and workers\' lives in India, Haiti, Mexico, Turkey, Cambodia, Hong Kong, China, Kenya, South Africa, El Salvador, Phillippines and Korea.\r\n\r\nLearn about the national campaign against WalMart and how you can help!\r\n\r\nHousing and food are included in registration. \r\n\r\nTravel scholarships are available for those who register early. \r\n\r\nMore info at http://www.studentsagainstsweatshops.org','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',63,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','2005-07-15',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(212,'test form test',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-10-13 00:54:24',69,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'modinput4.php?modin=51',1,'','0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(205,'strategic resources','<i>Smart</i>Meme designs unique strategy and training resources to help you effectively integrate messaging, strategic planning, and organizing so your story has impact.','\r\n<html><head></head><body>Here you can find specific, useful tools to harness the power of story telling for grassroots social change work. The worksheets lay out exercises to help you design “story based strategies” by applying the elements of effective story telling to campaign narratives. The essays reflect different case studies exploring “story based strategies” to infuse new ideas into the culture and win the “Battle of the Story.”','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',6,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(206,'worksheets','Here you can find worksheets that lay out exercises to help you design “story based strategies” by applying the elements of effective story telling to campaign narratives.','\r\n<html><head></head><body>Click on links below to download pdf documents<font size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font><br /><br /><strong><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/BattleoftheStoryExplain.pdf\" title=\"Battle of the Story\">Battle of the Story or Story of the Battle?</a></strong><br />This<strong>&nbsp;</strong>worksheet provides some definitions and thoughts about the two distinct types of social change narrative. <br /><br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/BOSworksheet.pdf\" title=\"Battle of the Story WS\"><strong>Battle of the Story Worksheet</strong></a><br />This sheet presents an exercise to apply the elements of story telling to existing campaigns by comparing the power-holder’s and the change agent’s stories.  <s>&nbsp;</s><br /><strong><br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/INFLUENCE%20MAP.pdf\" title=\"Influence Map\">Influence Map</a></strong>\r\nThe Influence Map works to get you thinking about “avenues of influence” for getting your message heard by key decision-makers through assessing the most important decision-makers and mapping out their relationships with other political players you may be able to influence. \r\n<br /><strong><br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/InterventionsWorksheet.pdf\" title=\"Interventions Worksheet\">Points of Intervention Worksheet</a></strong> \r\nThis worksheet helps activists to identify places in systems where action can be taken to effectively interrupt the system and create change.</body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',16,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,1,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-26',1,0,0,0,'Training.jpg','Strategy workshop with Houston Global Awareness, May 2005',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(207,'essays','These essays reflect different case studies exploring story based strategies to infuse new ideas into the culture and win the Battle of the Story.','\r\n<div>\r\n<div><p><font size=\"2\">Click on links below to download pdf documents</font></p><p><font size=\"2\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/StoryBasedStrategies4DirectAction.pdf\">New! Story-Based Strategy for Mass Nonviolent Direct Action</a></strong><br />This article by Doyle Canning and Patrick Reinsborough applies smartMeme\'s<br />Story-Based Strategy framework to organizing creative mass actions. By<br />exploring concepts like meta-verbs and action logic this article can help<br />to bring effective narrative strategy to direct action planning.<br /><br /><br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/Information%20Warfare%20in%20Miami.pdf\" title=\"Information Warfare\"><strong>Information Warfare in Miami</strong></a><strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />This essay is a case study done by Ilyse Hogue and Patrick Reinsborough of the November 2003 mobilization against the Free Trade Area of the Americas in Miami. The article, based on <em>smart</em>Memeï¿½s work supporting the mobilization,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>documents the use of military-style information warfare tactics against non-violent protest movements. </font></p></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"><br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/Battle%20of%20the%20Story-SPIN.pdf\" title=\"Winning the BOS\"><strong>Winning the</strong> <strong>Battle of the Story</strong></a> <br />Winning the Battle of the Story by Ilyse Hogue and Patrick Reinsborough explains how compelling stories and infectious memes can be used to amplify grassroots efforts to build a more democratic, just, and ecologically sane society.</font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"><br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/TYBOB_Znet.pdf\" title=\"Turn Your Back on Bush\"><strong>Turn Your Back on Bush</strong><br /></a>This essay by Doyle Canning explains how the<strong>&nbsp;</strong>campaign used memes to challenge assumptions about power and also describes how through direct action, activists can build solidarity through sharing their stories and strategies. </font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"><br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/De-colonizingImagination.pdf\" title=\"De-Colonizing\"><strong>De-Colonizing the Revolutionary Imagination</strong></a><strong> <br /></strong>This ten part essay by Patrick Reinsborough explores a wide range of innovative social change strategies and ideas including post-issue activism, direct action at the point of assumption and the politics of reality. </font></div></div>','','2006-11-28 15:55:35',67,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-26',1,0,0,0,'Speaker.jpg','The Battle for the Story: A news conference in front of Halliburton HQ on the eve of the 2005 share holders meeting. STORY worked with Houston Global Awareness to amplify their \"Blow the Whistle on Halliburton\" campaign. ',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(208,'glossary','The Pragmatic Dreamer\'s Glossary (a few cognitive stepping stones towards a lexicon for transformative action…..) explains some key terms to help activists build a common vocabulary around story-based strategies and meme campaigning. ','\r\n<html><head></head><body><div><font size=\"2\"><strong>ABCNNBCBS</strong> - the increasingly blurred brand names for the same narrow stream of U.S. corporate filtered mass media.  This is the delivery system for the advertising product that giant media corporations sell to the general public. This process used to occur primarily through overt advertising, increasingly however it has become a complex web of cross-marketing, branding and self-promotion among different tentacles of the same media empires.</font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font> </div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"><b>advertising</b> - the manipulation of collective desire for commercial interests.  Over the last 20 years as it has grown to be nearly a $200 billion industry it has become the propaganda shell and dream life of modern consumer culture.  (See <b>Control Mythology</b>)<b /></font></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>articulating values crisis</b> - a strategy in which radicals lay claim to common sense values and expose the fact that the system is out of alignment with those values<b /></font><b /></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>controlMeme </b>- a meme used to marginalize, co-opt or limit the scale of social change ideas by institutionalizing a status quo bias into popular perception of events.  The type of memes that RAND Corporation analysts and Pentagon information warfare experts spend countless hours and millions of dollars designing.</font></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>control mythology </b> - the web of stories, symbols and ideas which define the dominant culture\'s sense of normal (including limiting our imagination of social change) and make people think the system is unchangeable.</font></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>confirmatory bias</b> - psychological concept in which studies have shown people are more likely to accept/believe new information if it sounds like something they already believe.</font></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>defector syndrome </b>- the tendency of radicals to self-marginalize by exhibiting their dissent is such a way that it only speaks to those who already share their beliefs.<b /></font><b /></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>direct action at the point(s) of assumption </b>-<b>&nbsp;</b>actions whose goal is to re-frame issues and create infectious new political space by targeting underlying<b>&nbsp;</b>assumptions</font></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font> </b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>earth-centered </b>- a political perspective through which one defines themselves and their actions in the context of the planet\'s ecological operating systems, biological/cultural diversity and efforts to re-center human society within the Earth\'s natural limits/cycles.  An emerging term to draw links and build alliances between ecological identity politics, land based struggles, indigenous resistance, earth spirituality, agrarian folk wisdom and visions of sustainable, ecologically sane societies both past and future. (etc.)   A politicized acceptance of the sacredness of living systems.  </font></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>global crisis </b>- the present time in the history of planet earth characterized by the systematic undermining of the planet\'s life support systems through industrial extraction, unlimited growth, the commodification of all life and emergence of global corporate rule.  Symptoms include : accelerating loss of biological and cultural diversity, the deterioration of all ecosystems, the de-stabilization of global ecology (climate change, soil erosion, bio-contamination etc.) growing disparities between rich and poor, increased militarization, ongoing patterns of racism, classism and sexism and the spread of consumer monoculture.  Part of the endgame of 200 years of industrial capitalism, 500 years of white supremacist colonization and 10,000 years of patriarchal domination.<b /></font><b /></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>image event </b>- an experience, event or action which operates as a delivery system for smartMemes by creating new associations and meanings  <b /></font><b /></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>meme </b>- (pronounced meem) a unit of  self-replicating cultural transmission (ex. ideas, slogans, melodies, symbols) which spreads virally from brain to brain.  Word coined by evolutionary biologist Richard Dawkins in 1976 from a Greek root meaning &quot;to imitate&quot; to draw the analogy with &quot;gene&quot;.  &quot;A contagious information pattern&quot; - Glenn Grant. A meme often operates as a container, anchor or carrier for a larger more complex story.  <b>&nbsp;</b></font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>movement </b>- a critical mass of people who share ideas, take collective action and build alternative institutions to create social change. </font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>points of intervention </b> - a place in a system, be it a  physical system or a conceptual system (ideology, cultural assumption etc.) where action can be taken to effectively interrupt the system.  Examples include <b>point of production</b> (factory) <b>point of destruction</b>, (logging road) <b>point of consumption</b>, (chain store) <b>point of decision</b>,(corporate HQ) <b>point of assumption</b> (culture/mythology) and <b>point of potential</b> (actions which makes alternatives real). <b>&nbsp;</b></font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>political space</b> - the ability of an oppositional idea or critique of the dominant order to manifest itself and open up new revolutionary possibilities. </font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>psychic break </b>the process or moment where people realize the system is out of alignment with their values.</font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>psycho-geography</b> - the intersection of physical landscape with cultural and symbolic landscapes.   A framework for finding targets for direct action at the point of assumption. </font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font></b> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>smartMeme </b> - a designer meme which injects new infectious ideas into popular culture, contests established meaning (controlMemes) and facilitates popular re-thinking of assumptions. These are memes that act as containers for collaborative power, reveal creative possibilities for change and help grassroots social movements contest idea space.</font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>subverter </b>-<b>&nbsp;</b>an effective radical who works within the logic of the dominant culture to foster dissent, mobilize resistance and make fundamental social change imaginable</font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>Values crisis </b>- the disconnect between common sense values (justice, equality, democracy, ecological literacy) and the pathological values which underlie the global corporate system</font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>Values shift </b>-<b>&nbsp;</b>a recognition that the global crisis is the expression of pathological values</font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\">which we will need to change.   An area of extreme difficulty to organize since people\'s values are very ingrained and the values arena is often appropriated by powerful reactionary traditions and institutions. (government, organized religion, patriarchal family etc.)</font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"></font> </b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div>\r\n<div><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><b><font size=\"2\"><b>Xerxes</b>  - ancient Persian emperor who despite having the world\'s largest military force over extended himself and was defeated by the unity and creativity of the Greeks starting a long decline that led to the end of Persian dominance. A conceptual archetype for the fall of all empires.  America take note.</font></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></b></div></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',68,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,3,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-26',1,0,0,0,'abc.jpg','Do you notice anything about these letters?  Who\'s stories are in your brain? (Adapted from \"American Alphabet\" by Heidi Cody: http://www.heidicody.com and http://www.illegal-art.org)',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(211,'smartMeme Spring 2007','* New podcast and release of 2020 social change scenarios!\r\n* Youth Media Council Action Camp May 17-19\r\n*Join smartMeme at the US Social Forum\r\n\r\n\r\n','\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>New Strategy Resources from <em>smart</em>Meme! Building the Movement towards 2020...</strong><br /></font></p><p><strong><a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/downloads/Crisis%20&amp;%20Opportunity_%20Social%20Change%20Scenario%20Planning%20for%202020.mp3\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Listen in</font></a></strong><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"> on an invitational conference call held in March to release the outcomes of our collaboration with the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.sehn.org\">Science &amp; Environmental Health Network</a> on the development of story-based scenarios. </font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">These 2 documents and Pocast share what we imagine social change movements using the precautionary principle could look like in the year 2020. The outcomes of this 9 month project are offered here as part of the creative commons. Take these ideas and run with them, and let us know what you think:</font><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"> </font><br /></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/downloads/smartMeme.2020.Scenario.pdf\">Mapping 2020</a> outlines 10 possible scenarios for the precautionary principle</font> </p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><br /><a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/downloads/smartMeme.2020.Strategy.pdf\">The Future of Foresight&nbsp;</a> details the key trends, drivers, and oppurtunities coming down the pike</font><br /></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/downloads/Crisis%20&amp;%20Opportunity_%20Social%20Change%20Scenario%20Planning%20for%202020.mp3\">CLICK HERE</a> to download our podcast sharing the key findings about this exciting project.<br /></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><br />\r\n\r\n<strong>Upcoming STORY strategy trainings!</strong><br /></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><em>Smart</em>Meme\'s young adult leadership program STORY (strategy, training and organizing resources 4 youth) is gearing up for the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://youthmediacouncil.org/events/view/2\">Youth Media Council Action Camp</a> May 17-19 in Berkeley, CA!</font></p><p><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">We are also collaborating with the <a href=\"http://www.ruckus.org\">Ruckus Society</a> to bring story-based strategy training, along with nonviolent direct action workshops, to the <a href=\"http://www.ussf2007.org/\">US Social Forum</a> June 27-July 1 in Atlanta, GA. Stay Tuned!</font></font><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><br /><br />And, check out the fresh STORY website: <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org/\">changing the story dot org</a> <br /></font></p><p><strong><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">New Download! SmartMeme Elements...Memes &amp; smartMemes....</font></strong></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Check out our new <em>smartMeme Elements</em></strong> essays, which also serve as an invitation to join smartMeme as a member! Your <a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\">membership</a> can make a difference and help change the story in 2007...</font><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/smartmeme.memes.pdf\">Memes and Smart Memes: Shifting Culture With Contagious Thoughts</a><br />&nbsp;\r\n</font><br /></p>\r\n\r\n','','2007-05-10 01:55:19',9,1,1,'whatsnew',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'ivaw-wwrelease_1.jpg','<b><a href=\"http://www.ivaw.org\">Iraq Veterans Against the War</a> share their stories  at the release of their new collection, \"Warrior Writers,\" in Burlington, Vermont on April 21. Visit the STORY Iraq Collaborative online <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org/iraq\"> here! </a>',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','smartmeme bioneers ','smartmeme bioneers STORY \"doyle canning\" \"patrick reinsborough\" \"katie joaquin\" \"james bell\"',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(215,'goals of the STORY Collaborative','The Collaborative will work together to change the story and build the movement for peace!','<html><head></head><body>The goals of the STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq are:<br /><ul><li>	Build deep alliances between young Iraq Veterans and youth-based antiwar networks </li><li>Provide space for relational organizing across constituencies</li><li>Facilitate anti-war strategy development using story-based strategy </li><li>Amplify the voices of youth and young veterans in the anti-war movement and build leadership capacity amongst these constituencies.</li><li>Encourage the building of a long-term peace movement that can challenge the assumptions underlying racism, militarism and war.<br /><br /></li></ul><br /></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',71,1,1,'goals',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'peacesign.jpg','STORY is a space for young activists to share ideas, visions, and strategies in order to effectively tell a larger generational story of resistance and hope. Nonviolent protest to stop the Free Trade Area of the Americas in Miami, November 2003.',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(216,'sessions & workshops at Incite/Insight','Please check back for updates as sessions and workshops are confirmed. ','<html><head></head><body>The sessions and workshops provided at the Incite/Insight retreat will be collaborative and dynamic. They will include discussions on story-based strategies, anti-racist strategies, and power analysis.<br /><br /><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">More information coming soon!</span><br /><br /></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',72,1,1,'sessions & workshops',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'web-20050312a_ciw_0825.jpg','The Student/Farmworker Alliance worked alongside the Coalition of Immokalee Workers to win a landmark victory in the boycott against Taco Bell. This campaign offers an inspirational model of the kind of strategic work that is transforming the global economy. Photo:  Jacques-Jean Tiziou.',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(217,'facilities and accommodations','Join us in the autumn leaves on the foothills of Mount Kearsarge!','Incite/Insight will take place at The Owl’s Nest Lodge in Andover, New Hampshire. The site&nbsp;spans out&nbsp;over 200 acres of forest and fields in the foothills of Mount Kearsarge on Bradley Lake.<BR><BR>The main lodge is spacious and consists of a large central room for meeting as well as bunk rooms, baths, a dining room, and an outside deck.<BR><BR>Participants will be staying in the main lodge in the bunk-style rooms and will need to bring their own linins. Camping on the premises is also an option for those who like to rough it a bit more!<BR><BR>Food for the entire weekend will be provided and there will be vegetarian and vegan options.<BR><BR>The closest airports to Andover are Boston Logan and Manchester. For those coming by bus, the closest stops are Concord and New London.<BR>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',73,1,1,'facilities & accommodations',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'bunks_jpg_jpg.jpg','Owl\'s Nest Lodge.',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(218,'contact','Get in touch with STORY!','\r\nBy email: story (at) smartmeme.com<br /><br />802.860.1155 <br /><br />Write us at:<br />\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><em>smart</em>Meme<br />19 Church St. Suite 10<br />Burlington, VT 05401<br /></div>','','2006-10-11 20:55:36',76,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'http://www.changingthestory.org/contact',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'Speaker.jpg','Let\'s work together to end this war!',1,'',0,1,'','','right','graphic',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(241,'Apply!','','\r\n<html><head></head><body><br /></body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',2,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'modinput4.php?modin=52',1,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(225,'scholarships','Travel scholarships will be available.','\r\n<html><head></head><body>If you’re wondering how you’re going to financially be able to get to New Hampshire don’t fret! SmartMeme is dedicated to bringing a diverse pool of participants to the Incite/Insight retreat and to the extent we are able will be providing scholarships to subsidize travel expenses for those who need it.  Please apply for a travel scholarship by checking the appropriate box on the application if you need help with funding for your trip.</body></html>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',74,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'overhead_psd_jpg-1.jpg','Join us at Incite/Insight!',1,'',0,1,'','','right','Owls Nest',NULL,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(247,'Apply!',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-07-19 21:23:23',75,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,'modinput4.php?modin=52',1,'','0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(238,'Apply! section none, module template',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-10-13 00:54:24',1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'modinput4.php?modin=52',1,'','0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(248,'apply!','','\r\n \r\n                \r\n \r\n                \r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',75,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'modinput4.php?modin=52',1,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(249,'Thank you!',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-07-19 21:23:23',75,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'modinput.php?modin=52&thank=1',1,'','0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(250,'United Students For Fair Trade!','February 17-19 2006, Denver CO','smartMeme\'s STORY program is headed to the Rockies for the national convergence of the\r\n <a href=\"http://www.usft.org \">United Students for Fair Trade!</a> <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Story-based Strategies for a Fair Trade Future </b><br><br>\r\n\r\nHow can we tell our story of a fair trade future? How can we re-frame the debates around free-trade and globalization? How can we amplify the voices of communities struggling for fair wages and environmental justice? How can we change the story for a fair trade future?! <br><br>\r\n\r\nThe smartMeme Strategy and Training Project has developed a range of strategy tools for applying a narrative power analysis to social change work—That is, looking at the stories that are told, who tells them, and how we can change the story for a more just future. We explore the landscapes of media, the power of story in culture, and unearth the assumptions that are at the roots of dominant narratives.  We work with activists from coast to coast to design story-based strategies for reframing debates and messaging campaigns with creative grassroots action. <br><br>\r\n\r\nIn two sessions, the Battle of the Story training will explore the context of story based strategies for organizing work in the US in this period. We will discuss the relationship between meme theory -- the study of how memes (units of cultural transmission such as ideas, slogans, icons etc.) spread and replicate – and movement building for fair trade. We will work through the core strategy tool of the curriculum, The Battle of the Story framework, and share our learning and insights in creative and interactive ways.  Our multi-media, interactive, collaborative workshop will be interesting, provocative, and useful in your efforts to spread the story of fair trade!','','2006-09-20 19:54:35',63,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','2006-02-14 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(251,'Lancaster Coalition for Peace & Justice (PA)','STORY is working in partnership with the Lancaster Coalition to offer story-based strategy training March 23-24.','March 23-24 the smartMeme STORY team will be working in partnership with <a href=\"http://www.lancastervoice.org/\">The Lancaster Coalition for Peace & Justice</a> to offer a training and strategy workshop on the Battle of the Story for their work to build a movement to end the war and beyond in Lancaster, Penn. For more information contact: Matthew@lancastervoice.org','','2006-09-20 19:54:34',63,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','2006-02-14 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(252,'STORY Program',NULL,'',NULL,'2006-09-21 00:25:29',77,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(253,'meme lab',NULL,'',NULL,'2006-09-21 00:28:50',78,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
