, non-violent direct action, facilitation and group decision making. ','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><BR>\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme offers training in a number of key skill sets to help your group, network, or community gain experience and competence in grassroots organizing and campaigning. All of these trainings can be condensed into introductory 2-hour workshops, or be expanded to in-depth, multi-stage intensive trainings. We can custom design a training curriculum to meet the needs of your local community or specific campaign. For more info contact trainings@smartmeme.com.\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\nOur skills trainings include:\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n<b>Grassroots Organizing</b><BR>\r\n\r\nWe can work with your organization or community of emerging activists to give you the nuts and bolts skills of grassroots work.  Focusing on skills ranging from strengthening your group, recruiting members, developing leadership, setting goals, choosing avenues of action, making plans, hosting events, etc. \r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n<b>Don\'t Get Spun--SPIN BACK! Tools & Tactics for Talking to the Media</b><BR>\r\n\r\nFrustrated with the corporate media ignoring or mis-representing your efforts to make change? Ever been cornered on camera, clipped out, or mis-quoted? Never, ever talked to the corporate media---or duck and hide when the paparazzi shows up? Well, these workshops are for anyone who wants to practice being a more effective message-maker and spokesperson while gaining skills and confidence in wrangling the press. We can offer basic training for media-spokes people and practice how to give a good interview; the basics of different mediums, the “rules of engagement” and discuss how to move your “core messages”. \r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\nMore intensive trainings explore how to increase your chances of earning coverage for your event or campaign by developing multi-pronged, strategic media plans. We can look at what makes a good press event and how to organize and promote one. We can examine some sample press releases, press kits, and various tools and tactics for activists who want to engage with the mainstream media and win the Battle of the Story. \r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n<b>Video Activism</b><BR>\r\n \r\nOne of the core lessons emphasized by <i>Smart</i>Meme is that “If we don’t tell our own story, the story will be told about us.” We explore how to use video technology as a tool to tell our own stories, both to each other--in the form of documentation of events and actions we capture and share on tape—and to the world—in the form of “B-roll” for television networks. <i>Smart</i>Meme’s video team has extensive experience as broadcast media professionals who have made award-winning front-line documentary films and produced a range of independent and educational film projects.   They can share skills from street level video shooting to producing and successfully distributing a documentary for your campaign, action, or group.\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n<b>Non-violent Direct Action Skills and Action Design</b><BR>\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme trainers can offer civil disobedience and direct action preparation sessions for your action or mobilization, covering the basics of street safety and exploring action outcomes and scenarios for small groups to mass mobilizations. <i>Smart</i>Meme can also tailor trainings to include in-depth pieces on building strong affinity groups; integrated messaging and action logic; mass-action design and the points of intervention; and successful street level media work for supporting civil disobedience and creative action.  \r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n<b>Consensus & Facilitation: How to Run Effective Meetings </b><BR>\r\n\r\nEver wonder how your group can have more effective meetings? Strong facilitators are trained, not born!  <i>Smart</i>Meme can give your group tools and strategies for building a decision making process and meeting culture 