odified Organisms (GMOs). <I>Smart</I>Meme also provided facilitation and strategic planning support to help Rural Vermont grow its campaigning capacity. The state of Vermont is the first in the nation to pass a labeling law on GMOs.<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-04 17:09:06',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',6,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'RVTstacked.jpg','1.) This full page ad ran in the capitol city news paper as farmers and supporters geared up to march on the statehouse. 2.) The march, led by farmers, flooded the hearing where Monsanto lobbyists were testifying to VT lawmakers—resulting in historic news coverage. <BR> 3.) This ad, run later in the ’04 session, brought together the host of issues facing VT’s family farmers in the frame of “corporate control.”',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(598,144,'Safe Cosmetics Coalition','“<i>Smart</i>Meme is just that: smart, savvy and visionary.  Their expert facilitation brought a new level of synergy and cohesiveness to our campaign planning meeting. Their brilliant ad design conveyed our message perfectly--with results that far exceeded our expectations.\" --Lisa Archer, Friends of the Earth - U.S.','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org/\" target=_blank>Safe Cosmetics Coalition</A><BR>\r\n<B><BR>\r\nProject:</B> The Campaign for Safe Cosmetics<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Campaign Strategy Consultation, Coalition Facilitation, Ad Concepting, Design and Placement<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme designed a full-page advertisement for the Safe Cosmetics Coalition that ran in USA Today, and helped persuade three target companies to commit to removing hazardous chemicals from their line of products. <BR>\r\n<I><BR>\r\nSmart</I>Meme facilitated a coalition strategy session and designed a comprehensive communications plan for this impressive coalition of women’s, healthcare, and environmental justice organizations. <BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n“<I>Smart</I>Meme has excellent facilitators, experienced campaigners and talented designers -- a great package. <I>Smart</I>Meme designed a powerful ad campaign for us that was a perfect hit and resulted in three top cosmetics companies taking toxic phthalates out of their products. “ -- Stacy Malkan, Campaign for Safe Cosmetics <BR>\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-01 12:15:08',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',7,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'SafeCosm.jpg','This full-page ad ran in USA Today during a key corporate gathering in New York, resulting in the right kind of buzz to ensure swift action by the targets (L’Oreal and Revlon) to put women’s health first and negotiate with the campaigners.',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(599,145,'The SPIN Project','\"<i>Smart</i>Meme connected with activists and advocates from around the country to research their on-the-ground needs, and then created a useful, practical tool to help support the grassroots, real time work. <i>Smart</i>Meme\'s knowledge of both strategic communications and organizing makes them a unique and useful resource.\" --Holly Minch, Executive Director, the SPIN Project','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\nPartner:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.spinproject.org/\" target=_blank>The SPIN Project</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Prime Time for Change: Grassroots Communications Strategies at DNC/RNC 2004<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Project Design, Research, Outreach, Quantitative and Qualitative Analysis, Writing and Editing, Layout and Design <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme partnered with the SPIN project to create a 26 page report that surveyed organizations planning media events at the Democratic and Republican National Conventions and offered analysis and strategic recommendations. <I>Smart</I>Meme trainers have also worked at the SPIN academy, offering support and skills training for interfacing with the media. <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-01 11:27:32',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',7,0,'PRIMETIME4CHANGE!.pdf','pdf',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'PRIMETIME4.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme conducted a survey of organizations mobilizing for the 2004 DNC and RNC and collected nearly 100 responses. The results are explored and analysed in this 26- page report that was published online in July 2004.',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(600,146,'Turn Your Back on Bush',' “Bringing vision, experience, savvy and passion to the work, <I>smart</i>Meme knows how to integrate mass action planning scenarios, media strategy, messaging, and grassroots organizing; they are architects who developed a blue print together with us to design the action from inside out--and provided hands-on support to build it, giving 110% on through the day of action.\" --Jet Heiko, co-founder and Org. Dir., Turn Your Back on Bush','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><BR>\r\n<STRONG>Client:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.turnyourbackonbush.org\">Turn Your Back on Bush</A><BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n<STRONG>Project:</STRONG> On January 20th, You-Turn for Change <BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Strategic Consultation, Facilitation, Action Design, Messaging, Organizing<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nTurn Your Back on Bush brought together people from all walks of life from over 40 states for a dramatic public demonstration of dissent at the January 2005 inauguration. TYBOB brought <I>Smart</I>Meme on board to facilitate a strategy sessions, hammer out action design and logistics, and assist with messaging strategy and on the ground coordination and support. Over 5,000 people, from Military Families to students to Iraq Vets Against the War, engaged in direct nonviolent action to kick off four more years of resistance to the Bush agenda. <BR>\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-01 11:15:09',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',7,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'TYBOB.jpg','Top photo: <i>Smart</i>Meme worked on the ground to design the action, integrating strategy, messaging, and organizing work\r\nBottom photo: 5,000 people, including these Iraq Vets Against the War, participated on January 20th 2005\r\n',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(601,147,'United for Peace & Justice','“Working with <i>smart</i>Meme was an enormous help in our mobilization against the G8 Summit in Brunswick, GA.  Not only did they help us frame our message and provide us some great talking points, but their media support work throughout was invaluable!”--Lisa Fithian, Root Activist Network of Trainers; National Co-chair, UFPJ','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><BR>\r\n\r\n<STRONG>Client:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.unitedforpeace.org/\" target=_blank>United for Peace & Justice</A><BR>\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n<STRONG>Project:</STRONG> State of Emergency: End the War on Iraq! <BR>\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Facilitation, Messaging Document Development, Media Plan Consultation, Remote Media Work<BR>\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\nDuring the 2004 Sea Island G8 Summit, Georgia’s Governor declared a “state of emergency,” seriously infringing on free speech activities. The G8 Justice Media Team worked to defend civil liberties with an offense in the media, and used the media’s lens spread the word about the demonstrations, which called for an end to the Iraq war and unjust economic globalization. United for Peace & Justice worked to assemble the G8 Justice Media team to amplify the voices for change at the G8 Summit; <I>smart</I>Meme assisted with team conference call facilitation; the development of a messaging document; and remote support.<BR>\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>