BACK! Tools & Tactics for Talking to the Media</b><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFrustrated with the corporate media ignoring or mis-representing your efforts to make change? Ever been cornered on camera, clipped out, or mis-quoted? Never, ever talked to the corporate media---or duck and hide when the paparazzi shows up? Well, these workshops are for anyone who wants to practice being a more effective message-maker and spokesperson while gaining skills and confidence in wrangling the press. We can offer basic training for media-spokes people and practice how to give a good interview; the basics of different mediums, the <i>rules of engagement</i> and discuss how to move your <i>core messages</i>. \r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMore intensive trainings explore how to increase your chances of earning coverage for your event or campaign by developing multi-pronged, strategic media plans. We can look at what makes a good press event and how to organize and promote one. We can examine some sample press releases, press kits, and various tools and tactics for activists who want to engage with the mainstream media and win the Battle of the Story. \r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Video Activism</b><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nOne of the core lessons emphasized by <i>Smart</i>Meme is that “If we don’t tell our own story, the story will be told about us.” We explore how to use video technology as a tool to tell our own stories, both to each other--in the form of documentation of events and actions we capture and share on tape—and to the world—in the form of “B-roll” for television networks. <i>Smart</i>Meme’s video team has extensive experience as broadcast media professionals who have made award-winning front-line documentary films and produced a range of independent and educational film projects. They can share skills from street level video shooting to producing and successfully distributing a documentary for your campaign, action, or group.\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Non-violent Direct Action Skills and Action Design</b><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme trainers can offer civil disobedience and direct action preparation sessions for your action or mobilization, covering the basics of street safety and exploring action outcomes and scenarios for small groups to mass mobilizations. <i>Smart</i>Meme can also tailor trainings to include in-depth pieces on building strong affinity groups; integrated messaging and action logic; mass-action design and the points of intervention; and successful street level media work for supporting civil disobedience and creative action.  \r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Consensus & Facilitation: How to Run Effective Meetings </b><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEver wonder how your group can have more effective meetings? Strong facilitators are trained, not born!  <i>Smart</i>Meme can give your group tools and strategies for building a decision making process and meeting culture that gets things done and makes space for all voices. You will learn about making do-able, goals driven agendas; managing group dynamics; and moving your group through a formal consensus process.\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>','','2005-04-09 03:07:44',42,0,1,'',0,'',1,'',0,0,'','',0,8,'',0,'',