ms and protect endangered salmon species in Northern California’s Klamath basin. In July 2004 representatives of the tribes and other groups traveled to Scotland to protest Scottish Power’s annual shareholder’s meeting and attracted international media attention and public support to their cause. <I>Smart</I>Meme also designed a provocative direct-mail piece for the campaign to build local support in California and Oregon. </P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:03:11',59,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',2,0,'','img',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'FORstacked.jpg','Showing the front four of an eight panel design, this direct mail piece illustrated the cultural, ecological, and economic significance of restoring the salmon to their home in the Klamath’s upper basin. The back panels comprise a historical map of the Klamath Basin.',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(737,136,'Genewise','Partnering with <i>smart</i>Meme is about passion for justice meeting passion for justice; it\'s about empowering each other. Their effect is like a magnifying glass that works with you to set the right fire at the right time…”.\r\n--Christie Phillips, Genewise Coordinator','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.genewise.org/\" target=_blank>Genewise</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Mac & Genes<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Action Design; Graphic Design<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme worked with Genewise to design this “Mac & Genes” box—a spoof on Kraft’s flagship brand—to support the campaign targeting Kraft to remove Genetically Engineered (GE) ingredients from their products. Activists dressed in the box (and Butt Head Phillip Morris) went trick-or-treating in Kraft CEO Betsy Holden’s neighborhood to bring