on, New Yorkers started mobilizing immediately to protect the memory of September 11 from exploitation by the hawks in the GOP, and trumpet a resounding NO to the Bush agenda. <I>smart</I>Meme and Adopt-an-Activist partnered to bring <I>smart</I>Meme to New York for a six week project that became the “Reality Check A31 Media Team.” Reality Check trained activists, amplified voices, and made media space to tell the stories about peace, democracy, nonviolent civil disobedience at the 2004 RNC. <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-07 06:09:36',60,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',6,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'RNCmont.jpg','From top to bottom: <BR>1.) Demonstrators in Herald Square chanting behind the live shot of “Hardball with Chris Matthews” on August 31st <BR>2.) Demonstrators “die in” at Halliburton on August 31st, 2004<BR>3.) September 1st: Reality Check-organized press conference to free the 1,000+ detainees at Pier 57.<BR>4.) Aug 29th UFPJ march live on C-SPAN',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(744,142,'Reclaim the Commons','\"<i>Smart</i>Meme provided invaluable creative, strategic, and practical guidance for the Reclaim the Commons media team. They skillfully combined training with direct support for the mobilization so that not only did we succeed in our media goals, but our whole media team came out of the mobilization better equipped with fundamental social change skills.” \r\n--Rebecca Tarbotton, Prog. Dir., The Int\'l Society for Ecology and Culture','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<STRONG>Partner:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.reclaimthecommons.net/\" target=_blank>Reclaim the Commons</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Reclaim the Commons<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Training, Messaging, Media Strategy Support, Mobilization Media Support <BR>\r\n\r\n\