(opposition research, media climate assessment, etc)\r\n--Media Work (media list building, collaboration on media releases and statements)\r\n--Outreach & Promotion (tabling, mailings, etc)\r\n--Organizing and Logistics (for smartMeme trainings and other STORY events)\r\n--Development Work (the hands on work of building this exciting new organization!)\r\n\r\nAll internships require working at smartMeme\'s office in beautiful BURLINGTON, VERMONT for a minimum of 14 hours per week for a period of three months (BETWEEN JUNE-OCT). \r\n\r\nInterns work with an experienced staff member who designs and oversees the completion of a special project. Interns participate in the day-to-day operations of the STORY program as well. Some travel may be required to STORY related trainings and events.\r\n\r\nSmartMeme  will cover commuting and travel expenses into the field required by the position (interns may travel to trainings and events throughout the summer). \r\n\r\nA small housing stipend is available to the right candidate who can put in 20+ hours/week. \r\n\r\nAt the completion of the internship, each intern is given a chance to evaluate their internship, a letter of reference, and the waiver of fees to smartMeme\'s autumn STORY gathering...and some cool smartMeme gear!\r\n\r\nIF YOU ARE INTERESTED, PLEASE SEND A RESUME AND COVER LETTER OF INTEREST (YOUR STORY!) TO:\r\n\r\nSTORY@SMARTMEME.COM\r\n\r\nOR\r\n\r\nsmartMeme\r\n19 Church St, Suite 10\r\nBurlington, Vermont 05401\r\n\r\nNo Phone Calls Please.\r\n\r\nThe smartMeme collective is committed to challenging historic patterns of oppression and political marginalization.  Young activists from working class backgrounds, LBGTQ people, womyn, and youth of color are particularly encouraged to apply. \r\n\r\n** A housing stipend is available to the right candidate who can put in 20+ hours/week. Please tell us in your cover letter how much money per month you would require as a stipend in order to do this internship. **\r\n','