uccessfully targeting our audience with an effective message and strategy.\" \r\n--Anne Rabe, BE SAFE Network, Center for Health, Environment & Justice. ','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.chej.org/\" target=_blank>CHEJ</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Project:</B> Bad News Comes in 3\'s <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Messaging Strategy Consultation; Message Document Development <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen the Center for Health, Environment & Justice (CHEJ) was looking to launch their report on the toxic impacts of PVC, they worked with <I>smart</I>Meme strategists to develop their messaging strategy, and integrate a corporate campaigning savvy to move their work forward. </P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:24:38',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',1,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'CHEJ.jpg','Bad News Comes in 3’s',0,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1150,135,'Friends of the River','“<i>Smart</i>Meme’s team facilitated our first coalition meetings and fostered trust among diverse groups while moving our agenda forward. <i>Smart</i>Meme’s understanding of cross-cultural issues enabled them to bring together our diverse group of Native American Tribes and conservation groups to build a campaign plan and get it off the ground.”\r\n--Dr. Craig Tucker, Klamath River Campaign Coordinator, Karuk Tribe','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.friendsoftheriver.org/\" target=_blank>Friends of the River</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Bring the Salmon Home! <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Cross Cultural Facilitation, Coalition Building, Assistance Designing a Media Strategy, Campaign Strategy Consultation, Outreach Materials Concepting, Design and Production<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme provided consultation and cross cultural facilitation to help build a coalition uniting environmentalists, four tribal governments and commercial fishermen in a campaign to remove dams and protect endangered salmon species in Northern California’s Klamath basin. In July 2004 representatives of the tribes and other groups traveled to Scotland to protest Scottish Power’s annual shareholder’s meeting and attracted international media attention and public support to their cause. <I>Smart</I>Meme also designed a provocative direct-mail piece for the campaign to build local support in California and Oregon. </P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:25:19',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',2,0,'','img',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'FORstacked.jpg','Showing the front four of an eight panel design, this direct mail piece illustrated the cultural, ecological, and economic significance of restoring the salmon to their home in the Klamath’s upper basin. The back panels comprise a historical map of the Klamath Basin.',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1151,148,'Center for Economic Justice','\"As a campaigner at the World Bank Bonds Boycott in 2004, I worked with <i>smart</i>Meme to raise the profile of the struggle for global justice with creative communications strategies. We sold the World Bank on eBay during the Fall meetings, which ruffled a few feathers at the Bank and resulted in international news coverage for our campaign!\" --Basav Sen, former World Bank Bonds Boycott campaigner','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://econjustice.net/wbbb/\" target=_blank>Center for Economic Justice</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Challenging Global Apartheid<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Media Plan Development, Messaging Consultation, Media List Building, Media Work, Action Design <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme provided media support and strategy consultation to economic justice advocates from the World Bank Bonds Boycott. <I>Smart</I>Meme attracted national attention to the global campaign by orchestrating a widely reported media stunt in which the World Bank was “sold” on eBay.<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:24:00',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',1,0,'','img',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'World-Bank-eBay.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme designed this action to raise the profile of the World Bank Bonds Boycott at the 2004 Fall Meetings of the IMF & World Bank, and earned media coverage in The Financial Times, CNNmoney, Reuters, and the Times Of India.',1,'',0,0,'','','right','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1152,136,'Genewise','Partnering with <i>smart</i>Meme is about passion for justice meeting passion for justice; it\'s about empowering each other. Their effect is like a magnifying glass that works with you to set the right fire at the right time…”.\r\n--Christie Phillips, Genewise Coordinator','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.genewise.org/\" target=_blank>Genewise</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Mac & Genes<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Action Design; Graphic Design<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme worked with Genewise to design this “Mac & Genes” box—a spoof on Kraft’s flagship brand—to support the campaign targeting Kraft to remove Genetically Engineered (GE) ingredients from their products. Activists dressed in the box (and Butt Head Phillip Morris) went trick-or-treating in Kraft CEO Betsy Holden’s neighborhood to bring the campaign to the top of the corporate food chain. </P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:25:54',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',2,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'Genewise.jpg','Genewise activists trick-or-treat in Kraft CEO Betsy Holden’s neighborhood.',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1153,132,'Greenpeace','\"<i>Smart</i>Meme worked with us to develop the campaign messaging curriculum we are using to train our top activists around the country. <i>Smart</i>Meme\'s unique strategy tools and messaging insights will help us not only get our message out but challenge some of the underlying assumptions that are fueling environmental destruction.\"\r\n-- Phil Radford, Field Director, Greenpeace USA','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.greenpeaceusa.org/\" target=_blank>Greenpeace</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Moving Our Messages <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Produced Training Curriculum<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme designed a full campaign message-development curriculum for Greenpeace to use in their rigorous organizer training programs. The curriculum included a wide range of skills areas including messaging strategy, branding, analysis, polling research, and training campaign spokespeople. <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:41:05',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',3,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'Greenpeace.jpg','Another great example of Greenpeace’s media savvy, high profile action for the Earth. <i>Smart</i>Meme contributed to the Greenpeace’s 2004 organizer training curriculum. ',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1154,137,'Hawaii GEAN','“<i>Smart</i>Meme helped our grassroots group develop a media strategy for publicizing the hazards of the genetically engineered papaya. Working from our homes and farms in Hawaii with the help and support of <i>smart</i>Meme, we were able to get our story published in the New York Times, USA Today, the Miami Herald, and dozens of other major media markets across the US and abroad.”  --Noli Hoye, GMO Free Hawaii','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.higean.org/\" target=_blank>Hawaii Genetic Engineering Action Network</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Sounding the Alarm about Genetic Contamination <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Support to Design Media Strategy, Campaign Messaging and Media Plan <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme assisted a coalition of farmers, environmentalists and concerned citizens in launching a public education campaign around genetic contamination of the papaya crop. The group used <I>smart</I>Meme’s tools to develop a comprehensive media plan and organize a media event that alerted the public to the serious dangerous of genetically engineered agriculture. </P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:27:42',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',3,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'HIGEAN.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme helped farmers and activists tell their story about contamination of Hawaii’s papaya.',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1155,138,'Mobilization for Food Sovereignty','“<i>Smart</i>Meme’s work was critical to our coalition\'s success in disseminating our message of resistance and alternatives to industrialized agriculture. We were up against the propaganda machines of the USDA and some of the richest corporations in the world. The fact that people still heard our story speaks to <i>smart</i>Meme’s success in framing, messaging, and strategy  work.” --Tracy Lerman, Senior Organizer, Public Citizen ','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> Mobilization for Food Sovereignty<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Project:</B> Hungry for Justice? <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Media Strategy, Messaging, Action Design and Mobilization Media Support <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme worked with a coalition of environmental, family farm and direct action groups to organize a mass mobilization at the US Department of Agriculture’s Corporate Agriculture Ministerial in Sacramento, CA in June 2003. Our support for the mobilization included action design, messaging, media strategy and anchoring the mobilization media team. The mobilization resulted in international media coverage as well as the United State’s largest protest against genetic engineering and corporate control of agriculture. <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:28:41',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',4,0,'','img',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'Mob4FoodSov.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme was onsite to amplify the voices calling for people’s food sovereignty at the 2003 Sacramento Ministerial, a pre-WTO meeting of Agriculture Ministers and agri-business corporations.',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1156,139,'National Family Farm Coalition','\"The old saying goes that a picture paints a thousand words, but from my exciting time in a <i>smart</i>Meme workshop, I\'d say a few words well chosen with the help of <i>smart</i>Meme may paint a thousand pictures, and mobilize thousands of our citizens to get involved in unleashing real democracy in our country.“ -- George Naylor, President, National Family Farm Coalition, and Iowa soybean farmer','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.nffc.net/\" target=_blank>National Family Farm Coalition</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Project:</B> Stories about our Seeds <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Training<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe NFFC represents family farm and rural groups in 30 states whose members\' face the challenge of the deepening economic recession in rural communities caused primarily by low farm prices and the increasing corporate control of agriculture. <I>Smart</I>Meme attended the 2004 summer meetings of the National Family Farm Coalition to offer strategy support and a “power of story” training for NFFC staff and membership. <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:47:26',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',5,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'NFFC1.jpg','<i>Smart</i>Meme  provided media support for a farmer’s action at the 2003 Sacramento Agriculture Ministerial, where US farmers symbolically dumped genetically modified corn outside of then Secretary of Agriculture Anne Venemen’s gala reception. ',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1157,140,'Reality Check Media/Adopt-an-Activist','“<i>Smart</i>Meme had incredible experience in projecting grassroots messages into the corporate media. Adopt-an-activist partnered with <i>smart</i>Meme to support the Reality Check Media Team, to get the story straight about direct action at the RNC. It was the largest series of demonstrations outside a political convention, ever. Front page all week. The rest is history.” --Meddle Bolger, Director, Adopt-an-Activist','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPartner:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.adoptanactivist.org/\" target=_blank>Adopt-an-Activist</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Reality Check! <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Organizing, Training, Media Support <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen the Republican Party selected New York City to hold its annual convention, New Yorkers started mobilizing immediately to protect the memory of September 11 from exploitation by the hawks in the GOP, and trumpet a resounding NO to the Bush agenda. <I>smart</I>Meme and Adopt-an-Activist partnered to bring <I>smart</I>Meme to New York for a six week project that became the “Reality Check A31 Media Team.” Reality Check trained activists, amplified voices, and made media space to tell the stories about peace, democracy, nonviolent civil disobedience at the 2004 RNC. <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:30:29',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',6,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'RNCmont.jpg','From top to bottom: <BR>1.) Demonstrators in Herald Square chanting behind the live shot of “Hardball with Chris Matthews” on August 31st <BR>2.) Demonstrators “die in” at Halliburton on August 31st, 2004<BR>3.) September 1st: Reality Check-organized press conference to free the 1,000+ detainees at Pier 57.<BR>4.) Aug 29th UFPJ march live on C-SPAN',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1158,142,'Reclaim the Commons','\"<i>Smart</i>Meme provided invaluable creative, strategic, and practical guidance for the Reclaim the Commons media team. They skillfully combined training with direct support for the mobilization so that not only did we succeed in our media goals, but our whole media team came out of the mobilization better equipped with fundamental social change skills.” \r\n--Rebecca Tarbotton, Prog. Dir., The Int\'l Society for Ecology and Culture','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<STRONG>Partner:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.reclaimthecommons.net/\" target=_blank>Reclaim the Commons</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> Reclaim the Commons<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Training, Messaging, Media Strategy Support, Mobilization Media Support <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme supported a cross section of activists in building a media team at the June 2004 mobilization against Bio 2004 (the world\'s largest biotechnology and pharmaceutical conference). We provided messaging support, training in mobilization media strategy as well as on-site skills support throughout the actions.<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:31:05',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',6,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'RTC1.jpg','Bay area residents announce their intention to shut down the BIO conference at a press conference at the Moscone Center. Photo- Jeff Paterson',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1159,143,'Rural Vermont','“In 2004, Rural Vermont took on Big Agribusiness in a classic David and Goliath struggle. <I>Smart</I>Meme was our slingshot, providing us with an integrated package of services, from action design to advertising to on-the-ground media work, they helped us hit the giant right between the eyes. Reporters are still talking about our great campaign. <I>Smart</I>Meme Rocks!” --Amy Shollenberger, Policy Director, Rural Vermont','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.ruralvermont.org/\" target=_blank>Rural Vermont</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Project:</B> One Contaminated Farm is One too Many!<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Message Development, Campaign Strategy Consulting, Action Design, Facilitation, Strategic Planning Consultation, Media Work, Print Advertisements<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme provided strategic consulting, direct media support, and designed two full page ads for Rural Vermont, a statewide farmer advocacy group working for a “Time Out” on Genetically Modified Organisms (GMOs). <I>Smart</I>Meme also provided facilitation and strategic planning support to help Rural Vermont grow its campaigning capacity. The state of Vermont is the first in the nation to pass a labeling law on GMOs.<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:36:23',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',6,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'RVTstacked.jpg','1.) This full page ad ran in the capitol city news paper as farmers and supporters geared up to march on the statehouse. 2.) The march, led by farmers, flooded the hearing where Monsanto lobbyists were testifying to VT lawmakers—resulting in historic news coverage. <BR> 3.) This ad, run later in the ’04 session, brought together the host of issues facing VT’s family farmers in the frame of “corporate control.”',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1160,144,'Safe Cosmetics Coalition','“<i>Smart</i>Meme is just that: smart, savvy and visionary.  Their expert facilitation brought a new level of synergy and cohesiveness to our campaign planning meeting. Their brilliant ad design conveyed our message perfectly--with results that far exceeded our expectations.\" --Lisa Archer, Friends of the Earth - U.S.','<P align=left><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=#000000 size=2><STRONG><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClient:</STRONG> <A href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org/\" target=_blank>Safe Cosmetics Coalition</A><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProject:</B> The Campaign for Safe Cosmetics<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Services Provided:</B> Campaign Strategy Consultation, Coalition Facilitation, Ad Concepting, Design and Placement<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I>Smart</I>Meme designed a full-page advertisement for the Safe Cosmetics Coalition that ran in USA Today, and helped persuade three target companies to commit to removing hazardous chemicals from their line of products. <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<I><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSmart</I>Meme facilitated a coalition strategy session and designed a comprehensive communications plan for this impressive coalition of women’s, healthcare, and environmental justice organizations. <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n“<I>Smart</I>Meme has excellent facilitators, experienced campaigners and talented designers -- a great package. <I>Smart</I>Meme designed a powerful ad campaign for us that was a perfect hit and resulted in three top cosmetics companies taking toxic phthalates out of their products. “ -- Stacy Malkan, Campaign for Safe Cosmetics <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</P></FONT>','','2005-04-12 07:53:08',15,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',7,0,'','',0,1,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'SafeCosm.jpg','This full-page ad ran in USA Today during a key corporate cosmetics gathering in New York, resulting in the right kind of buzz to ensure swift action by the targets (L’Oreal, Revlon and Unilever) to negotiate with the campaigners. The result was an immediate victory for women\'s health.',1,'',0,0,'','','left','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1161,145,'The SPIN Project','\"<i>Smart</i>Meme connected with activists and advocates from around the country to research 