trategies, movement building, and how the stories we tell can reshape our world.<br /><br />Sessions will focus on the power of story, the landscape of media, leadership and organization, and points of intervention to change the story for a more hopeful future.<br /><br />MORE INFORMATION COMING SOON at www.smartMeme.com<br /><br />** SAVE THE DATE ** SAVE THE DATE**<br /><br />September 29-October 3, 2005 </body></html>','','2005-07-25 18:44:59',9,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',0,0,'','',0,8,'',0,'','2005-07-19',1,0,0,0,'retreatlake.jpg','The STORY Retreat, Incite/Insight, will take place at the Owl\'s Nest Lodge in Andover, New Hampshire September 29-Oct 3 2005',1,'',0,0,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1193,211,'SmartMeme Holiday Letter & Highlights 2005','Thank you to everyone who took part in making smartMeme\'s story so sucessfull in 2005!\r\n','Dear friends, family, colleagues and supporters, \r\n\r\nWarm regards from the four corners of the country we call home: San Francisco, Chicago,  Burlington (Vermont), and the Skokomish Nation in Washington State.  \r\n\r\nCan you believe it is almost 2006?! When we last wrote you, our little organization was on  the verge of a big growth spurt—and here we are, having accomplished so much! We are  looking forward to a holiday season of gratitude, rest, and refl ection. With your support, the smartMeme collective has made 2005 an amazing year of smartMeme collective has made 2005 an amazing year of smart inspiration and action. We launched our new youth training program STORY (Strategy  Training and Organizing Resources for Youth), and continued providing direct support  to grassroots activists working to reframe the debates on the war, the prison industrial  complex, farmworker justice, toxics, indigenous rights and genetic engineering—among  others. We are working to amplify the voices of movements for democracy, justice, peace  and ecological sanity, and to build a culture of strategy in progressive social change  movements in this country.  \r\n\r\nSo, in our second year as a full-time, for real, non-profi t organization, we have trained  over 500 activists, worked in partnership with 22 grassroots groups, and been in 15 states!  SmartMeme has been spotted collaborating with agitators from Mississippi to Maine—SmartMeme has been spotted collaborating with agitators from Mississippi to Maine—Smart from Bellingham to Houston—from Boston to Los Angeles—training, strategizing, telling  stories and sharing victories.  \r\n\r\nYour support helps us make all of this possible. It fuels our everyday work too—keeps the  website up, provides resources for our internship program, keeps the phone lines humming,  keeps the (recycled!) paper in the printers...Helps us help grassroots movements grow and  strengthen for the long haul ahead and the stories we’ve yet to tell... \r\n\r\nIn 2006, we are looking forward to continuing to support grassroots organizing and advocacy  work with the power of story and strategic communications. With the solidarity of your gift  this season, we can continue to grow and bring story-based strategy to the forefront of social  movements in this country.  We look forward to hearing from you, and wish you hope and a joyous holiday, and a very  happy and peaceful new year!  \r\n\r\nFor the Earth, \r\n\r\nThe smartMeme collective \r\n\r\n James John Bell \r\nDoyle Canning \r\nJ Cookson\r\nPatrick Reinsborough','','2005-12-29 22:29:16',9,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',0,0,'smartMeme Highlights 05.pdf','pdf',0,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'retreatlake.jpg','',0,'',0,0,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1194,211,'SmartMeme Holiday Letter & Highlights 2005','Thank you to everyone who took part in making smartMeme\'s story so sucessfull in 2005!\r\n','Dear friends, family, colleagues and supporters, <br>\r\n\r\nWarm regards from the four corners of the country we call home: San Fran