s. We are working to amplify the voices of movements for democracy, justice, peace  and ecological sanity, and to build a culture of strategy in progressive social change  movements in this country.  <br><br>\r\n\r\nSo, in our second year as a full-time, for real, non-profit organization, we have trained  over 500 activists, worked in partnership with 22 grassroots groups, and been in 15 states!  SmartMeme has been spotted collaborating with agitators from Mississippi to Maine—from Bellingham to Houston—from Boston to Los Angeles—training, strategizing, telling  stories and sharing victories.  <br><br>\r\n\r\nYour support helps us make all of this possible. It fuels our everyday work too—keeps this  website up, provides resources for our internship program, keeps the phone lines humming,  keeps the (recycled!) paper in the printers...Helps us help grassroots movements grow and  strengthen for the long haul ahead and the stories we’ve yet to tell... <br><br>\r\n\r\nIn 2006, we are looking forward to continuing to support grassroots organizing and advocacy work with the power of story and strategic communications. With the solidarity of your gift  this season, we can continue to grow and bring story-based strategy to the forefront of social  movements in this country.  We look forward to hearing from you, and wish you hope and a joyous holiday, and a very  happy and peaceful new year!  <br><br>\r\n\r\nFor the Earth, <br><br>\r\n\r\nThe smartMeme collective <br><br>\r\n\r\nJames John Bell <br>\r\nDoyle Canning <br>\r\nJ Cookson <br>\r\nPatrick Reinsborough','','2005-12-29 22:45:14',9,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',0,0,'smartMeme Highlights 05.pdf','pdf',0,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'incite table.jpg','Download smartMeme highlights \'05 by clicking on the PDF icon',1,'',0,0,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1198,211,'Jobs @ smartMeme!','Want to work for smartMeme? We\'re looking for a Youth Organizer AND a Development Associate...','<b> Download smartMeme HIGHLIGHTS 2005 by clicking on the PDF icon to your right! </b><br><br>\r\n\r\n1) JOB ANNOUNCEMENT: STORY Program Youth Organizer <br>\r\n \r\nDeadline: Rolling Application Process Through March 15th but position will be filled as soon as possible<br>\r\n \r\nWanted: Peace, Justice, Ecological Sanity…<br>\r\n \r\nYouth organizer to join a dynamic, collaborative movement-building project focused on strategy, training, and communications! <br><br>\r\n\r\n9 MONTH POSITION (April 1–Dec 31) with potential to grow into a permanent position <br>\r\nSTARTING SALARY $24,000 (plus flexible health care package and vacation) <br><br>\r\n \r\nBASED IN: Burlington, VT or San Francisco, CA \r\n \r\nYOU ARE:<br>\r\n \r\n* A 20-something youth organizer with a background in Strategic Campaigning/Training/Advocacy Communications, a commitment to fundamental social change and the motivation to work for it. <br>\r\n* Someone with two or more years working as an organizer/coordinator/campaigner in a progressive social change organization. \r\n* A skilled networker, communicator, trainer, facilitator and organizer. <br>\r\n* Organized, accountable, highly motivated and politically mature, with a commitment to self care and healthy relationships with work and with colleagues. <br>\r\n* A creative team player (have prioritization and delegation skills, flexibility, and collaborative approach). <br>\r\n* Committed to an anti-oppression praxis. <br>\r\n* A leader and change agent who deeply shares the mission and values of the organization. <br>\r\n* Experienced in strategy development and communications (strongly preferred). <br>\r\n \r\nWE ARE: <br>\r\n \r\n* A collective of social change practitioners building an institution to support holistic movement building for justice, democracy, peace and ecological sanity. <br>\r\n* Committed to “building a culture of strategy” in grassroots social change movements. This includes a focus on developing training and strategy models using “narrative power analysis” and “story-based strategies” to challenge the underlying assumptions that perpetuate militarism, racism, injustice and ecological destruction. <br>\r\n* A fun crew who loves big ideas. <br>\r\n* A fresh, growing organization with lots of room to explore and experiment. <br><br>\r\n \r\nSmartMeme’s STORY program (Strategy, Training and Organizing Resources for Youth) strengthens youth movements and builds strategic capacities in youth networks. The program offers trainings, partnership projects, and movement building gatherings. We have partnered and trained with dozen of grassroots youth groups including: Student Farmworker Alliance, National Youth & Student Peace Coalition, Student Environmental Action Coalition, Boston Mobilization, and the Nuclear Age Peace Foundation. <br><br>\r\n \r\nJOB DESCRIPTION:<br>\r\n\r\nThe Organizer will--<br>\r\n* Work with the collective to implement the STORY program’s outreach and organizing efforts. <br>\r\n* Coordinate logistics and outreach for the 2006 STORY youth strategy retreat. <br>\r\n* Work to build the strategic and organizational capacity of grassroots youth groups through STORY’s partnership and training program.  <br>\r\n* Coordinate and shepherd the development of the STORY Board, volunteers and interns. <br>\r\n* Publicly represent the organization, the program, and its values. <br>\r\n* Travel to work with amazing youth activists on some of the most important issues of our times.  Applicants must have the ability to work while out of the office, travel by air extensively, and be away from home for up to 2 weeks at a time. <br>\r\n \r\nThe STORY Organizer will work in close collaboration with the smartMeme Core Collective as part of an extended collective model.<br> \r\n \r\nROLLING DEADLINE: (February 15-March 15 or until position filled.) We anticipate filling the position as soon as possible so if you are interested please apply as soon as you can! <br>\r\n \r\nSend a Letter of Interest telling us “Your Story,” and why you would be a good fit with the smartMeme team. Please also attach a resume with references and send TO: <br>\r\n \r\nBY EMAIL: story@smartmeme.com <br>\r\nMAIL:  19 Church St Suite 10 Burlington Vermont 05401\r\n \r\nNo Phone Calls Please.   <br><br>\r\n\r\n2) JOB ANNOUNCEMENT: Development Associate <br><br>\r\n \r\nDeadline: Rolling Application Process Through March 15th but position will be filled as soon as possible <br>\r\n \r\nWe’re looking for a Development Associate to join a dynamic, collaborative movement building project focused on strategy, training, and communications! <br>\r\n \r\n9 month position (April 1 – Dec 31) with potential to grow into a permanent position. <br>\r\nStarting wage $12.75/hour, Part time (2-3 days a week) Flexible hours<br>\r\nBased in:  Burlington, VT <br><br>\r\n \r\nSmartMeme is an innovative and fast-paced non-profit organization, implementing dynamic programs with national reach in the fields of strategic communication and movement building. We are seeking the right individual who can work with us to develop and implement fundraising systems for our organization.  <br>\r\n \r\nWe are seeking a development associate to assist us in organizational development, day-to-day office management, and securing funding for our programs. Candidate must be a self-starter, well organized and highly motivated. Preferably you are experienced in grant writing, donor communications, and general office management. Experience in a social change organization is a big plus. <br>\r\n \r\nResponsibilities include grant solicitation, researching grant prospects, foundation and donor outreach, some grant writing, and general assistance to smartMeme’s development and fundraising efforts. Your tasks may also include developing our database, website administration and integration of an online fundraising program, development projects and events  (such as house parties and mailings), and general assistance to the core staff (scheduling, answering general enquiries, clerical support). Development Associate will work closely with the core collective. Part-time, flexible hours. Position will ideally grow over time. <br>\r\n \r\nCandidate must possess strong communication skills (written and interpersonal), have strong computer skills in MSWord and Excel (we run on Macintosh OSX) and must be able to work well with timelines and budget. Person must also share the core values of the organization and feel political affinity with our mission. <br>\r\n \r\nThe Development Associate will work in very close collaboration with the smartMeme core collective as part of an extended collective model. <br>\r\n \r\nRolling Deadline (February 15-March 15 or until position is filled.) We anticipate filling the position as soon as possible, so if you are interested please apply as soon as you can! <br>\r\n \r\nSend a Letter of Interest telling us “Your Story,” and why you would be a good fit with the smartMeme team. Please also attach a resume with references and send TO: <br>\r\n \r\nBY EMAIL: story@smartmeme.com <br>\r\nMAIL:  19 Church St Suite 10 Burlington Vermont 05401 <br>\r\n \r\nNo Phone Calls Please. <br><br>\r\n \r\nSmartMeme is an equal opportunity employer committed to identifying and developing the skills and leadership of people from diverse backgrounds and challenging historic patterns of political marginalization and oppression. People of Color, working-class people, differently-abled people and LGBT persons are strongly encouraged to apply.','','2006-02-14 22:59:51',9,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',0,0,'smartMeme Highlights 05.pdf','pdf',0,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'incite table.jpg','Download smartMeme highlights \'05 by clicking on the PDF icon',1,'',0,0,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1199,211,'Jobs @ smartMeme!','Want to work for smartMeme? We\'re looking for a Youth Organizer AND a Development Associate...','