\n\r\nAn intimate 3-day retreat at the historic Highlander Center in Tennessee focused on vision, strategy work, cross-cultural movement building and leadership development for young peace activists. The Collaborative emphasizes deepening the alliance of Iraq Veterans Against the War and youth and student peace networks, particularly those working on counter recruitment in youth of color communities. At the gathering, we will apply some of smartMeme’s story-based strategy tools, and deepen relationships amongst young people working to end the war in communities across the country. We will gather to explore strategies that can harness the historic moment and help to build a strong, grassroots peace movement led by those most directly affected. \r\n \r\n<b>Our Goals</b><br><br>\r\n\r\n•	Build deep alliances between young Iraq Veterans and youth-based antiwar networks<br>\r\n•	Provide a space for building relationships across constituencies<br>\r\n•	Facilitate anti-war strategy development using story-based strategy models<br>\r\n•	Amplify the voices of youth and young veterans in the anti-war movement and build leadership capacity amongst these constituencies<br>\r\n•	Encourage the building of a long-term peace movement that can challenge the assumptions underlying racism, militarism and war.<br>\r\n\r\n<b>Your Support</b><br><br>\r\n\r\nIf you want to offer solidarity and support to the youth and Veterans who are offering us new stories and new visions of what an antiwar movement in the US could look like, please make the most generous contribution you can. Your charitable gift can help to bring young Iraq Vets who are speaking out against the war, and young visionaries of the next generation of antiwar activism, together at Highlander to share stories and develop strategies to end the Iraq occupation and challenge US Empire. <br><br>\r\n\r\nNo one at the White House is going to end this war for us. It is up to us to dare to be more creative, strategic, and powerful!