o this end, smartMeme’s youth program, STORY, is convening a gathering this summer at the historic Highlander Center in New Market, Tennessee to bring young Iraq Vets and youth anti-war leaders together to strategize about ending this war. We feel this gathering is an essential next step in the process of building a strong, strategic anti-war movement.  </strong><br /></p><p> <br />\r\n\r\n<b>THE SPACE....</b><br><br>\r\nAn intimate 3-day retreat at the historic Highlander Center in Tennessee [hyperlink: www.highlandercenter.org] focused on vision, strategy work, cross-cultural movement building and leadership development for young peace activists. The Collaborative emphasizes deepening the alliance of Iraq Veterans Against the War and youth and student peace networks, particularly those working on counter recruitment in youth of color communities. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>THE HAPPENINGS....</b><br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Relationship Building * Story-Based Strategizing * Capacity Building * Movement Building</b><br><br>\r\n\r\nAt the gathering, we will apply some of smartMeme’s story-based strategy tools, and deepen relationships amongst young people working to end the war in communities across the country. We will gather to explore strategies that can harness the historic moment and help to build a strong, grassroots peace movement led by those most directly affected.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<br /><br />In a rural retreat setting, we will take three days to explore narrative power analysis, story-based strategies, creative direct action at the point(s) of assumption, and more! <br /><br />The Collaborative will be a unique and intimate gathering of young activists (18 - 30 years old) working for an end to the war in Iraq and building a movement for justice in the US. The retreat will offer a reflective forum for deep discussions on the system(s), our strategies, movement building, and how the stories we tell can reshape our world.<br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>THE PARTICIPANTS....</b><br><br>\r\nThe gathering will bring together Iraq Veterans, Conscientious Objectors, Counter-Recruitment Activists, Youth from Military Families, Community Organizers, and Strategy People from across the U.S. that are currently doing work around the war. <br><br> \r\n\r\n For more information about STORY <a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/article.php?list=type&type=50\">click here</a><br /><br />For more information about <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">smart</span>Meme <a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/article.php?list=type&type=4\">click here</a></p>','','2006-05-06 01:01:25',70,1,1,'about incite/insight',0,'',1,'',0,0,'','',0,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'highlander.jpg','Highlander will be the site of the 2006 STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq',1,'',0,0,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1220,211,'Jobs @ smartMeme!','Want to work for smartMeme? We\'re looking for a Youth Organizer AND a Development Associate...','<b>1) JOB ANNOUNCEMENT: STORY Program Youth Organizer </b><br><br>\r\n \r\nDeadline: Rolling Application Process Through March 15th but position will be filled as soon as possible<br><br>\r\n \r\nWanted: Peace, Justice, Ecological Sanity…<br><br>\r\n \r\nYouth organizer to join a dynamic, collaborative movement-building project focused on strategy, training, and communications! <br><br>\r\n\r\n9 MONTH POSITION (April 1–Dec 31) with potential to grow into a permanent position <br>\r\nSTARTING SALARY $24,000 (plus flexible health care package and vacation) <br><br>\r\n \r\nBASED IN: Burlington, VT or San Francisco, CA <br><br>\r\n \r\nYOU ARE:<br><br>\r\n \r\n* A youth organizer with a background in Strategic Campaigning/Training/Advocacy Communications, a commitment to fundamental social change and the motivation to work for it. <br>\r\n* Someone with two or more years working as an organizer/coordinator/campaigner in a progressive social change organization. <br>\r\n* A skilled networker, communicator, trainer, facilitator and organizer. <br>\r\n* Organized, accountable, highly motivated and politically mature, with a commitment to self care and healthy relationships with work and with colleagues. <br>\r\n* A creative team player (have prioritization and delegation skills, flexibility, and collaborative approach). <br>\r\n* Committed to an anti-oppression praxis. <br>\r\n* A leader and change agent who deeply shares the mission and values of the organization. <br>\r\n* Experienced in strategy development and communications (strongly preferred). <br><br>\r\n \r\nWE ARE: <br><br>\r\n \r\n* A collective of social change practitioners building an institution to support holistic movement building for justice, democracy, peace and ecological sanity. <br>\r\n* Committed to “building a culture of strategy” in grassroots social change movements. This includes a focus on developing training and strategy models using “narrative power analysis” and “story-based strategies” to challenge the underlying assumptions that perpetuate militarism, racism, injustice and ecological destruction. <br>\r\n* A fun crew who loves big ideas. <br>\r\n* A fresh, growing organization with lots of room to explore and experiment. <br><br>\r\n \r\nSmartMeme’s STORY program (Strategy, Training and Organizing Resources for Youth) strengthens youth movements and builds strategic capacities in youth networks. The program offers trainings, partnership projects, and movement building gatherings. We have partnered and trained with dozen of grassroots youth groups including: Student Farmworker Alliance, National Youth & Student Peace Coalition, Student Environmental Action Coalition, Boston Mobilization, and the Nuclear Age Peace Foundation. <br><br>\r\n \r\nJOB DESCRIPTION:<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe Organizer will--<br>\r\n* Work with the collective to implement the STORY program’s outreach and organizing efforts. <br>\r\n* Coordinate logistics and outreach for the 2006 STORY youth strategy retreat. <br>\r\n* Work to build the strategic and organizational capacity of grassroots youth groups through STORY’s partnership and training program.  <br>\r\n* Coordinate and shepherd the development of the STORY Board, volunteers and interns. <br>\r\n* Publicly represent the organization, the program, and its values. <br>\r\n* Travel to work with amazing youth activists on some of the most important issues of our times.  Applicants must have the ability to work while out of the office, travel by air extensively, and be away from home for up to 2 weeks at a time. <br><br>\r\n \r\nThe STORY Organizer will work in close collaboration with the smartMeme Core Collective as part of an extended collective model.<br> <br>\r\n \r\n<b>ROLLING DEADLINE: (February 15-March 15 or until position filled.) We anticipate filling the position as soon as possible so if you are interested please apply as soon as you can! </b><br><br>\r\n \r\nSend a Letter of Interest telling us “Your Story,” and why you would be a good fit with the smartMeme team. Please also attach a resume with references and send TO: <br>\r\n \r\nBY EMAIL: story@smartmeme.com <br>\r\nMAIL:  19 Church St Suite 10 Burlington Vermont 05401\r\n \r\nNo Phone Calls Please.   <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>2) JOB ANNOUNCEMENT: Development Associate </b><br><br>\r\n \r\nDeadline: Rolling Application Process Through March 15th but position will be filled as soon as possible <br><br>\r\n \r\nWe’re looking for a Development Associate to join a dynamic, collaborative movement building project focused on strategy, training, and communications! <br><br>\r\n \r\n9 month position (April 1 – Dec 31) with potential to grow into a permanent position. <br>\r\nStarting wage $12.75/hour, Part time (2-3 days a week) Flexible hours<br>\r\nBased in:  Burlington, VT <br><br>\r\n \r\nSmartMeme is an innovative and fast-paced non-profit organization, implementing dynamic programs with national reach in the fields of strategic communication and movement building. We are seeking the right individual who can work with us to develop and implement fundraising systems for our organization.  <br><br>\r\n \r\nWe are seeking a development associate to assist us in organizational development, day-to-day office management, and securing funding for our programs. Candidate must be a self-starter, well organized and highly motivated. Preferably you are experienced in grant writing, donor communications, and general office management. You must be a creative, confident, task-juggler! Experience in a social change organization is a big plus. <br><br>\r\n \r\nResponsibilities include grant solicitation, researching grant prospects, foundation and donor outreach, some grant writing, and general assistance to smartMeme’s development and fundraising efforts. Your tasks may also include developing our database, website administration and integration of an online fundraising program, development projects and events  (such as house parties and mailings), and general assistance to the core staff (scheduling, answering general enquiries, clerical support). Development Associate will work closely with the core collective. Part-time, flexible hours. Position will ideally grow over time. <br><br>\r\n \r\nCandidate must possess strong communication skills (written and interpersonal), have strong computer skills in MSWord and Excel (we run on Macintosh OSX) and must be able to work well with timelines and budget. Person must also share the core values of the organization and feel political affinity with our mission. <br><br>\r\n \r\nThe Development Associate will work in very close collaboration with the smartMeme core collective as part of an extended collective model. <br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Rolling Deadline (February 15-March 15 or until position is filled.) We anticipate filling the position as soon as possible, so if you are interested please apply as soon as you can! </b><br><br>\r\n \r\nSend a Letter of Interest telling us “Your Story,” and why you would be a good fit with the smartMeme team. Please also attach a resume with references and send TO: <br><br>\r\n \r\nBY EMAIL: story@smartmeme.com <br>\r\nMAIL:  19 Church St Suite 10 Burlington Vermont 05401 <br><br>\r\n \r\nNo Phone Calls Please. <br><br>\r\n \r\nSmartMeme is an equal opportunity employer committed to identifying and developing the skills and leadership of people from diverse backgrounds and challenging historic patterns of political marginalization and oppression. People of Color, working-class people, differently-abled people and LGBT persons are strongly encouraged to apply.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                <b> Download smartMeme HIGHLIGHTS 2005 by clicking on the PDF icon to your right! </b><br><br>','','2006-02-16 22:24:33',9,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',0,0,'smartMeme Highlights 05.pdf','pdf',0,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'incite table.jpg','Download smartMeme highlights \'05 by clicking on the PDF icon',1,'',0,0,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1221,211,'The STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq','An intimate 3-day retreat at the historic <a href=\"http://www.highlandercenter.org\">Highlander Center</a> in Tennessee focused on vision, strategy work, cross-cultural movement building and leadership development for young peace activists. ','For More on the STORY Collaborative... <h href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/story\"> visit smartmeme.com/story</a> <br><br><br>\r\n\r\n \r\n           <b> For our 2005 happenings...Download smartMeme HIGHLIGHTS 2005 by clicking on the PDF icon to your right! </b><br><br>','','2006-05-06 01:43:29',9,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',0,0,'smartMeme Highlights 05.pdf','pdf',0,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'incite table.jpg','Download smartMeme highlights \'05 by clicking on the PDF icon',1,'',0,0,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1222,218,'contact','Get in touch with STORY!','<html><head></head><body>By email: story (at) smartmeme.com<br /><br />Call toll free: 1-877-763-5437<br /><br />Write us at:<br />\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><i>smart</i>Meme<br />19 Church St. Suite 10<br />Burlington, VT 05401<br /></div></body></html>','','2006-05-06 01:35:32',76,1,1,'',0,'',1,'',0,0,'','',0,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'Speaker.jpg','Let\'s work together to end this war!',1,'',0,0,'','','right','graphic',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1223,214,'The STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq','An intimate 3-day retreat at the historic <a href=\"http://www.highlandercenter.org\">Highlander Center</a> in Tennessee focused on vision, strategy work, cross-cultural movement building and leadership development for young peace activists. ','<b>Download this appeal</b> by clicking on the PDF icon in the photo to your right ---> <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<b> Youth + Young Veterans Working for Peace |  <a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\"> Give </a> </b> <br><br>\r\n\r\nMay 5, 2006 <br><br>\r\n\r\nDear friends, allies and supporters, <br><br>\r\n\r\nLike so many people with a heart for peace and justice, you probably wake up almost every morning, and as the radio blares the latest from Baghdad, you ask yourself… “How are we going to end the war in Iraq?” <br><br>\r\n\r\nYou go through your days in the United States, to the snarling of Fox NewsHardball with Chris Matthews, wondering, “How are we going to unmake this mythology, this system, that thrives on racism, military machines and fear?” <br><br>\r\n\r\nAs you lay down to sleep, you have dreams of young Veterans returning home to their families for good…of schools that are abundant and overflowing with learning and creativity…of an Iraq that is a place of peace, freedom and self determination…and of an antiwar movement led by Vets and young people that could make this dream a reality. <br><br>\r\n\r\nYou know that what is happening in Iraq is unforgivable, egregious, maddening. You know that it will take a massive campaign of strategic, thoughtful action to end the war. You are, and can be a partner in that work. <br><br>\r\n\r\nYouth and young Iraq Vets are working together for peace. It is indeed an exciting and timely alliance that needs to be strengthened and supported. To this end, smartMeme’s youth program, STORY, is convening a gathering this summer at the historic Highlander Center in New Market, Tennessee to bring young Iraq Vets and youth anti-war leaders together to strategize about ending this war. This gathering is an essential next step in the process of building a strong, strategic anti-war movement, and we need you to <a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\"> join us with a gift of support. </a><br><br>\r\n \r\nThe idea for the STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq emerged during informal conversation with young peace movement leaders after the <a href=\"http://www.nyspc.net\"> National Youth and Student Peace Coalition (NYSPC)</a> meeting in New York in January, where STORY offered facilitation and strategy support. The project is led by STORY Board members as well as young organizers from NYSPC member groups including <a href =\"http://www.warresisters.org\">War Resisters League</a> , <a href =\"http://www.sfalliance.org\">Student Farmworker Alliance</a>, and <a href=\"http://www.ivaw.net\"> Iraq Veterans Against the War.</a> <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Our Vision</b><br><br>\r\n\r\nAn intimate 3-day retreat at the historic Highlander Center in Tennessee focused on vision, strategy work, cross-cultural movement building and leadership development for young peace activists. The Collaborative emphasizes deepening the alliance of Iraq Veterans Against the War and youth and student peace networks, particularly those working on counter recruitment in youth of color communities. At the gathering, we will apply some of smartMeme’s story-based strategy tools, and deepen relationships amongst young people working to end the war in communities across the country. We will gather to explore strategies that can harness the historic moment and help to build a strong, grassroots peace movement led by those most directly affected.<br><br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Our Goals</b><br><br>\r\n\r\n•	Build deep alliances between young Iraq Veterans and youth-based antiwar networks<br>\r\n•	Provide a space for building relationships across constituencies<br>\r\n•	Facilitate anti-war strategy development using story-based strategy models<br>\r\n•	Amplify the voices of youth and young veterans in the anti-war movement and build leadership capacity amongst these constituencies<br>\r\n•	Encourage the building of a long-term peace movement that can challenge the assumptions underlying racism, militarism and war.<br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Your Support</b><br><br>\r\n\r\nIf you want to offer solidarity and support to the youth and Veterans who are offering us new stories and new visions of what an antiwar movement in the US could look like, please make the most generous contribution you can. Your charitable gift can help to bring young Iraq Vets who are speaking out against the war, and young visionaries of the next generation of antiwar activism, together at Highlander to share stories and develop strategies to end the Iraq occupation and challenge US Empire. <br><br>\r\n\r\nNo one at the White House is going to end this war for us. It is up to us to dare to be more creative, strategic, and powerful! The STORY Collaborative will create a space for young leaders and young veterans to connect, find voice, and develop a collaborative vision. Be a part of this historic gathering and <a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\">chose to make a gift of solidarity today.</a><br>  <br>\r\n\r\nFor Peace, <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',69,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'Youth+VetsSTORYAppeal2006.pdf','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-