th testicular problems in rats and humans. The chemical is banned from use in cosmetics in Europe and is considered a reproductive toxin by California.\r\n<br><br>\r\nA study that examined nail polishes and perfumes, published in 2004 in The Journal of Toxicology and Environmental Health, concluded that the amount of exposure to dibutyl phthalate from these cosmetics is relatively small. The study cautioned, however, that total exposure to the chemical from multiple sources may be greater and requires further investigation.\r\n<br><br>\r\nCompanies are adjusting formulas even though beauty executives said the ingredient is safe in the concentrations in which it is used in cosmetics.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\"We are reacting here to changing consumer trends and a changing regulatory environment,\" said Bruce MacKay, the vice president for scientific affairs/R&D of Del Laboratories, the maker of Sally Hansen. \"In high concentrations in lab experiments, these materials may be of concern, but there is no body of evidence that says this particular ingredient is not safe in the concentration in which it is used in nail products.\"\r\n<br><br>\r\nBut health groups like the Breast Cancer Fund, an advocacy group in San Francisco that focuses on the environment, said that phthalates are too risky to use in consumer products.\r\n<br><br>\r\n \"If there is evidence that an ingredient causes or is suspected of causing cancer or birth defects, cosmetics companies should not be using it in their products,\" said Kevin Donegan, the group\'s director of communications. \"Phthalates have clearly been demonstrated to cause harm.\"\r\n<br><br>\r\n<br>\r\n ','','2006-09-20 19:36:51',9,1,1,'whatsnew',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'incite table.jpg','Download smartMeme highlights \'05 by clicking on the PDF icon',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1245,211,'smartMeme Fall 2006!','Victory for Safe Cosmetics Campaign\r\nSTORY in Immokalee\r\nsmartMeme @ Bioneers\r\nand more!','<b>September 21-24 @ Immokalee, Florida <br><br>\r\nSTORY at <a href=\"http://www.sfalliance.org\">Student Farmworker Alliance Youth Encuentro 2006\r\n</a></b>\r\n<br><br><br>\r\nThis weekend, dozens of young organizers and activists from across the country will gather in Immokalee, Florida for three days of strategizing about the struggle for fair food, farmworker rights and building a more just world. Standing in solidarity with the Coalition of Immokalee Workers, the SFA is taking their campaign for human rights to McDonald\'s and the rest of the fast-food industry!\r\n<br><br>\r\nTrainers from smartMeme’s  STORY program will be onsite strategizing with SFA to analyze the McDonald\'s \"story\" and train SFA activists in story-based strategy. We will also be sharing lessons and alliance building strategies from the STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq -- of which SFA is a key partner!  Human Rights....I\'m Lovin It!\r\n<br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>October 18-21\r\nCatch smartMeme at<a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org\"> Bioneers 2006\r\n</a> -- for a special pre-conference youth intensive, or at our Saturday workshop!\r\n<br><br></b>\r\nOctober 19 @ Marin, California -- Bioneers Youth Intensive\r\nWHICH STORY? WHICH FUTURE?\r\nVision and Strategy for the Next Generation\r\nFor Young Activists (18 to 30 year-olds)\r\n<br><br>\r\nOctober 21 @ Marin, California -- Bioneers Conference Workshop\r\nCHANGE THE STORY:\r\nNew Strategies for Shifting Culture\r\nFor Bioneers conference goers!\r\n<br><br>\r\nTO REGISTER <a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org/conference\">CLICK HERE\r\n</a> \r\n<br><br><br>\r\n<b>VICTORY! <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org\">Safe Cosmetics Campaign </a> wins on OPI -- New York TImes Story!</b>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nFor over two years now smartMeme has collaborated with the Campaign for Safe Cosmetics -- an innovative coalition of women\'s, public health and environmental justice groups who are working to get toxic chemicals out of personal care products. We have provided facilitation, strategy consultation and designed several full page ads for the campaign.  \r\n<br><br>\r\nSmartMeme\'s latest ad targeted OPI for their use of dangerous chemicals. See ad <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org/docUploads/Miss%20Treatment%20OPI%5F2006%5F8%2E5x11%2Epdf\">HERE! </a>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nResponding to the Safe Cosmetics Campaign  pressure, OPI has agreed to remove the dangerous chemical -- dibutyl pthalate from their nail polish!!! OPI is the latest in an industry wide shift away from toxics due in great part to the savvy work of our friends at SafeCo!\r\n<br><br>\r\nThis is another victory for the campaign and one more step towards a cancer-free economy!\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Nail Polish Makers Yield on Disputed Chemical\r\nThe New York Times</b>\r\nSeptember 7, 2006\r\n<br><br>\r\n By NATASHA SINGER\r\n<br><br>\r\nBOWING to pressure from environmental groups and European lawmakers,several cosmetics makers are removing a chemical from nail polish that is suspected of interfering with the endocrine system.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOrly International and OPI Products have already started selling reformulated nail polishes without the chemical, dibutyl phthalate. Sally Hansen plans to start selling similarly reformulated products in 2007.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSome studies have linked exposure to dibutyl phthalate - a plasticizing ingredient that has been used to increase flexibility in nail polishes as well as medical equipment - with testicular problems in rats and humans. The chemical is banned from use in cosmetics in Europe and is considered a reproductive toxin by California.\r\n<br><br>\r\nA study that examined nail polishes and perfumes, published in 2004 in The Journal of Toxicology and Environmental Health, concluded that the amount of exposure to dibutyl phthalate from these cosmetics is relatively small. The study cautioned, however, that total exposure to the chemical from multiple sources may be greater and requires further investigation.\r\n<br><br>\r\nCompanies are adjusting formulas even though beauty executives said the ingredient is safe in the concentrations in which it is used in cosmetics.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\"We are reacting here to changing consumer trends and a changing regulatory environment,\" said Bruce MacKay, the vice president for scientific affairs/R&D of Del Laboratories, the maker of Sally Hansen. \"In high concentrations in lab experiments, these materials may be of concern, but there is no body of evidence that says this particular ingredient is not safe in the concentration in which it is used in nail products.\"\r\n<br><br>\r\nBut health groups like the Breast Cancer Fund, an advocacy group in San Francisco that focuses on the environment, said that phthalates are too risky to use in consumer products.\r\n<br><br>\r\n \"If there is evidence that an ingredient causes or is suspected of causing cancer or birth defects, cosmetics companies should not be using it in their products,\" said Kevin Donegan, the group\'s director of communications. \"Phthalates have clearly been demonstrated to cause harm.\"\r\n<br><br>\r\n<br>\r\n ','','2006-09-20 19:50:05',9,1,1,'whatsnew',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'bioneers-logo-final.jpg','Catch smartMeme @ the 2006 Bioneers Conference in Marin, CA October 19-22: Register <a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org/conference\"> here! </a>',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1246,103,'what\'s new','The latest stories, features, announcements, news, and updates from <i>smart</i>Meme.','<P align=left><B>Welcome to <I>smart</I>Meme\'s new website! </B><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe\'ve expanded our previous website in order to provide you with a <A href=\"/article.php?list=type&type=5\">portfolio</A> of our work, a better understanding of <A href=\"/article.php?list=type&type=3\">who we are</A>, and a run down of <A href=\"/article.php?list=type&type=4\">what we do</A>! In addition we will soon offer a number of downloadable strategic communications tools, essays, suggested readings, and more in the strategic resources section of this site. <BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions about <I>smart</I>Meme, about how to hire us for our communications and design services, or about our newest program <A href=\"/article.php?list=type&type=50\">STORY (Strategy, Training & Organizing Resources for Youth)</A> please <A href=\"/contactus.php\">contact us</A>. We\'re excited that you\'re here and invite you to get in touch with us!</P>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',9,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'CIW1.jpg','Join <i>smart</i>Meme for trainings and more at the first ever national <A HREF= \"http://smartmeme.radicaldesigns.org/article.php?id=197\">Student/Farmworker Alliance SUMMER ENCUENTRO</A>  in Immokalee, FL, August 1-7. Register Soon!',1,'',0,1,'','','left','',NULL,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1247,192,'Internships Available for 2006!','The <i>smart</i>Meme Strategy & Training Project, a national organization dedicated to radical, grassroots social change work, is looking for interns....like you! We are accepting applications for Spring, Summer and Fall of 2006. Deadlines are March 1, May 1, and September 1.','<i>Smart</i>Meme is a collective founded in 2003 dedicated to amplifying the voices of peace, justice, democracy, and ecological sanity. <i>Smart</i>Meme supports movements with strategic social change communications, working with grassroots groups and campaigning organizations from coast to coast.\r\n\r\nInternships are now available to enable activists to plug into <i>smart</i>Meme\'s new youth-focused training initiative: <A HREF=\"article.php?list=type&type=50\">STORY (Strategy, Training, and Organizing Resources for Youth)</A>.\r\n\r\nThis internship is a unique opportunity that is designed to help develop the skills of participants as grassroots organizers, trainers, communicators, and effective change agents.\r\n\r\n<b>You are a great candidate if you:</b>\r\n\r\n--Have a passion for social change work\r\n--Hold a strong commitment to strategic anti-war, social justice, and ecological activism\r\n--Have some experience working with a youth/student activist organization\r\n--Are looking to build your skills, networks, and experiences as a social change practitioner...\r\n\r\n<b>Responsibilities of interns may include:</b>\r\n\r\n--Research (opposition research, media climate assessment, etc)\r\n--Media Work (media list building, collaboration on media releases and statements)\r\n--Outreach & Promotion (tabling, mailings, etc)\r\n--Organizing and Logistics (for smartMeme trainings and other STORY events)\r\n--Development Work (the hands on work of building this exciting new organization!)\r\n\r\nAll Spring internships require working at <i>smart</i>Meme\'s office in beautiful BURLINGTON, VERMONT for a minimum of 14 hours per week for a period of three months. <br><br>\r\n\r\nSummer internships are in the works for  SAN FRANCISCO, CA and SKOKOMISH NATION, WA. <br>\r\n\r\nInterns work with an experienced staff member who designs and oversees the completion of a special project. Interns participate in the day-to-day operations of the STORY program as well. Some travel may be required to STORY related trainings and events.\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme  will cover commuting and travel expenses into the field required by the position (interns may travel to trainings and events throughout the summer). \r\n\r\nA small housing stipend is available to the right candidate who can put in 20+ hours/week. \r\n\r\nAt the completion of the internship, each intern is given a chance to evaluate their internship, a letter of reference, and the waiver of fees to <i>smart</i>Meme\'s autumn STORY gathering...and some cool <i>smart</i>Meme gear!\r\n\r\n<b>IF YOU ARE INTERESTED, PLEASE SEND A RESUME AND COVER LETTER OF INTEREST (YOUR STORY!) TO:</b>\r\n\r\n<b><i>STORY@SMARTMEME.COM</i></b>\r\n\r\nOR\r\n\r\n<b><i>smart</i>Meme\r\n19 Church St, Suite 10\r\nBurlington, Vermont 05401</b>\r\n\r\nNo Phone Calls Please.\r\n\r\nThe <i>smart</i>Meme collective is committed to challenging historic patterns of oppression and political marginalization.  Young activists from working class backgrounds, LBGTQ people, womyn, and youth of color are particularly encouraged to apply. \r\n\r\n<i>** A housing stipend is available to the right candidate who can put in 20+ hours/week. Please tell us in your cover letter how much money per month you would require as a stipend in order to do this internship. **</i>','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',65,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-04-05',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1248,104,'what we do','<i>Smart</i>Meme builds movements and amplifies the impact of grassroots organizing with new strategy and training resources, values based communication tools and meme campaigning.  ','<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\">\r\n\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme is a one-stop-shop for strategic consultation, messaging, and design. We help grassroots groups magnify their impact by linking traditional organizing and movement building skills with values based messaging, narrative concepts and creative action. We provide direct support either through sliding scale, fee-for-service work or through our STORY youth training program.  <i>Smart</i>Meme also collaborates with our allies to concept and implement meme campaigns that promote new ideas and creative actions.','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',4,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1249,104,'what we do','Our Mission: <br> <i>smart</i>Meme builds movements and amplifies the impact of grassroots organizing with new strategy and training resources, values based communications, collaborations, and meme campaigning. SmartMeme uses the power of narrative to advance a holistic vision of grassroots social change that connects struggles for democracy, peace, justice, and ecological sanity. ','<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\">\r\nWe call what we do <b> \"story based strategy\" .... </b>\r\n<br><br>\r\nSmartMeme is about doing social change in a holistic way – shifting from issues to values, supplementing organization building with movement building, focusing on the intersections of story telling, relational organizing, communications, alliance building and creative new forms of civic engagement and action. \r\n<br><br>\r\nSmartMeme amplifies the impact of local and national non-profit and grassroots organizations with capacity-building partnerships, collaborations, and new strategy tools to change the stories that shape the dominant culture. We integrate the art of framing, the science of strategy, and the approach of grassroots organizing through our framework of “story-based strategy.” \r\n<br><br>\r\nStory-based strategy links traditional organizing and movement building work with new strategy, training, and communications methods to give social change workers the tools to hone their story, challenge prevailing cultural narratives, and ultimately win campaigns on the issues. As a movement support and training organization, smartMeme partners with social change organizations to offer strategic consultation and facilitation, messaging and branding, graphic design, advertising, and training. \r\n<br><br>\r\nSmartMeme has helped win victories for the <a href=\"http://www.preventharm.org\">Environmental Health Strategy Center </a> (Chemical Policy Reform),<a href=\"http://www.ruralvermont.org\"> Rural Vermont </a> (Genetic Engineering), <a href=\"http://klamathrestoration.org/wp/bring-the-salmon-home-un-dam-the-klamath/\">the Klamath Tribes</a> (River Restoration), and <a href= \"http://www.notwithourmoney.org/01_home/dumpfarallon.html\"<a>Not With Our Money! </a>(Prison Privatization). SmartMeme has strengthened the work of over <b>40 organizations across the country, and trained over 1,500 activists since 2002</b>. \r\n<br><br>\r\nSmartMeme consutling offers your organization strategy, communiations and design services with a story-based approach and an eye for building movement. Contact us for more information at: partners@smartmeme.com','','2006-09-21 00:46:31',4,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0,0,0,'','',0,'',0,1,'','','','',0,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1250,104,'what we do','<i>smart</i>Meme\'s mission is to build movements and amplify the impact of grassroots organizing with new strategy and training resources, values based communications, collaborations, and meme campaigning. <i>smart</i>Meme uses the power of narrative to advance a holistic vision of grassroots social change that connects struggles for democracy, peace, justice, and ecological sanity. ','<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\">\r\nWe call what we do <b> \"story based strategy\" .... </b>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme is about doing social change in a holistic way – shifting from issues to values, supplementing organization building with movement building, focusing on the intersections of story telling, relational organizing, communications, alliance building and creative new forms of civic engagement and action. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<i>Smart</i>Meme amplifies the impact of local and national non-profit and grassroots organizations with capacity-building partnerships, collaborations, and new strategy tools to change the stories that shape the dominant culture. We integrate the art of framing,