d><body><p align=\"left\"><i>Smart</i>Meme’s high caliber team of social change practitioners has brought tools from the worlds of grassroots organizing, advertising, marketing, public relations, scientific inquiry, education and advocacy campaigning to create a unique range of strategic services.  \r\n<br /><br />\r\nWe provide strategy consultation, design and communications services to grassroots social change organizations and other non-profits on a sliding scale fee-for-service basis.  \r\n<br /><br />\r\nTo explore hiring <i>smart</i>Meme please contact <i>partners@smartmeme.com</i> or call one of our offices to request an estimate. \r\n<br />','','2006-07-19 21:23:23',36,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',NULL,'',0,1,'','','','',NULL,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1254,107,'menu of services','<i>Smart</i>Meme is a comprehensive source for strategic communications, facilitation, and design. <i>Smart</i>Meme provides a wide range of advocacy communications and movement support services on a fee-for-service basis.','<html><head></head><body><p align=\"left\"><i>Smart</i>Meme is a national strategy center for holistic movement building founded in 2002. We develop and apply narrative power analysis and story-based strategies—frameworks to integrate organizing, messaging, and strategy through the power of storytelling. We bring combined decades of experience in grassroots movements, as well as training in the fields of advertising, advocacy, organizing, film & broadcast media, ecology, and education. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<i>Smart<i/>Meme serves national and grassroots organizations as a comprehensive source for movement based strategy consultation, messaging, meeting planning and facilitation, communications, and design. \r\n<br><br>\r\nOur firm grounding in grassroots social change work enables smartMeme to connect messaging, advertising and branding with a campaigns’ overall organizing strategy. We are not another PR firm – we are a strategy team that will work in collaboration with organizations who share our mission in order to change the stories that are eroding our collective future. \r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Consulting Program offers our partners the following services, all with the approach of story-based strategy:\r\n<br><br>\r\n?	Messaging\r\n<br>\r\n               Production of messaging strategy documents, talking points, branding and brand planning\r\n<br><br>\r\n?	Training\r\n<br>\r\n               Custom training in story-based strategies for client organizations\r\n<br><br>\r\n?	Strategy\r\n<br> \r\n               Opposition research, positioning, campaign strategy development and planning, long-range scenario development\r\n<br><br>\r\n?	Design\r\n<br>\r\n               Graphic design projects including mailers, stickers, logos, web graphics, etc.\r\n<br><br>\r\n?	Advertising\r\n<br>\r\n              Concepting, production, and placement of ads for print, radio, TV, web (and other creative venues!)\r\n<br><br>\r\n?	Facilitation \r\n<br>\r\n              Agenda design, meeting planning consultation, strategy session facilitation for organizations and coalitions\r\n<br /><br />\r\nTo explore hiring <i>smart</i>Meme please contact <a href=\"mailto:james@smartmeme.com\"> partners@smartmeme.com</a> or call 360-898-0041 to chat about what we could do with your organization! \r\n<br />','','2006-09-21 01:40:41',36,0,1,'menu',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'EHSC-blocksFINAL-Bangor-sm.jpg','A full page Ad developed for the Environmental Health Strategy Center in Maine in 2005.',0,'',0,1,'','','','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1255,211,'smartMeme Fall 2006','Victory for Safe Cosmetics Campaign!\r\nSTORY in Immokalee...\r\nsmartMeme @ Bioneers...\r\nand more!','<b>September 21-24 @ Immokalee, Florida <br><br>\r\nSTORY at <a href=\"http://www.sfalliance.org\">Student Farmworker Alliance Youth Encuentro 2006\r\n</a></b>\r\n<br><br><br>\r\nThis weekend, dozens of young organizers and activists from across the country will gather in Immokalee, Florida for three days of strategizing about the struggle for fair food, farmworker rights and building a more just world. Standing in solidarity with the Coalition of Immokalee Workers, the SFA is taking their campaign for human rights to McDonald\'s and the rest of the fast-food industry!\r\n<br><br>\r\nTrainers from smartMeme’s  STORY program will be onsite strategizing with SFA to analyze the McDonald\'s \"story\" and train SFA activists in story-based strategy. We will also be sharing lessons and alliance building strategies from the STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq -- of which SFA is a key partner!  Human Rights....I\'m Lovin It!\r\n<br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>October 18-21\r\nCatch smartMeme at<a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org\"> Bioneers 2006\r\n</a> -- for a special pre-conference youth intensive, or at our Saturday workshop!\r\n<br><br></b>\r\nOctober 19 @ Marin, California -- Bioneers Youth Intensive\r\nWHICH STORY? WHICH FUTURE?\r\nVision and Strategy for the Next Generation\r\nFor Young Activists (18 to 30 year-olds)\r\n<br><br>\r\nOctober 21 @ Marin, California -- Bioneers Conference Workshop\r\nCHANGE THE STORY:\r\nNew Strategies for Shifting Culture\r\nFor Bioneers conference goers!\r\n<br><br>\r\nTO REGISTER <a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org/conference\">CLICK HERE\r\n</a> \r\n<br><br><br>\r\n<b>VICTORY! <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org\">Safe Cosmetics Campaign </a> wins on OPI -- New York TImes Story!</b>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nFor over two years now smartMeme has collaborated with the Campaign for Safe Cosmetics -- an innovative coalition of women\'s, public health and environmental justice groups who are working to get toxic chemicals out of personal care products. We have provided facilitation, strategy consultation and designed several full page ads for the campaign.  \r\n<br><br>\r\nSmartMeme\'s latest ad targeted OPI for their use of dangerous chemicals. See ad <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org/docUploads/Miss%20Treatment%20OPI%5F2006%5F8%2E5x11%2Epdf\">HERE! </a>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nResponding to the Safe Cosmetics Campaign  pressure, OPI has agreed to remove the dangerous chemical -- dibutyl pthalate from their nail polish!!! OPI is the latest in an industry wide shift away from toxics due in great part to the savvy work of our friends at SafeCo!\r\n<br><br>\r\nThis is another victory for the campaign and one more step towards a cancer-free economy!\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Nail Polish Makers Yield on Disputed Chemical\r\nThe New York Times</b>\r\nSeptember 7, 2006\r\n<br><br>\r\n By NATASHA SINGER\r\n<br><br>\r\nBOWING to pressure from environmental groups and European lawmakers,several cosmetics makers are removing a chemical from nail polish that is suspected of interfering with the endocrine system.\r\n<br><br>\r\nOrly International and OPI Products have already started selling reformulated nail polishes without the chemical, dibutyl phthalate. Sally Hansen plans to start selling similarly reformulated products in 2007.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSome studies have linked exposure to dibutyl phthalate - a plasticizing ingredient that has been used to increase flexibility in nail polishes as well as medical equipment - with testicular problems in rats and humans. The chemical is banned from use in cosmetics in Europe and is considered a reproductive toxin by California.\r\n<br><br>\r\nA study that examined nail polishes and perfumes, published in 2004 in The Journal of Toxicology and Environmental Health, concluded that the amount of exposure to dibutyl phthalate from these cosmetics is relatively small. The study cautioned, however, that total exposure to the chemical from multiple sources may be greater and requires further investigation.\r\n<br><br>\r\nCompanies are adjusting formulas even though beauty executives said the ingredient is safe in the concentrations in which it is used in cosmetics.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\"We are reacting here to changing consumer trends and a changing regulatory environment,\" said Bruce MacKay, the vice president for scientific affairs/R&D of Del Laboratories, the maker of Sally Hansen. \"In high concentrations in lab experiments, these materials may be of concern, but there is no body of evidence that says this particular ingredient is not safe in the concentration in which it is used in nail products.\"\r\n<br><br>\r\nBut health groups like the Breast Cancer Fund, an advocacy group in San Francisco that focuses on the environment, said that phthalates are too risky to use in consumer products.\r\n<br><br>\r\n \"If there is evidence that an ingredient causes or is suspected of causing cancer or birth defects, cosmetics companies should not be using it in their products,\" said Kevin Donegan, the group\'s director of communications. \"Phthalates have clearly been demonstrated to cause harm.\"\r\n<br><br>\r\n<br>\r\n ','','2006-09-20 19:51:28',9,1,1,'whatsnew',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'bioneers-logo-final.jpg','Catch smartMeme @ the 2006 Bioneers Conference in Marin, CA October 19-22: Register <a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org/conference\"> here! </a>',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1256,211,'smartMeme Fall 2006','Victory for Safe Cosmetics Campaign!\r\nSTORY in Immokalee...\r\nsmartMeme @ Bioneers...\r\nand more!','\r\n<strong>September 21-24 @ Immokalee, Florida <br /><br />\r\nSTORY at <a href=\"http://www.sfalliance.org\">Student Farmworker Alliance Youth Encuentro 2006\r\n</a></strong>\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThis weekend, dozens of young organizers and activists from across the country will gather in Immokalee, Florida for three days of strategizing about the struggle for fair food, farmworker rights and building a more just world. Standing in solidarity with the Coalition of Immokalee Workers, the SFA is taking their campaign for human rights to McDonald\'s and the rest of the fast-food industry!\r\n<br /><br />\r\nTrainers from smartMeme’s  STORY program will be onsite strategizing with SFA to analyze the McDonald\'s &quot;story&quot; and train SFA activists in story-based strategy. We will also be sharing lessons and alliance building strategies from the STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq -- of which SFA is a key partner!  Human Rights....I\'m Lovin It!\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<strong>October 18-21\r\nCatch smartMeme at<a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org\"> Bioneers 2006\r\n</a> -- for a special pre-conference youth intensive, or at our Saturday workshop!\r\n<br /><br /></strong>\r\nOctober 19 @ Marin, California -- Bioneers Youth Intensive\r\nWHICH STORY? WHICH FUTURE?\r\nVision and Strategy for the Next Generation\r\nFor Young Activists (18 to 30 year-olds)\r\n-- <strong>including a special evening on the &quot;space bridge&quot; with the Council of Indigenous Grandmothers LIVE from Darmasala India!</strong><br /><br />\r\nOctober 21 @ Marin, California -- Bioneers Conference Workshop\r\nCHANGE THE STORY:\r\nNew Strategies for Shifting Culture\r\nFor Bioneers conference goers!\r\n<br /><br />\r\nTO REGISTER <a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org/conference\">CLICK HERE\r\n</a> \r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\n<strong>VICTORY! <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org\">Safe Cosmetics Campaign </a> wins on OPI -- New York TImes Story!</strong>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n\r\nFor over two years now smartMeme has collaborated with the Campaign for Safe Cosmetics -- an innovative coalition of women\'s, public health and environmental justice groups who are working to get toxic chemicals out of personal care products. We have provided facilitation, strategy consultation and designed several full page ads for the campaign.  \r\n<br /><br />\r\nSmartMeme\'s latest ad targeted OPI for their use of dangerous chemicals. See ad <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org/docUploads/Miss%20Treatment%20OPI%5F2006%5F8%2E5x11%2Epdf\">HERE! </a>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n\r\nResponding to the Safe Cosmetics Campaign  pressure, OPI has agreed to remove the dangerous chemical -- dibutyl pthalate from their nail polish!!! OPI is the latest in an industry wide shift away from toxics due in great part to the savvy work of our friends at SafeCo!\r\n<br /><br />\r\nThis is another victory for the campaign and one more step towards a cancer-free economy!\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Nail Polish Makers Yield on Disputed Chemical\r\nThe New York Times</strong>\r\nSeptember 7, 2006\r\n<br /><br />\r\n By NATASHA SINGER\r\n<br /><br />\r\nBOWING to pressure from environmental groups and European lawmakers,several cosmetics makers are removing a chemical from nail polish that is suspected of interfering with the endocrine system.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nOrly International and OPI Products have already started selling reformulated nail polishes without the chemical, dibutyl phthalate. Sally Hansen plans to start selling similarly reformulated products in 2007.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nSome studies have linked exposure to dibutyl phthalate - a plasticizing ingredient that has been used to increase flexibility in nail polishes as well as medical equipment - with testicular problems in rats and humans. The chemical is banned from use in cosmetics in Europe and is considered a reproductive toxin by California.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nA study that examined nail polishes and perfumes, published in 2004 in The Journal of Toxicology and Environmental Health, concluded that the amount of exposure to dibutyl phthalate from these cosmetics is relatively small. The study cautioned, however, that total exposure to the chemical from multiple sources may be greater and requires further investigation.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nCompanies are adjusting formulas even though beauty executives said the ingredient is safe in the concentrations in which it is used in cosmetics.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n&quot;We are reacting here to changing consumer trends and a changing regulatory environment,&quot; said Bruce MacKay, the vice president for scientific affairs/R&amp;D of Del Laboratories, the maker of Sally Hansen. &quot;In high concentrations in lab experiments, these materials may be of concern, but there is no body of evidence that says this particular ingredient is not safe in the concentration in which it is used in nail products.&quot;\r\n<br /><br />\r\nBut health groups like the Breast Cancer Fund, an advocacy group in San Francisco that focuses on the environment, said that phthalates are too risky to use in consumer products.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n &quot;If there is evidence that an ingredient causes or is suspected of causing cancer or birth defects, cosmetics companies should not be using it in their products,&quot; said Kevin Donegan, the group\'s director of communications. &quot;Phthalates have clearly been demonstrated to cause harm.&quot;\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n ','','2006-09-29 21:12:17',9,1,1,'whatsnew',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'grandmothers_1.jpg','Catch smartMeme @ the 2006 Bioneers Conference in Marin, CA October 19-22: Register <a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org/conference\"> here! </a>',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','',NULL,NULL),(1257,214,'The STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq','Read the Findings of our latest project: A 3 day Collaborative at the historic <a href=\"http://www.highlandercenter.org\">Highlander Center</a> in Tennessee focused on vision, strategy work, cross-cultural movement building and leadership development for young peace activists. DOWNLOAD the PDF by clicking on the icon to your right.','<p>\r\n<strong>Download the Findings of the STORY Collaborative,&nbsp; <em>We Are the Ones We\'ve Been Waiting For</em></strong> by clicking on the PDF icon to your right ---&gt; <br /><br />\r\n\r\nVISIT THE IRAQ COLLAB WEBSITE: <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org/iraq\"> changing the story dot org / iraq </a>  <br />\r\n\r\n<object width=\"425\" height=\"350\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/YTLwtVuqS0I\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/YTLwtVuqS0I\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"600\" height=\"350\"></embed></object>\r\n<br/>\r\nYouth + Veterans Working for Peace |  <a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\"> Give </a> </strong> <br /><br />\r\n\r\nDear friends, allies and supporters, <br /></p><p>Youth and young Iraq Vets are working together for peace. It is indeed an exciting and timely alliance that needs to be strengthened and supported. To this end, <em>smart</em>Meme’s youth program, STORY, convened a gathering this summer at the historic Highlander Center in New Market, Tennessee to bring young Iraq Vets and youth anti-war leaders together to strategize about ending this war. This gathering is an essential next step in the process of building a strong, strategic anti-war movement, and we need you to <a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\"> join us with a gift of support. </a><br /><br />\r\n \r\nThe idea for the STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq emerged during informal conversation with young peace movement leaders after the <a href=\"http://www.nyspc.net\"> National Youth and Student Peace Coalition (NYSPC)</a> meeting in New York in January, where STORY offered facilitation and strategy support. The project is led by STORY Board members as well as young organizers from NYSPC member groups including <a href=\"http://www.warresisters.org\">War Resisters League</a> , <a href=\"http://www.sfalliance.org\">Student Farmworker Alliance</a>, and <a href=\"http://www.ivaw.net\"> Iraq Veterans Against the War.</a> <br /><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<strong>Your Support</strong><br /><br />\r\n\r\nIf you want to offer solidarity and support to the youth and Veterans who are offering us new stories and new visions of what an antiwar movement in the US could look like, please make the most generous contribution you can. Your charitable gift can help to bring young Iraq Vets who are speaking out against the war, and young visionaries of the next generation of antiwar activism, together at Highlander to share stories and develop strategies to end the Iraq occupation and challenge US Empire. <br /><br />\r\n\r\nNo one is going to end this war for us. It is up to us to dare to be more creative, strategic, and powerful! The STORY Collaborative will create a space for young leaders and young veterans to connect, find voice, and develop a collaborative vision. Be a part of this historic gathering and <a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\">chose to make a gift of solidarity today.</a><br />  <br />\r\n\r\nFor Peace, <br /><br />\r\n\r\n\r\nThe STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq</p>','','2006-08-11 18:45:21',69,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'STORYCollaborativeFindings.pdf','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'','',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','antiwar movement iraq veterans against the war IVAW youth peace'),(1258,214,'STORY ','Strategy, Training & Organizing Resources for Youth','\r\n<p> VISIT THE STORY PROGRAM WEBSITE: <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org/iraq\"> changing the story dot org</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','2006-10-11 18:42:58',69,1,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'Fall06STORYappealFINAL.pdf','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-25',1,0,0,0,'incitegroupondeck.jpg','in 2005 STORY convened the first national conference on story-based strategies, incite/insight,a youth leadership retreat. <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org\">Visit the STORY website...</a>',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','','antiwar movement iraq veterans against the war IVAW youth peace'),(1259,214,'STORY : Strategy, Training & Organizing Resources 4 Youth','Strategy | Leadership | Training\r\n\r\n         Movement Building','\r\n<p><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">In 2004 smartMeme launched a leading-edge youth training and movement-building program called STORY (Strategy Training and Organizing Resources for Youth). This innovative leadership program provides young activists with training, strategy support, and a peer network to apply story-based strategies. STORY activists share sophisticated media literacy skills and apply narrative analysis to campaigning for social change in the arenas of peace, global economic justice, and environmental protection. <br /><br />Since it’s founding in 2004, the STORY program has:<br /><br /></font></p><ul><li><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Developed and refined the core story-based strategy curriculum</font></li><li><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Founded the <strong>STORY Board</strong>, a multi-cultural young-women-led advisory board and leadership team of 15 members</font></li><li><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Trained over 1,000 young activists in 20 states <br /></font></li><li><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Partnered with 15 youth-based organizations, and built communications and strategy capacity for youth networks addressing issues of:</font></li></ul><ul><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.nyspc.org\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Peace: The war in Iraq/US militarism</font></a></li></ul><ul><li><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org/youth\" target=\"_blank\">Ecology &amp; Environment&nbsp;</a></font></li></ul><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.usft.org\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">US trade policy</font></a></li></ul><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.sfalliance.org\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Farmworker justice and Fair Food<br /></font></a></li></ul><ul><li><a href=\"http:www.nwom.net\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Prison privatization</font></a></li></ul><ul><li><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><a href=\"http://www.energyaction.net\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"EnAct\">Global&nbsp; warming</a> <br /></font></li></ul><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.livingwageaction.org\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Living wages</font></a></li></ul><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.duhc.org\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Corporate power &amp; democracy</font></a></li></ul><ul><li><a href=\"http://wagingpeace.org/youth/\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Nuclear disarmament</font></a></li></ul><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.immigrantsolidarity.org/\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Immigrant rights</font></a>&nbsp;</li></ul><ul><li><a href=\"http://studentsagainstsweatshops.org/\"><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Sweatshops</font></a><br /></li></ul><p><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>And so much more...&nbsp;</strong></font></p><li><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">In 2005, STORY convened the first national conference on narrative social change strategy incite/insight: storytelling, movement building, and creating a culture of strategy, a youth leadership retreat</font></li><li><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">In 2006, we Convened the <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org/iraq\" target=\"_blank\">STORY Collaborative to End the War</a>, a national youth leadership strategy retreat at the <a href=\"http://www.highlandercenter.org\" target=\"_blank\">Highlander Center</a></font></li></ul><p><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Download our latest letter on STORY <a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/Fall06STORYappealFINAL.pdf\">here</a></font><br /><font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,h