rong>&nbsp;</strong><br />This essay is a case study done by Ilyse Hogue and Patrick Reinsborough of the November 2003 mobilization against the Free Trade Area of the Americas in Miami. The article, based on <em>smart</em>Memeï¿½s work supporting the mobilization,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>documents the use of military-style information warfare tactics against non-violent protest movements. </font></p></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"><br /><a title=\"Winning the BOS\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/Battle%20of%20the%20Story-SPIN.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Winning the</strong> <strong>Battle of the Story</strong></a> <br />Winning the Battle of the Story by Ilyse Hogue and Patrick Reinsborough explains how compelling stories and infectious memes can be used to amplify grassroots efforts to build a more democratic, just, and ecologically sane society.</font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"><br /><a title=\"Turn Your Back on Bush\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/TYBOB_Znet.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Turn Your Back on Bush</strong><br /></a>This essay by Doyle Canning explains how the<strong>&nbsp;</strong>campaign used memes to challenge assumptions about power and also describes how through direct action, activists can build solidarity through sharing their stories and strategies. </font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font></div>\r\n<div><font size=\"2\"><br /><a title=\"De-Colonizing\" href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/De-colonizingImagination.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>De-Colonizing the Revolutionary Imagination</strong></a><strong> <br /></strong>This ten part essay by Patrick Reinsborough explores a wide range of innovative social change strategies and ideas including post-issue activism, direct action at the point of assumption and the politics of reality. </font></div></div>','','2006-11-28 15:52:34',67,0,1,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,2,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-07-26',1,0,0,0,'Speaker.jpg','The Battle for the Story: A news conference in front of Halliburton HQ on the eve of the 2005 share holders meeting. STORY worked with Houston Global Awareness to amplify their \"Blow the Whistle on Halliburton\" campaign. ',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'pic','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','',''),(1269,211,'smartMeme Fall 2006','Victory for Safe Cosmetics Campaign!\r\nSTORY in Immokalee...\r\nsmartMeme @ Bioneers...\r\n','<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Download our latest <a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/dowloads/Fall06STORYappealFINAL.pdf\">STORY Letter</a> !</font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>September 21-24 @ Immokalee, Florida <br /><br />\r\nSTORY at <a href=\"http://www.sfalliance.org\">Student Farmworker Alliance Youth Encuentro 2006\r\n</a></strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/Fall06STORYappealFINAL.pdf\"><br /></a><br />\r\nDozens of young organizers and activists from across the country gathered in Immokalee, Florida for three days of strategizing about the struggle for fair food, farmworker rights and building a more just world. Standing in solidarity with the Coalition of Immokalee Workers, the SFA is taking their campaign for human rights to McDonald\'s and the rest of the fast-food industry!\r\n<br /><br />\r\nTrainers from smartMeme’s  STORY program went down to Florida to strategize with SFA to analyze the McDonald\'s &quot;story,&quot; and train SFA activists in story-based strategy. We&nbsp; also shared lessons and alliance building strategies from the STORY Collaborative to End the War in Iraq -- of which SFA is a key partner!  Human Rights....I\'m Lovin It!\r\n<br /><br /><strong>October 18-21\r\nCatch smartMeme at<a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org\"> Bioneers 2006\r\n</a> -- for a special pre-conference youth intensive, or at our Saturday workshop!\r\n<br /><br /></strong>\r\nOctober 19 @ Marin, California -- Bioneers Youth Intensive\r\nWHICH STORY? WHICH FUTURE?\r\nVision and Strategy for the Next Generation\r\nFor Young Activists (18 to 30 year-olds)\r\n-- <strong>including a special evening on the &quot;space bridge&quot; with the Council of Indigenous Grandmothers LIVE from Darmasala India!</strong><br /><br />\r\nOctober 21 @ Marin, California -- Bioneers Conference Workshop\r\nCHANGE THE STORY:\r\nNew Strategies for Shifting Culture\r\nFor Bioneers conference goers!\r\n<br /><br />\r\nTO REGISTER <a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org/conference\">CLICK HERE\r\n</a><br /><br /><br /><strong>VICTORY! <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org\">Safe Cosmetics Campaign </a> wins on OPI -- New York TImes Story!</strong>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n\r\nFor over two years now smartMeme has collaborated with the Campaign for Safe Cosmetics -- an innovative coalition of women\'s, public health and environmental justice groups who are working to get toxic chemicals out of personal care products. We have provided facilitation, strategy consultation and designed several full page ads for the campaign.  \r\n<br /><br />\r\nSmartMeme\'s latest ad targeted OPI for their use of dangerous chemicals. See ad <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org/docUploads/Miss%20Treatment%20OPI%5F2006%5F8%2E5x11%2Epdf\">HERE! </a><br /><br />\r\n\r\nResponding to the Safe Cosmetics Campaign  pressure, OPI has agreed to remove the dangerous chemical -- dibutyl pthalate from their nail polish!!! OPI is the latest in an industry wide shift away from toxics due in great part to the savvy work of our friends at SafeCo!\r\n<br /><br />\r\nThis is another victory for the campaign and one more step towards a cancer-free economy!\r\n<br /><br /><strong>Nail Polish Makers Yield on Disputed Chemical\r\nThe New York Times</strong><br /><br />\r\n By NATASHA SINGER\r\n<br /><br />\r\nBOWING to pressure from environmental groups and European lawmakers,several cosmetics makers are removing a chemical from nail polish that is suspected of interfering with the endocrine system.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nOrly International and OPI Products have already started selling reformulated nail polishes without the chemical, dibutyl phthalate. Sally Hansen plans to start selling similarly reformulated products in 2007.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nSome studies have linked exposure to dibutyl phthalate - a plasticizing ingredient that has been used to increase flexibility in nail polishes as well as medical equipment - with testicular problems in rats and humans. The chemical is banned from use in cosmetics in Europe and is considered a reproductive toxin by California.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nA study that examined nail polishes and perfumes, published in 2004 in The Journal of Toxicology and Environmental Health, concluded that the amount of exposure to dibutyl phthalate from these cosmetics is relatively small. The study cautioned, however, that total exposure to the chemical from multiple sources may be greater and requires further investigation.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nCompanies are adjusting formulas even though beauty executives said the ingredient is safe in the concentrations in which it is used in cosmetics.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n&quot;We are reacting here to changing consumer trends and a changing regulatory environment,&quot; said Bruce MacKay, the vice president for scientific affairs/R&amp;D of Del Laboratories, the maker of Sally Hansen. &quot;In high concentrations in lab experiments, these materials may be of concern, but there is no body of evidence that says this particular ingredient is not safe in the concentration in which it is used in nail products.&quot;\r\n<br /><br />\r\nBut health groups like the Breast Cancer Fund, an advocacy group in San Francisco that focuses on the environment, said that phthalates are too risky to use in consumer products.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n &quot;If there is evidence that an ingredient causes or is suspected of causing cancer or birth defects, cosmetics companies should not be using it in their products,&quot; said Kevin Donegan, the group\'s director of communications. &quot;Phthalates have clearly been demonstrated to cause harm.&quot;\r\n<br /><br /></font><font size=\"2\">\r\n</font>\r\n\r\n </p>','','2006-10-11 21:02:51',9,1,1,'whatsnew',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'bioneers-logo-final.jpg','Catch smartMeme @ the 2006 Bioneers Conference in Marin, CA October 19-22: Register <a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org/conference\"> here! </a>',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','smartmeme bioneers ','smartmeme bioneers STORY \"doyle canning\" \"patrick reinsborough\" \"katie joaquin\" \"james bell\"'),(1270,211,'smartMeme Fall 2006','Victory for Safe Cosmetics Campaign!\r\nSTORY in Immokalee...\r\nsmartMeme @ Bioneers...\r\n','\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Download our latest <a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/dowloads/Fall06STORYappealFINAL.pdf\">STORY Letter</a> !</font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>September 21-24 @ Immokalee, Florida <br /><br />\r\nSTORY at <a href=\"http://www.sfalliance.org\">Student Farmworker Alliance Youth Encuentro 2006\r\n</a></strong><br /><a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/Fall06STORYappealFINAL.pdf\"><br /></a><br />\r\nDozens of young organizers and activists from across the country gathered in Immokalee, Florida for three days of strategizing about the struggle for fair food, farmworker rights and building a more just world. Standing in solidarity with the Coalition of Immokalee Workers, the SFA is taking their campaign for human rights to McDonald\'s and the rest of the fast-food industry!\r\n<br /><br />\r\nTrainers from smartMemeï¿½s  STORY program went down to Florida to strategize with SFA to analyze the McDonald\'s &quot;story,&quot; and train SFA activists in story-based strategy. We&nbsp; also shared lessons and allia