rtMeme @ Bioneers National Conference...\r\nVictory for Safe Cosmetics Campaign!\r\n\r\n','\r\n<p><font size=\"3\"><strong><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Happy Holidays from <em>smart</em>Meme! Download our Season\'s Greetings Letter <a href=\"http://smartmeme.com/downloads/sMHolidayLetter2006.pdf\">here</a>...</font></strong></font> Your <font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\">gift of solidarity</a> can make a difference and help <em>smart</em>Meme change the story in 2007...</font><br /></p><p>&nbsp;<font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>STORY Program Kickin\' It in Oakland...</strong><br /></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><em>Smart</em>Meme\'s youth program <strong>STORY (strategy, training and organizing resources 4 youth)</strong> gathered for our Fall 2006 STORY Board retreat November 9-13 at the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ctwo.org/\">Center for Third World Organizing</a>\r\nin Oakland California.&nbsp; We welcomed 4 new STORY Board members, schemed\r\nand dreamed about 2007, and also offered an all day Training for Youth\r\nTrainers for our Bay Area \'peeps. </font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">And we also threw a great birthday party for STORY! Thanks to all of you who came out to celebrate with us!<br /></font> </p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Check out the fresh STORY website: <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org/\">changing the story dot org</a> !</font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong><em>Smart</em>Meme\'s Got the Bioneers Buzz...&nbsp;</strong></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><em> Smart</em>Meme was busy at<a href=\"http://www.bioneers.org\"> Bioneers 2006\r\n</a> -- with a special pre-conference youth intensive, several panels and standing room only at our Saturday workshop!\r\n<br /></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong> Listen</strong> to the <em>smart</em>Meme workshop @ the 2006 Bioneers\r\nConference<a href=\"https://secure.bioneers.org/audio/by/title/change_the_story_new_strategies_for_shifting_culture\"> </a><a href=\"https://secure.bioneers.org/audio/by/title/change_the_story_new_strategies_for_shifting_culture\">here!&nbsp;</a></span></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">We are also proud to be in ongoing partnership with Bioneers and looking forward to changing the story together in 2007!</font><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><br /></font><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong><br /></strong></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>VICTORY! <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org\">Safe Cosmetics Campaign </a> wins on OPI -- New York TImes Story!</strong>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n\r\nFor over two years now smartMeme has collaborated with the Campaign for Safe Cosmetics -- an innovative coalition of women\'s, public health and environmental justice groups who are working to get toxic chemicals out of personal care products. We have provided facilitation, strategy consultation and designed several full page ads for the campaign.  \r\n<br /><br />\r\nSmartMeme\'s latest ad targeted OPI for their use of dangerous chemicals. See ad <a href=\"http://www.safecosmetics.org/docUploads/Miss%20Treatment%20OPI%5F2006%5F8%2E5x11%2Epdf\">HERE! </a><br /><br />\r\n\r\nResponding to the Safe Cosmetics Campaign  pressure, OPI has agreed to remove the dangerous chemical -- dibutyl pthalate from their nail polish!!! OPI is the latest in an industry wide shift away from toxics due in great part to the savvy work of our friends at SafeCo!\r\n<br /><br />\r\nThis is another victory for the campaign and one more step towards a cancer-free economy!\r\n<br /><br /><strong>Nail Polish Makers Yield on Disputed Chemical\r\nThe New York Times</strong><br /><br />\r\n By NATASHA SINGER\r\n<br /><br />\r\nBOWING to pressure from environmental groups and European lawmakers,several cosmetics makers are removing a chemical from nail polish that is suspected of interfering with the endocrine system.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nOrly International and OPI Products have already started selling reformulated nail polishes without the chemical, dibutyl phthalate. Sally Hansen plans to start selling similarly reformulated products in 2007.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nSome studies have linked exposure to dibutyl phthalate - a plasticizing ingredient that has been used to increase flexibility in nail polishes as well as medical equipment - with testicular problems in rats and humans. The chemical is banned from use in cosmetics in Europe and is considered a reproductive toxin by California.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nA study that examined nail polishes and perfumes, published in 2004 in The Journal of Toxicology and Environmental Health, concluded that the amount of exposure to dibutyl phthalate from these cosmetics is relatively small. The study cautioned, however, that total exposure to the chemical from multiple sources may be greater and requires further investigation.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nCompanies are adjusting formulas even though beauty executives said the ingredient is safe in the concentrations in which it is used in cosmetics.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n&quot;We are reacting here to changing consumer trends and a changing regulatory environment,&quot; said Bruce MacKay, the vice president for scientific affairs/R&amp;D of Del Laboratories, the maker of Sally Hansen. &quot;In high concentrations in lab experiments, these materials may be of concern, but there is no body of evidence that says this particular ingredient is not safe in the concentration in which it is used in nail products.&quot;\r\n<br /><br />\r\nBut health groups like the Breast Cancer Fund, an advocacy group in San Francisco that focuses on the environment, said that phthalates are too risky to use in consumer products.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n &quot;If there is evidence that an ingredient causes or is suspected of causing cancer or birth defects, cosmetics companies should not be using it in their products,&quot; said Kevin Donegan, the group\'s director of communications. &quot;Phthalates have clearly been demonstrated to cause harm.&quot;\r\n<br /><br /></font><font size=\"2\">\r\n</font>\r\n\r\n </p>','','2006-11-28 18:39:31',9,1,1,'whatsnew',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,0,0,'','pdf',NULL,8,'',0,'','2005-12-28',1,0,0,0,'2007STORYboard.jpg','<b> Welcome </b> to the 2006-2007 STORY Board! Visit STORY online <a href=\"http://www.changingthestory.org\"> here! </a>',1,'',0,1,'','','right','',0,'original','0000-00-00 00:00:00',1,'','',1,1,0,'','','','','','','smartmeme bioneers ','smartmeme bioneers STORY \"doyle canning\" \"patrick reinsborough\" \"katie joaquin\" \"james bell\"'),(1283,211,'smartMeme Winter 2007','New strategy resources from smartMeme!\r\nSTORY program work: Iraq Veterans Against the War & DC Fair Budget Coalition\r\nLISTEN to smartMeme @ Bioneers National Conference...\r\n\r\n\r\n','</p><p>&nbsp;<font size=\"2\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong><b>New</b> Strategy Resources from <i>smart</i>Meme!<br><br>\r\nCheck out our new <i>smartMeme Elements</i>essays, which also serve as an invitation to join smartMeme as a member! Your <font size=\"3\" face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\">membership</a> can make a difference and help change the story in 2007...</font><br />\r\n\r\nNew Downloads!<br><br>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/smartmeme.storybasedstrategy.pdf\">Story-Based Strategy: How Changing the Story Changes the World</a><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.smartmeme.com/downloads/smartmeme.memes.pdf\">Memes and Smart Memes: Shifting Culture With Contagious T