INSERT INTO `blast` VALUES (1,'Email-Admin','2006-12-15 19:04:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','info@smartMeme.com','smartMeme',NULL,'info@smartMeme.com','It is better to light a candle...',NULL,'<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">...<em><strong> than to curse the darkness.</strong></em><br />~Confucius<br /><br />Dear friends and fellow change agents, <br /><br />Season’s greetings from the <em>smart</em>Meme collective!<br /><br />With your support, the <em>smart</em>Meme Strategy &amp; Training Project has made 2006 another inspirational year of shifting stories and making positive change possible. Our groundbreaking work to harness the power of story telling for social change continues to strengthen movements for peace, justice, democracy, and ecological sanity. <u>With the hard work and contributions of people like you,</u> we are winning victories today and supporting tomorrow’s visionaries through our youth leadership program STORY – Strategy Training and Organizing Resources for Youth. </font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">We are writing to invite you to join us and </font><font size=\"2\" face=\"verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">give online today at <a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\">smartmeme.com</a></font><br /><font size=\"2\" face=\"verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><br /><em>Smart</em>Meme’s programs bring intergenerational circles of people together to tell stories of dignity, justice, peace, and guardianship of future generations. We write to you now because we know you share our aspirations for a better world. You are already an important participant in this circle of circles--and this season, <u>we invite you to step further into our circle by becoming a <em>smart</em>Meme member with an annual contribution of $35, $50, $100 or more. </u><br /><br /><strong>Why should you join as a member?</strong> Because smartMeme is one of the most fun, dynamic, strategic, and effective social change organizations in the US today…and by supporting <em>smart</em>Meme, you support campaigns, leaders, organizations and networks who are driving the rising tide of progressive change. <br /><br />And of course, smartMeme’s 2006 work to change the story has been getting results: <br /><br /></font></p><ul><li><font size=\"2\" face=\"verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><em>Smart</em>Meme created a powerful advertisement for the Safe Cosmetics Campaign (Featuring a “Miss Treatment” beauty pageant) targeting nail polish manufacturer OPI for its use of toxic chemicals. After the ad helped galvanize public opposition, OPI pledged to remove the toxic “dibutyl phthalate” from their nail polishes, starting a new safety trend the industry can’t ignore!</font></li><li><font size=\"2\" face=\"verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><em>Smart</em>Meme’s STORY program partnered with the youth-based human rights group Not With Our Money! to challenge investors in private for-profit prison corporations. The campaign targeted Farallon Investments and succeeded in getting them to fully divest from CCA, the largest private prison corporation in the U.S. </font></li><li><font size=\"2\" face=\"verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">In 2006 <em>smart</em>Meme staff were <u>on the ground in 15 states training, speaking, strategizing and rabble rousing to support front line organizers in hard-hitting, effective campaigns.</u> From supporting the youth-farmworker campaign targeting McDonald’s for fair wages in the tomato fields of Immokalee, Florida…to helping the township of Zilwaukee, Michigan stop Dow Chemical’s toxic pollution of the Great Lakes…to convening Iraq Veterans Against the War and National Youth &amp; Student Peace Coalition to forge strategies for peace at the historic Highlander Center, the inspiring movement-building center where Rosa Parks got her training….</font></li></ul><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><br />In the last 12 months, <em>smart</em>Meme has collaborated with over 25 organizations to collaborate for change. <em>Smart</em>Meme is a comprehensive source for strategy, messaging, and campaign support for a wide cross section of networks who are lighting the candles of hope, instead of cursing in the darkness. <br /><br />We invite you to lend your light to <em>smart</em>Meme and share the warmth of hope and solidarity. <u>A contribution as part of our new membership program is the best way to support us as an emergent national organization and to spread narrative analysis and story-based strategies to the movements who are making a difference.</u><br /><br />With an annual membership contribution of $35, $50, $100 or more, you can <strong>help us reach our goal of 1,000 individual members,</strong> and be a partner in smartMeme’s innovative and inspirational work. <br /></font></p><p><font size=\"2\" face=\"verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Please Give online today at <a href=\"https://secure.groundspring.org/dn/index.php?aid=9879\">smartmeme.com</a><br /><br />In 2007, we are looking forward to continuing to support grassroots organizing and advocacy work with the power of story-based strategies. We plan to continue to grow the STORY youth program and the Peace Collaborative, as well as advance the idea of the Commons and our work for democracy and an ecological future. We will also be piloting a “story-based strategy circle” in the San Francisco Bay Area, convening youth leadership gatherings, working to combat climate change, and so much more…<br /><br /><em>Smart</em>Meme’s vision is to cultivate diverse, intergenerational alliances to achieve lasting change that can sustain future generations, build a culture of peace, and actualize an economy of justice. <em><strong>Join us with a gift of solidarity this season.</strong></em><br /><br />Be in Touch, and May Peace Be Upon You and Yours…<br /><br />The smartMeme collective....<br />James John Bell<br />Doyle Canning<br />J Cookson<br />Katie Joaquin<br />Patrick Reinsborough</font><br /><br />\r\n</p>','...than to curse the darkness.\r\n~Confucius\r\n\r\nHoliday 2006\r\n\r\nDear friends and fellow change agents,\r\n\r\nSeason’s greetings from the smartMeme collective!\r\n\r\nWith your support, the smartMeme Strategy & Training Project has made 2006 another inspirational year of shifting stories and making positive change possible. Our groundbreaking work to harness the power of story telling for social change continues to strengthen movements for peace, justice, democracy, and ecological sanity. With the hard work and contributions of people like you, we are winning victories today and supporting tomorrow’s visionaries through our youth leadership program STORY – Strategy Training and Organizing Resources for Youth.\r\n\r\nWe are writing to invite you to join us and give online today at http://smartmeme.com\r\n\r\nSmartMeme’s programs bring intergenerational circles of people together to tell stories of dignity, justice, peace, and guardianship of future generations. We write to you now because we know you share our aspirations for a better world. You are already an important participant in this circle of circles--and this season, we invite you to step further into our circle by becoming a smartMeme member with an annual contribution of $35, $50, $100 or more.\r\n\r\nWhy should you join as a member? Because smartMeme is one of the most fun, dynamic, strategic, and effective social change organizations in the US today…and by supporting smartMeme, you support campaigns, leaders, organizations and networks who are driving the rising tide of progressive change.\r\n\r\nAnd of course, smartMeme’s 2006 work to change the story has been getting results:\r\n\r\n    * SmartMeme created a powerful advertisement for the Safe Cosmetics Campaign (Featuring a “Miss Treatment” beauty pageant) targeting nail polish manufacturer OPI for its use of toxic chemicals. After the ad helped galvanize public opposition, OPI pledged to remove the toxic “dibutyl phthalate” from their nail polishes, starting a new safety trend the industry can’t ignore!\r\n    * SmartMeme’s STORY program partnered with the youth-based human rights group Not With Our Money! to challenge investors in private for-profit prison corporations. The campaign targeted Farallon Investments and succeeded in getting them to fully divest from CCA, the largest private prison corporation in the U.S.\r\n    * In 2006 smartMeme staff were on the ground in 15 states training, speaking, strategizing and rabble rousing to support front line organizers in hard-hitting, effective campaigns. From supporting the youth-farmworker campaign targeting McDonald’s for fair wages in the tomato fields of Immokalee, Florida…to helping the township of Zilwaukee, Michigan stop Dow Chemical’s toxic pollution of the Great Lakes…to convening Iraq Veterans Against the War and National Youth & Student Peace Coalition to forge strategies for peace at the historic Highlander Center, the inspiring movement-building center where Rosa Parks got her training….\r\n\r\n\r\nIn the last 12 months, smartMeme has collaborated with over 25 organizations to collaborate for change. SmartMeme is a comprehensive source for strategy, messaging, and campaign support for a wide cross section of networks who are lighting the candles of hope, instead of cursing in the darkness.\r\n\r\nWe invite you to lend your light to smartMeme and share the warmth of hope and solidarity. A contribution as part of our new membership program is the best way to support us as an emergent national organization and to spread narrative analysis and story-based strategies to the movements who are making a difference.\r\n\r\nWith an annual membership contribution of $35, $50, $100 or more, you can help us reach our goal of 1,000 individual members, and be a partner in smartMeme’s innovative and inspirational work.\r\n\r\nPlease Give online today at http://smartmeme.com\r\n\r\nIn 2007, we are looking forward to continuing to support grassroots organizing and advocacy work with the power of story-based strategies. We plan to continue to grow the STORY youth program and the Peace Collaborative, as well as advance the idea of the Commons and our work for democracy and an ecological future. We will also be piloting a “story-based strategy circle” in the San Francisco Bay Area, convening youth leadership gatherings, working to combat climate change, and so much more…\r\n\r\nSmartMeme’s vision is to cultivate diverse, intergenerational alliances to achieve lasting change that can sustain future generations, build a culture of peace, and actualize an economy of justice. Join us with a gift of solidarity this season.\r\n\r\nBe in Touch, and May Peace Be Upon You and Yours…\r\n\r\nThe smartMeme collective....\r\nJames John Bell\r\nDoyle Canning\r\nJ Cookson\r\nKatie Joaquin\r\nPatrick Reinsborough',NULL,'HTML and Text',0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'Complete',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,30,'','','','1','NORMAL',NULL,'2006-12-15 19:04:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0);
